        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:04:41.773000Z",
        "message": "Can you give me an example? What kind of question or or situation makes you reach for Google, and what sort leads you to use ChatGPT?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c697c50c893f4f45b70c28589",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:04:51.344000Z",
        "message": "I would use Google for a more vague answer, but chat GPT, something way more specific like I was saying before about an exact answer on a test."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c697c50c893f4f45b70c28589",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:05:02.684000Z",
        "message": "That's a super clear split. When you get a vague answer, from Google or a specific 1 from ChatGPT, how do those answers feel different to you? For example, do you notice differences in in detail, certainty, or maybe just the tone of the response?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c697c50c893f4f45b70c28589",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:05:19.564000Z",
        "message": "I feel like ChatGPT has the exact answer that I was looking for, where Google would just give me, like, a roundabout answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c697c50c893f4f45b70c28589",
        "index": 30,
