      {
        "callId": "c697c50c893f4f45b70c28589",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:07:08.764000Z",
        "message": "That's a colorful comparison. What makes you see ChatGPT as the egotistical maniac who knows everything? And for Google, can you say more about that laid back Elon Musk vibe?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c697c50c893f4f45b70c28589",
        "index": 43,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:07:23.214000Z",
        "message": "Because I feel like any person who knew everything out there, which I feel like that AI has potential for. Is always gonna be the person who stands out and thinks that, obviously, they're better than anyone else. Knowing everything."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c697c50c893f4f45b70c28589",
        "index": 44,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:07:43.883000Z",
        "message": "Interesting take. And, uh, with Google feeling like a laid back Elon Musk, do you mean by that? Is it about confidence, coolness, or something else?"
