      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:59:04.023000Z",
        "message": "No worries."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:59:05.774000Z",
        "message": "yeah. I was working on a project to get a little ad for Instagram, and I was working on Canva. And so I was asking on what would be the best way, you know, what would be the best way of saying approaching this? Should I say this? Give me some ideas of what I should my script should be uh, find some images that might fit the the ad that I was going for, things like that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:59:44.714000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So you're juggling Instagram, Canva, and turning to Gemini for guidance. When you started asking Gemini for our help, like script ideas or or image suggestions, What happens step by step? How did it respond? And what did you do with its advice?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:00:02.754000Z",
        "message": "With the device I'm sorry. Could you clarify that?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:00:07.944000Z",
        "message": "Sure. I just meant when Gemini gave you its responses, like the script ideas or or image suggestions, what did you actually do next? Did you copy them straight into Canva, tweak them, or maybe look somewhere else too? Just curious what's your next steps look like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:00:24.493000Z",
        "message": "On this particular project, I didn't really look elsewhere, but I did kind of tweak, you know, the is it Gemini will respond, and I would say, well, that's that's a great image, but I really was looking for something more that had, a family in distress or something like that. So I did a lot of fine tuning on some of the information that Gemini gave me to fit what I was trying to do."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:00:57.614000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful. So you get a baseline from Gemini, then go back and forth to narrow it down. Kind of like a conversation. How did that feel emotionally or or practically? Anything stand out as especially helpful. Or maybe a bit frustrating during that exchange?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:01:15.844000Z",
        "message": "I found that working with images in Gemini was the most frustrating task that I've done with Gemini. Generally asking questions and getting answers or asking for research and getting information. Generally, it's pretty it was been pretty spot on, and and what impresses me the most is the speed that it comes up with answers. It's remarkable. The image search is a little bit more I think I need to learn how to refine what I'm asking a little bit better so that Gemini actually is understanding what I'm asking them. I think sometimes I would make it too general, and it would come up with something that just didn't work for me. But as I said, to pursue it and keep fine tuning the Eventually, it came on something that was suitable for me. I found the process great. I found it often working with geminitis. Pretty much like talking to someone, you know, your your assistant or a research or it's a very easy conversation. I kind of enjoy it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:02:34.254000Z",
        "message": "That paints a clear picture. Sounds like when it comes to words or facts, Gemini feels quick and accurate. Almost like having a helpful assistant. But with images, it can take a bit of back and forth, especially if the prompt isn't super specific. If you hadn't used Gemini for that Instagram project, what would you have done instead? Where would you have turned for things like script ideas or image suggestions?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:02:58.954000Z",
        "message": "Well, yeah, if I hadn't used Gemini, the the task would have taken probably double or even triple the time. I found prior to using Gemini is the most, time consuming task for me was to search images, and I would use, I try to use free services like Pix Pix I can't even think of it now. Unsplash is 1 1 and Pixabay is another. And it would be time to to be looking at the different images trying different ways. Again, trying to ask for different ways of saying what it was they needed to to find 1. It it was often very that was often the most time consuming part of the project that I was doing. So it is much easier with Gemini."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:03:58.194000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So Gemini mainly helped speed things up for you, especially around images. Which used to mean bouncing between Unsplash, Pixabay, and lots of trial and error. Does Gemini's help replace"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
