        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:04:11.124000Z",
        "message": "those other tools entirely for you or do you still find yourself double checking elsewhere sometimes?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:04:16.824000Z",
        "message": "Maybe sometimes if I you know, sometimes if I'm not really crazy about the the image, I'm, like, go out and see if I see something better. But often, I'm I'm happy with what I get, and I'm happy in saving the time and effort."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:04:34.934000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. So mostly Gemini gets the job done. But every now and then, you'll double check elsewhere if you're not thrilled with the results."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:04:43.423000Z",
        "message": "Correct."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:04:43.654000Z",
        "message": "Have you ever Thanks for clarifying. Now thinking about times you've used other answer engines, like GPT, Perplexity, or even Google, what kinds of tasks or situations push you to switch from Gemini? Can you tell me about a time that happened?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:05:01.244000Z",
        "message": "We don't I I I don't remember when the last time I used CHET CBT. I was never that thrilled about it. And as I said, when I got to be in that, that test group and it provided it first, it provided instructions on what to do and how to use it, and then it gave many, many different examples. I mean, we had to ask it questions. We had to ask it to edit something. We had to ask it to schedule an event for us or a travel or a vacation. We had to do some image work. So that's really what got me into Gemini. It was really very helpful. To go through that process and to get introduced to Gemini."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:05:52.374000Z",
        "message": "So it sounds like Gemini really won you over. During that test program, giving you hands on tasks that showed what it could do. And from then on, you haven't really felt the need to use Chatuche or others much at all. About Google? Do you find yourself using Google Search or their AI summaries anymore? Or does Gemini"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:06:10.244000Z",
        "message": "What Yeah. I do use Google Search and often Google Search the first thing that comes up is an AI respond. I I do use Google search, but generally, it's something, you know, like, what what's the nearest, what's the nearest Lowe's to my house or something like that. Something that I need that's not really too in-depth, and it's a quick search."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:06:39.184000Z",
        "message": "That's clear. For quick location style questions, Google Search is still in your mix."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
