        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:06:45.054000Z",
        "message": "And those AI summaries pop up first. For bigger or creative projects, Gemini takes takes the lead."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:06:48.004000Z",
        "message": "Yeah."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:06:51.274000Z",
        "message": "Now, if you think about the way Gemini answers feel versus Google or chat GPTs, how would you describe the difference? Anything come to mind about tone depth? The way it presents sources?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:07:04.004000Z",
        "message": "Well, like I said, I really didn't I can't even remember the last time I used and I really wasn't I don't know. It seemed to be more difficult to use, and it has been I'm sure it's improved since the last time I used it. You know? So and since Gemini worked so well for me, I just don't really use any other service."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:07:31.754000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So Gemini's ease and your positive experience with it have kept you from exploring others much even if they've improved. When you think about Gemini's answers, do any words or feelings come up? How would you describe its personality if it had 1?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:07:50.704000Z",
        "message": "I no. It depends again on what I'm doing. What comes to mind is there was I had a quite I was watching a TV show that had a very interesting cat, and I didn't familiar with what the breed was. So I went on Gemini and asked them if they knew what what this breed was. And we went through a couple of back and forth questions and answers, and they did it it came up with the breed and then, you know, the personality and what is a good breed for anyway, was a long conversation that was very fun and pleasant. And I even said at the end of it, I, uh, you know, it would've I would've even felt more like I was speaking to a person if it had a name rather than Gemini. I guess Gemini is the name, but, you know, like, Tony or Mary or you know? Hey. It just felt very, like, just a normal conversation with a another human being. It was very interesting and fun and pleasant."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:08:54.324000Z",
        "message": "That's a great story. So it felt friendly and conversational. Almost like talking to someone real, especially when you dug into details and had that back and forth. And it sounds like you found it enjoyable, not just useful. When you share answers you've gotten with others, say you forward a script or a fact, it matter to you? Which engine the info came from? Does 1 feel more credible or or quotable than another, or is that not something you really think about?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:09:23.554000Z",
        "message": "I guess I don't think about it too much. I do, I do ask, I do ask Gemini to edit my, um, emails, sometimes my responses, my letters. Even sometimes questions that I have for for my colleagues to to you know, my resume just to to update it and to make it sound, better and to say exactly what it is that I I want. And I've always been very pleased with the results, and I don't find I have no question about it or feel, you know, uncomfortable about it. It's not like I'm asking them to to make it up and give me something that I haven't already you know, it is my work. They're just polishing it, so I feel fine doing that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc3d117b394c4959a44d5b1d4",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:10:22.324000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. Sounds like Gemini Axe almost like a behind the scenes editor for you, and you feel comfortable putting your name to what comes out. Thinking back over the last year or so, has anything shifted about the way you look things up or get help online? Maybe how often you use Gemini? Or how much you rely on it compared to before."
      },
