    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:54:18.891000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:54:26.771000Z",
        "message": "Great."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:54:30.801000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. Let's jump in. When you need answers online, whether it's something quick or a bit more detailed, what's what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:54:40.541000Z",
        "message": "Well, I search it up on Google, And if I see that it doesn't make sense, then I'll go on to chat GPT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:54:48.571000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So Google is usually your starting point, then you turn to ChatGPT if things aren't clear. Can you walk me through the most recent time this happened? What were you searching for? And what made you switch from Google to ChatGP?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:04.841000Z",
        "message": "So I was looking for information on, um, King Charles the fifth. And, um, it really didn't, like, give me clear information. So I had to go on to chat GPT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:18.321000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Starting with your Google search for King Charles the fifth, what did you see or experience that felt unclear? It the search results, the summaries, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:31.721000Z",
        "message": "It was like the language was, like, really complicated. Like, it was had, like, some big words that I didn't really understand."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:40.891000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. Sometimes those results can get pretty dense. So you switched over to ChatGPT. Tell me about that experience. What was different about"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:47.051000Z",
        "message": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:49.061000Z",
        "message": "the answer you got there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:51.321000Z",
        "message": "Well, it was it was more in-depth. Which gave me a better, like, gave me a better understanding"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:56:03.751000Z",
        "message": "It sounds like ChatGPT gave you a a more thorough and easier to understand explanation. Was there anything about the way ChatGPT's answer was written or presented that made it especially helpful for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:56:18.071000Z",
        "message": "It seemed like it was, like, a good source and it seemed, uh, really reliable. Unlike Google, you don't, like, know where, like, all that information can come from."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:56:28.941000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So it sounds like seeing ChatGPT's answer felt more trustworthy. Even without knowing all the sources. When you're reading answers, what makes you feel confident that the information is reliable? Is it the tone, the details, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:56:45.891000Z",
        "message": "Well, before, uh, I'll look on Google, and I'll see if, like, the answer is, like, up with JATTPT. And then I'll get, like, a pretty good understanding of, like, what's right and what's wrong."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:56:59.071000Z",
        "message": "So you kind of cross check between Google and ChatGP to get a clearer picture when you're comparing their answers are you looking for matching facts, or do you focus more on which explanation makes the most sense to you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:57:12.951000Z",
        "message": "I checked for both matching facts and the information that, like, seems like would be true."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:57:22.001000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to hear. When you get answers from ChatGPT, Google or any other tool, do you ever look for extra details like sources or citations Or do you mainly go by how the answer feels and how clearly it's explained?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:57:35.031000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. I definitely need to look for, like, sources and citations to, like, to make sure it's, a a reliable and trustworthy source."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:57:45.710000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for clarifying. When you're using ChatGPT or Google, which 1 gives you what you need in terms of sources or site citations more often, or does it depend on the type of question you're asking?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:57:56.951000Z",
        "message": "Depends on the type of question I'm asking."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:58:01.921000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Can you share an example where the type of question changed which tool you chose or trusted more? Maybe a specific topic or situation, where 1 engine gave better sources or clarity than the other."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:58:16.791000Z",
        "message": "There was, um, more history assignments that I had to do, And instead of using, like, Google, I went into, like, more in-depth reliable sources such as, like, national geographics."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:58:31.861000Z",
        "message": "That's a great example. So for your history assignments, you sought out sources like National Geographic rather than just sticking with Google or ChatGPT. What made you choose National Geographic? And how did you get there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:58:44.441000Z",
        "message": "Because I knew it was my teacher actually gave me it to, like, use to test it out. And I think that it was, like, really nice and really helpful. To find the information that I needed."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:59:02.241000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So a teacher's suggestion played a big part in where you turn for answers. When you used National Geographic for your assignment, how did the experience compare to using Google or ChatGPT? Was anything noticeably different? About how you searched or what you got back?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:59:20.131000Z",
        "message": "Definitely. It was, like, really organized."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:59:25.031000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like organization made a big difference for you. Was it the way the information was broken down? The visuals, or just how easy it was to find what you needed? Tell me more about what made it feel organized compared to the others."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:59:38.400000Z",
        "message": "It was how it was broken down. Because, like, that really helped me, like, read like, like, understand the bigger picture. Like, it's not just, like, 1 big block of text."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:59:53.001000Z",
        "message": "That paints a clear picture. So having information broken into sections or steps helps you grasp the bigger picture rather than having to wade through a wall of text Thinking back to Google and ChatGPT, is there anything you wish they did the way National Geographic does in terms of the way they present answers or"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:00:09.391000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. Definitely. Pictures and, like, how National Geographic's, like, broke it down. Like, ChatGPT is just, like, 1 big block of text."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:00:21.421000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. If you could design the the perfect answer engine for yourself, what are some features or qualities you'd want it to have, maybe borrowing from National Geographic ChatGPT, or Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:00:35.851000Z",
        "message": "Definitely, an area that has all of all of the sources all the sources and pictures and not a big block of text."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:00:50.060000Z",
        "message": "Makes total sense. Source is all in 1 spot, visuals, and answers that aren't just a big text wall that's hard to read. Thinking about your habits over time, has anything changed in the past year about which answer engine you use first? Or how often you switch between them? If so, what triggered the shift"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:01:09.901000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. I only changed my like, sources for, like, history. Because, like, I don't, like, know any other sources for, like, other subjects. That I can't just go and ask the teacher."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:01:27.411000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to know. For most topics, you're still starting with Google or ChatGPT. Except for history, where you rely more on, uh, trusted sources suggested by your teacher. If you were to get source recommendations for other subjects do you think you'd change your habits there too? Or would you stick with what you're already using?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:01:48.471000Z",
        "message": "Definitely. I would give it a try to see, like, how well it works. And then if it's if it's, like, better, then I'll switch."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:01:56.901000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense? Uh, open to switching. A new source proves helpful. When you share answers with friends or classmates, um, do you mention which engine or or source you used, or does it usually not come up?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:02:09.181000Z",
        "message": "Yes. I would I would source my cite my sources."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:02:20.111000Z",
        "message": "Got it. You make a point to cite your sources when sharing answers. When you mention ChatGPT, Google, or National Geographic, Do people have any reactions, like trust, skepticism, or curiosity, or do they usually accept it?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:02:35.031000Z",
        "message": "They usually are, like, curious on, like, how it works, but then they're, like, accepted, like, after I show them, like, all of this and that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:02:44.311000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So people are curious at first, but once you show them where the info came from or how you got it, they're comfortable with it. If you imagine ChatGPT, Google, National Geographic, or even Perplexity or Gemini as people at a party what kind of personalities do you see them having?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 43,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:03:03.411000Z",
        "message": "Very reliable. I would say that they're very intelligent."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 44,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:03:08.601000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. If you compare those engines, Google, ChatGPT, National Geographic, or the others who feels most approachable to you, and who feels more distant or hard to connect with based on your experience."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 45,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:03:22.921000Z",
        "message": "Can you repeat that question?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 46,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:03:26.261000Z",
        "message": "Of course, out of Google, ChatGPT, National Geographic, Perplexity, or Gemini, which 1 feels most approachable and friendly to you? And is there any that feel more distant or harder to connect with?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 47,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:03:39.351000Z",
        "message": "Definitely, National Geographics is, like, the easiest 1 to approach because like I said, it's just like really easy to, like, figure out and get the information that you need."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 48,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:03:52.260000Z",
        "message": "That's clear. National Geographic feels easiest to approach for you. Is there any engine or tool that feels more distant, maybe hard to use, or not as welcoming? If so, what about it makes it feel that way."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 49,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:04:06.331000Z",
        "message": "Definitely, Google feels more distant because, like, I don't know where all that information came from, and it's hard to, like, cite Google. As a source."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 50,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:04:17.361000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Uh, earlier, you mentioned switching engines. When an answer didn't make sense. If you ever found another engine that was quicker, clearer, or easier to cite,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 51,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:04:24.021000Z",
        "message": "Okay."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 52,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:04:27.901000Z",
        "message": "than Google, what would make you switch over to using it more often or even make it your new go to?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 53,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:04:40.981000Z",
        "message": "Just use it, I guess."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 54,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:04:45.331000Z",
        "message": "Sounds straightforward. If another tool does the job better, you'll just start using it. For being so open today about your habits and preferences. Before we wrap up, did you have any thoughts about whole AI interview experience or anything else you want to add?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 55,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:05:00.621000Z",
        "message": "No. I think the AI was really helpful."
      },
      {
        "callId": "bbd57a6b83aa49c5a5be1f10f",
        "index": 56,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:05:06.141000Z",
        "message": "Thank you for calling."
      }
