        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:53:22.614000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:53:31.004000Z",
        "message": "I'm horrible."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:53:35.714000Z",
        "message": "I'm really sorry to hear that. Want to talk about what's on your mind, or would you rather we stick to the research for now? Totally up to you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:53:42.533000Z",
        "message": "We could sync to the research for now."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:53:47.074000Z",
        "message": "Got it. And thanks for letting me know. If you ever wanna talk about something else, just say so. So to start us off, when you need answers online, say you're curious about something, or need to figure something out, what's what's the very first thing you usually do? Feel free to ask me any questions. Feel free to ask me any questions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:54:23.144000Z",
        "message": "I don't know what to ask you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:54:26.324000Z",
        "message": "No worries at all. There's no wrong way to do this. Um, I'm just here to learn about how you look things up online. Let's make it easy. Can you remember the last time you searched for an answer or information online? Tell me what you were looking for and what you did first."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:54:43.714000Z",
        "message": "I was looking for some nonslip shoes for work, and I went to Walmart on the app, and that was the first place I chose to look for non slip resistant shoes. So that way I could, um, well, I needed them for work. So I they said they had them there the cheapest, so that's the first place that I had went."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:04.194000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. So you need to choose for work. And, uh, you started straight with Walmart's app to find them."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:07.844000Z",
        "message": "Yes. Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:11.583000Z",
        "message": "I'm curious, what made you pick Walmart to start your search? Instead of say Google or another website?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:18.174000Z",
        "message": "Because Walmart's close to my house, and it's lit literally right next to my work. So once I found them, found that Walmart had them and they had my size, I just bought them when I was on my way to work."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:33.824000Z",
        "message": "That's super practical. Makes a lot of sense. To go for the nearby store. When you were searching in the Walmart app, did you have to look through many results, or did you find what you needed pretty quickly? Tell me about that experience."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:47.694000Z",
        "message": "I I just looked up nonslip resistant shoes, and I just I mean, I scrolled for a little bit to find the ones that"
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:59.014000Z",
        "message": "You scrolled for a bit. Sounds like you had some choices. What helped you decide which shoes to pick? Was it price, reviews, the look, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:56:10.564000Z",
        "message": "And the the price and the look had a lot to do."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:56:17.654000Z",
        "message": "Got it. The price and the look mattered most. Did you check any reviews or ratings before you bought, or was it mostly about seeing the shoes and the cost? Tell me more about what you noticed or checked before, uh, deciding."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:56:31.724000Z",
        "message": "No. I I went. I saw shoes that I liked, and I saw that they were non slip resistant. I put them I tried them on. I made sure they were comfortable. And once I walked around and felt they were comfortable enough for me, that's when I was like, okay. And then I checked the price. If the price was good enough for me, that's when I decided to be like, okay. Comfortable and not expensive. I'm gonna buy these."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:56:55.634000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for walking me through what you did. Sounds like comfort, price, and making sure they had that non slip feature were the big things for you. Switching gears bit, you ever need info, not shopping, more like advice or quick answers online, do you usually use first? Google, ChatGPT,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:57:13.254000Z",
        "message": "Alright. Usually go to Google first because that's the first thing that I think of ever since I was younger. I would always be like, oh, Google. Google. So I always go to Google first."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:57:27.304000Z",
        "message": "That habit runs deep. When you go to Google for answers, you walk me through what you do step by step? For example, say you have a random question. What do you type? What do you look at first? How do you pick which result to read?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:57:41.794000Z",
        "message": "Well, now that Google has a AI, I'll type in my question or whatever I'm looking for, searching for. And I'll read the AI to see what it says first. But then I'll go down to scroll to see other online websites that give advice about that just to see if the AI matches the advice from legit companies."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:58:07.394000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. You're checking the AI summary first. But then you double check by looking at advice from other sites to make sure it lines up. What makes you wanna compare the AI Answer against those other sources? What are you hoping to see or maybe avoid?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:58:23.384000Z",
        "message": "I just wanna make sure that AI is working as people and companies are promising it to work."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:58:34.734000Z",
        "message": "Totally understandable. You wanna be sure the AI is actually giving accurate answers. Like everyone says it will. Has the AI ever given"
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:58:41.274000Z",
        "message": "That's correct."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:58:45.154000Z",
        "message": "has there ever been a time when the Google AI summary gave you an answer that seemed off, made you feel unsure. If so, how did you handle that?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:58:55.614000Z",
        "message": "No. Not at all. Like, every I mean, I'm like, every time I seen what it says, like, it's, uh, like, I know. I'm like, okay. That seems a little bit accurate, but I'll go to somewhere else and be like, let me make sure just to see. And it it turns out right so far. Like, Google has always been 1 of the best search engines."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:59:16.214000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like so far, Google's AI summaries have matched up with what you find on other sites, and they feel accurate to you. So even though you trust Google, you still like to double check. Just in case. Have you ever tried other AI answer engines, like ChatGPT Perplexity or Gemini for questions or advice? If so, what's the story there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:59:36.444000Z",
        "message": "No. I I've never tried. The only other AI that I've tried is Meta."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:59:42.554000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. You've tried Meadows AI too. What kind of questions or things did you use Meta for? And how did that experience compare to using Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:59:52.094000Z",
        "message": "I just searched it to find places and like, I, um, like, pages of places that are there so I could like them. That's about it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:00:03.294000Z",
        "message": "So mostly just looking up places or pages you might want to follow, or, like, was there anything about using Meta's AI that stood out to you good or bad? Or did it just feel pretty straightforward?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:00:18.404000Z",
        "message": "I mean, it's Facebook. You it's either pick and choose."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:00:25.614000Z",
        "message": "Gotcha. So it kinda feels like take it or leave it. Nothing special or memorable compared to Google. Last quick question. Uh, if you suddenly needed, say, really detailed advice or something tricky and, uh, Google gave you a summary that didn't feel helpful, what would you do next?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:00:43.364000Z",
        "message": "I will scroll down Google to find an online resource that is the information I'm looking for that's resourceful? Like, for sure approved, and I'll search there to just to make sure that it matches what Google's AI is saying."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:01:01.864000Z",
        "message": "So you'd stick with Google, but look deeper for a more solid source when the summary isn't enough Does anything ever make you think about switching to a different tool Maybe something friends mentioned, an ad, or frustration with Google, or is Google just still your main pick no matter what?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:01:20.824000Z",
        "message": "Google all day."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:01:24.594000Z",
        "message": "That's clear and simple. Google's still your go to. Thanks for sharing all this. Last thing before we wrap up, any wish list feature or something you wish was different about how you find answers online. Doesn't matter how wild or small. Curious what comes to mind, if anything."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:01:42.244000Z",
        "message": "No. Google does a good job at informing me on all of my interests because they've already asked me my interests, um, when I first joined Google. So they know what I like. Um, what they could do is probably, like, every other maybe 2 months inform me of, like, have your interest changed so that way I could add new interest if they have changed."
      },
      {
        "callId": "6e4f9d05801c4e3980ddfa3ae",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T01:02:04.703000Z",
        "message": "That's a thoughtful suggestion. Having Google check-in every couple of months to ask if your interests have changed so it can help you stay up to date on what matters to you. Appreciate that detail. Thanks for talking with me today and sharing your honest thoughts. If you ever wanna chat again or have questions, you know where to find me, you can end the call. Whenever you'd like. Wishing you a better rest of your day."
      }
    ],
