  {
    "id": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
    "responseId": "cb3be670f94e4562a28dce5d5",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:51:42.272000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:51:50.482000Z",
        "message": "My day is going alright. Thank you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:51:54.232000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. Let's jump in. When you need answers online, maybe for something quick or to settle a debate, what's what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:52:03.352000Z",
        "message": "I go to the Google bar and I either type it in or I use the voice, uh, typer thing to get an answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:52:15.292000Z",
        "message": "Got it. You're reaching for Google right off the bat. Can you walk me through what happens next step by step when you search for something start from entering your question, and then just narrate everything you typically do until you find out your answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:52:30.061000Z",
        "message": "So I type in the question, and then when it loads up, normally, I look for the little synopsis that will show up at the top, like the little overview. And then if I can't find that, then I'll go through, like, each of the individual results and then see which 1 gives me the answer I'm looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:52:49.902000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for laying that out. Thinking about that top overview, sometimes called an answer box or snippet, what's most helpful about it for you. And have you ever found it frustrating or lacking some way?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:53:04.432000Z",
        "message": "I've never found it frustrating or lacking in any way, but the thing that I like the most about it is the fact that it is basically a summary and it's right there. And I don't have to look for the answer like it's in the synopsis."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:53:18.962000Z",
        "message": "That sounds super convenient? Outside of those quick overviews, is there ever a time when Google doesn't give you what you need? Like, the answer is missing, unclear, or feels incomplete. If so, what do you do next?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:53:33.702000Z",
        "message": "Well, if that happens to me, I just have to go and maybe Google it a different way, like, ask the question a different way."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:53:46.252000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Of like rephrasing until you get what you need. Uh, can you remember a specific time? When you had to do that? Tell me about what you were searching for and how you ended up changing your question."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:54:01.382000Z",
        "message": "I think I was searching for information to do a school project back when I was in high school, and I was asking something about frogs. Like, how did frogs mate? And then it answered it 1 way, but then I had to reword it about the frogs another way."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:54:22.002000Z",
        "message": "That's a great example. Tell me the steps you tried starting from your first search How did you originally phrase the question? About frog mating? And then what did you change it to? What were you hoping to see? That didn't show up at first?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:54:37.302000Z",
        "message": "Well, I looked up how do frogs mate and it told me the process of how they mated, but it didn't tell me, like, where they like to go to mate. So then I had to type in where do frogs like to mate at, and then that gave me an answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:54:53.532000Z",
        "message": "So you started with how do frogs mate? Got the general process, wanted location details prompting the second search. When you finally found that that answer, how did you feel? And just curious, did you ever click into the sites below the summaries, or did the do the job?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:10.932000Z",
        "message": "I felt relieved, and I did not have to click into the sites below the summary. The snippet was all I needed to look at."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:20.592000Z",
        "message": "Relief is a strong signal. When it comes to getting answers fast, would you say that feeling relief, confidence, is usually what you're after, or, uh, are there other emotions that matter when use Google for answers?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:33.842000Z",
        "message": "No. Relief is definitely what I'm after."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:38.322000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate that. Thinking beyond Google for a second. Have you ever used other tools like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini? To get answers? If yes, in what situations do you reach for them instead? If not, what's held you back?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:52.241000Z",
        "message": "No. I don't really because I've never really thought about There's never been a scenario where I needed to use them because I've always just used Google, and that's it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:56:05.102000Z",
        "message": "That's clear. So Google's just been your default, and it does the job for you. Curious. If you imagine a tool like ChatGPT or Perplexity, what do you think might be different about using them compared to Google? Any expectations or or maybe hesitations?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:56:21.382000Z",
        "message": "Think that you would just talk to it in chat form, like, if you were sending text messages and no, I don't really have any expectations. Or limitations."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:56:32.002000Z",
        "message": "That sense of chatting with it, almost like texting, is is interesting. And in terms of trust, when you get that answer from Google, what makes it feel credible to you? Is it the source, the summary format, the reputation, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:56:45.932000Z",
        "message": "It's the source."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:56:49.082000Z",
        "message": "Got it. The actual website is being cited beneath the summary. Give you that sense of credibility. When you share an answer with someone else, does it matter to you that it came from Google? Or do you usually reference the specific website from the snippet? How do you handle that?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:57:06.132000Z",
        "message": "It really doesn't matter to me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:57:09.822000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Looking back over the past year or so, has anything changed about how you search for answers online? Any new habits, ways you phrase things, changes in how often you use Google, or has it stayed pretty much the same?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:57:23.782000Z",
        "message": "It stayed the same."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:57:28.182000Z",
        "message": "Understood. Have you ever had a friend or coworker suggest using a different answer engine for something? Like, ChatGPT or another site? If yes, what made you stick with Google in that moment instead? If not, no worries. Just curious."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:57:42.872000Z",
        "message": "Nope."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:57:46.842000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for walking me through your habits and, uh, thoughts today. Before we wrap up, how was this interview experience for you? Anything surprising, confusing, or just interesting? About talking with an AI. And you're welcome to end the call whenever you'd like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:58:03.712000Z",
        "message": "I thought it was interesting. I thought it's a lot better than having to click and type Being able to talk is a lot better."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1def6304b8f4d2abe0d8df84",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:58:12.412000Z",
        "message": "That's great to hear. Thanks for sharing your thoughts in this format. I enjoyed chatting with you and learned a lot from your perspective. Take care, and feel free to end the call. Whenever you're ready."
      }
    ],
