    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:48:57.529000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:49:05.239000Z",
        "message": "My day is going fine. Thank you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:49:08.409000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. Let's start with something simple. When you need to look up answers online, whether it's for work, everyday life, or just curiosity, what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:49:19.589000Z",
        "message": "I usually go to Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:49:24.499000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Google's your default spot. Can you walk me through what that process looks like for you from the moment you realize you need an answer to actually getting what you need?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:49:35.149000Z",
        "message": "I just type in my question on my cell phone and wait for the answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:49:41.109000Z",
        "message": "That sounds pretty straightforward. When you type in your question, and get the results, what do you usually look for on that page before deciding what to click or read?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:49:52.259000Z",
        "message": "I looked to see if my question was answered."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:49:58.509000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Is there a particular part of the results page you focus on first? For example, the featured snippet or those boxes at the top or do you scroll down and check links from certain websites?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:50:10.789000Z",
        "message": "No. I usually just stick to what Google has to say, and it usually supplies me with the answer that I'm looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:50:20.119000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like you trust whatever Google presents up top. Thinking about"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:50:23.459000Z",
        "message": "It hasn't let me be done yet."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:50:28.019000Z",
        "message": "absolutely. I'll keep it moving. Sticking with Google for now, can you tell me about the last time you looked something up and actually got frustrated or felt like Google's answer didn't quite help. What was that like?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:50:41.919000Z",
        "message": "I To be honest, I can't remember a time. I mean, I don't ask an awful lot of questions. But the questions I ask are pretty straightforward. The answers are just as straightforward. I don't think I've ever been disappointed."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:50:59.149000Z",
        "message": "Understood. Sounds like your questions are direct. And Google usually nails it for you. Um, out of curiosity, have you ever tried using other answer engines like ChatGPT Perplexity, Gemini, or even Google's AI generated summaries? Do you mostly stick with regular Google search?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:51:18.469000Z",
        "message": "I've I've stuck with Google for a long time. I have started using Gemini. Because it's 1 button on my cell phone. It's a Google phone. And so I've tried using Gemini and found that actually Gemini gives me much more complete answers than Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:51:43.479000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. Gemini's built in ease and those more complete answers caught your attention. Can you tell me about a specific time you use Gemini instead of regular Google? What did you need to find, and how did the experience go?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:51:58.549000Z",
        "message": "I've lately used it for finding out what the next day's stock futures are. And I'm very satisfied with the answers it gives me. It's in a very easy to read format. And, again, it's as satisfied my curiosity."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:52:21.829000Z",
        "message": "Great example. When you use Gemini for checking stock futures, what feels different about its answer compared to the typical Google search results? Anything stand out about how it presents the info or how you feel about the answer?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:52:35.119000Z",
        "message": "It's presented in a much nicer format, easy to read, and the answer seems to be much more complete. Complete,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:52:47.339000Z",
        "message": "That sense of completeness seems important for you. When you say complete, makes the answer feel that way? You know, is it the amount of detail, the way the information is organized, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:52:58.338000Z",
        "message": "Actually, all of that, the amount of information recapped in a in a reasonable length. And, again, with a nice presentation, makes it very easy and pleasant to read."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:53:15.049000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So the right amount of detail summed up neatly and easy on the eyes. When you use Gemini now, do you ever still double check its answer? By searching Google, or do you pretty much trust what Gemini gives you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:53:28.178000Z",
        "message": "No. I trust what Gemini's gives me, and and it hasn't been incorrect. I mean, it's been accurate."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:53:36.208000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like Gemini's earned your trust. Especially with those detailed and well presented answers. Thinking about Google"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:53:41.708000Z",
        "message": "Correct. Sorry. I don't mean to keep interrupting."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:53:44.279000Z",
        "message": "thinking no worries at all. Jump in anytime. It's your stories that matter. Since you've started using Gemini more, have your habits shifted much? For example, do you find yourself reaching for Gemini first now? Or does Google still come up first for some questions?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:54:05.039000Z",
        "message": "I'm reaching for Gemini much more often."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:54:10.548000Z",
        "message": "That's a pretty clear shift. You remember what triggered you to start using Gemini? More often instead of Google? Was it just the convenience"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:54:18.299000Z",
        "message": "Again, just to sorry again. Just again, I'd I'd like the presentation. I trust the answers."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:54:26.239000Z",
        "message": "No. Appreciate you sharing that. Presentation and trust are big factors for you. If you think about other answer engines like ChatGPT or Perplexity, have you had any experience with those, or do they not come up for you at all?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:54:42.789000Z",
        "message": "No. I have not not experienced them. At 1 point, a while ago, I tried chat, cheat cheat whatever it is, But I didn't like it, and it also wanted me to sign up for a pay subscription, which I wasn't willing to do."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:04.339000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to know. So ChatGPT didn't feel appealing mainly because of the subscription and maybe something about the experience. Can you remember what you didn't like about it even during that brief try? Was it about the way answers were given or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:20.259000Z",
        "message": "I don't remember. It was a while ago, But, again, I know I was totally put off when I had reached my limit. I didn't even know I had a limit. Then wanted to charge me. For any future answers."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:36.689000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. Having having a hidden limit and then hitting a paywall unexpectedly can be pretty off putting. If you think about Gemini, Google, and that brief chat GPT experience, how would you describe each of them in terms of personality? Like, if they were people at a party, how would you picture them acting?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:55:57.979000Z",
        "message": "Chat GPT as obnoxious self righteous person. Google as a well versed friendly kind of person. And Gemini as a kind of person I'd like to stick around with. Maybe form a friendship."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:56:21.458000Z",
        "message": "Really vivid descriptions. When you think about quoting or sharing answers with someone else, uh, like a friend or colleague, which of those engines answers would you feel most comfortable sharing? What makes that 1 feel more credible or or trustworthy to you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:56:35.679000Z",
        "message": "Again, I've gotten hooked on Gemini. So that's my default answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:56:43.249000Z",
        "message": "Perfect. So Gemini's answers are the ones you're most likely to share with others now. Looking back a year or so, what would you say has changed most about how you look up answers online? Anything stand out about your habits now versus them?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:56:58.139000Z",
        "message": "I'm much more likely to immediately think I could get my answer from than I did before. It took a while to get used to the fact that any information I need was readily at hand."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:57:18.519000Z",
        "message": "That's really interesting. Sounds like the realization of having instant answers from Gemini is a pretty recent shift for you. Do friends or coworkers ever mention which engines they use? Has anyone recommended the Gemini, Google, or something else to you lately?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:57:35.739000Z",
        "message": "No. I don't remember anyone recommending. I know Google is widely used by many. But, no, I nothing specific."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:57:50.119000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing all of that with me, seriously. Just 1 last thing. Talking with an AI about your online habits. How was that? Any thoughts you want to pass on before we wrap up?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 43,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:58:03.139000Z",
        "message": "I actually enjoyed it. It was much more efficient than talking to a human. So, no, I very pleasant experience."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0ebc8809c80b410f8104300a5",
        "index": 44,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:58:13.709000Z",
        "message": "Thank you for calling."
