  {
    "id": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
    "responseId": "91f32f931ad74504a7787690c",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:42:58.138000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:43:06.178000Z",
        "message": "Pretty good."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:43:09.508000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. To start, when you need answers online, what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:43:16.238000Z",
        "message": "Open up a tab. Google Chrome. Type in a prompt."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:43:24.408000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So you head straight for Chrome and use the search bar. Walk me through what happens next. After you type in your prompt, what do you look for, and what guides your next steps?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:43:35.338000Z",
        "message": "Usually don't go past the first page. I look at the first few openings on the SEO, and I typically ignore anything that's sponsored and I will go down to what I deem to be the authentically real website that I'm after."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:43:54.238000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So you tend to scan the first page skipping anything sponsored and focus on what feels authentic. What signals or clues help you decide a site is authentically real for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:44:07.018000Z",
        "message": "Usually, it's if the website, the URL is sort of a given, like, w w w dot delta airlines dot com. Or w w w dot MSN dot com."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:44:23.988000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. Familiar official URLs give you confidence. Thinking about your process is Google the tool you use most often for quick answers, or do you ever reach for other answer engines, ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini, or anything else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:44:39.968000Z",
        "message": "Well, I feel like Gemini is kinda thrust upon me when I use Google. So I'm not sure when that does and doesn't happen. I don't specifically seek out things like chat GPT, I do use Bing on a regular basis, so Copilot. It just really depends on what I'm typing in and what's being presented to me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:45:01.858000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful. Sounds like Google's your main starting point, but Bing Copilot pops up too, and Gemini sneaks in when you're on Google. Can you tell me about the last time you used Bing Copilot instead of Google? What were you searching for, and why did you end up there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:45:18.448000Z",
        "message": "I usually do that because I have a rewards program. And so you get points for searching. So sometimes I will instead of searching on Google, I'll just search on Bing."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:45:34.088000Z",
        "message": "Got it. The rewards program nudges you to Bing Copilot, for your searches. When you use Bing or Copilot, do you notice any differences in the results or experience compared to Google? What stands out, if anything?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:45:47.048000Z",
        "message": "Um, I don't think the Bing program is as robust. I don't think the SEO on it is as developed as the Google SEO. So while you might get some of the same websites initially, some same crossover, I think that the Bing search is comes up with less than optimal search engine optimization."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:46:15.718000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So Bing might show some of the same sites. But you you feel the results aren't quite as fine tuned. Is there anything about the experience on Bing Copilot itself like the way answers are presented or or how you interact with them? That's feels notably different from Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:46:35.358000Z",
        "message": "I think the biggest thing is it just doesn't feel as robust as Google. It's it's kinda hard to describe I feel like Google is I feel like I can trust Google to get me what I'm looking for, whereas Bing might but not necessarily."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:46:59.798000Z",
        "message": "That's a useful distinction. You feel you feel more trust and reliability with Google. While Bing feels a bit hit or miss, thinking about those those moments, what do you do if Bing doesn't quite deliver what you need? Can you tell me the full story of a time when that happened?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:47:15.808000Z",
        "message": "I can't think of a specific instance. But when I do go to Bing and say I do search on a term or or a prompt, and I'm not satisfied with the answers, then I'll just go to Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:47:29.778000Z",
        "message": "Makes a sense. So if Bing isn't cutting it, you switch over to Google to try your luck there. When you do this, is it usually for certain types of questions or tasks, or does it just depend on the day?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:47:41.188000Z",
        "message": "Oh, it doesn't I don't think it depends on the day. But it just probably depends on what I'm searching for. You know, some things I might get my answer right away on Bing, and so I don't have to go back to Google. And then other things, you know, just not satisfied, I do go to Google. It's it really, really varies, and it really depends."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:48:01.978000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for that. Let's shift to answer engines. Like, ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini. Have you tried any of those directly? Outside of what gets mixed into Google or Bing? If so, what led you to give them a shot? What was the situation?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:48:17.118000Z",
        "message": "I don't think I've used any of them separately because I was under the impression that chat chat GPT was you had to pay for it, and so I just never bothered bothered with anything like that. Um, I've never really ever come across perplexity, to be totally honest. Um, so yeah. So the when Gemini pops up, it is typically under the guise of me using Google."
