        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:50:18.278000Z",
        "message": "Well, I I think I already answered that. If if I feel like the the the synopsis from Gemini is either misleading, incorrect, or not comprehensive enough for what I'm looking for, that's when I'll go to our particular site or sites. To dive deeper into whatever it is I'm after."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:50:36.978000Z",
        "message": "That lines up with what you said. Earlier. If the rundown's not enough or feels off, you dive into sites yourself. When you're scanning for those those deeper answers, how do you decide which specific sites to trust or spend time on? What clues or habits guide you through that process?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:50:53.118000Z",
        "message": "Well, again, when I see the results of a prompt, I usually skip the sponsored 1 and go to sites that either appear more legitimate or are perhaps sites I'm already familiar with. So there is an inherent trust. And I just click on them in turn and, you know, if the first 1 answers my question fully, then I'm done. If not, I'll back out and try some of the other URLs and sites until I find what I'm looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:51:33.207000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for describing that. It sounds like your process is a mix of sticking with familiar legitimate seeming sites and some trial and error clicking through. Thinking about the different answer engines you've mentioned, Google, BingcoPilot, Gemini. If you line them up from most to least helpful for you, what would that order look like? And what's behind your ranking?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:51:54.798000Z",
        "message": "First and foremost, Google. I feel like that gives you your options, and then you have the power to choose from there what you wanna click on and what you trust. And then Gemini, I guess, simply because sort of a subset of Google, And then search engines from there."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:52:17.438000Z",
        "message": "So Google sits at the top for you. You feel it gives the broadest set of options and lets you decide where to put your trust. Gemini comes next. Mainly because it's part of the Google experience and then other engines follow. When you think about Google, Gemini, or Bing Copilot, what words or feelings come to mind with each? Do any of them have a distinct personality or vibe for you?"
