        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:52:43.138000Z",
        "message": "My name is I didn't think of it in terms of that. It's just more sort of a given. Like, when I want answers, it's a given. I'm gonna start with Google. And, you know, again, Gemini either pops up or it doesn't. And then Bing is sort of something that I go to simply because of the rewards program."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:53:07.848000Z",
        "message": "That's a good way to put it. Google's just the default almost automatic. Gemini is an occasional feature, and Bing is more transactional. Thanks to the rewards. Do any of your friends, coworkers, or family ever talk about using other Answer Engines for certain questions or tasks? Have you noticed others recommending tools, or does everyone you know just Google things by default?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:53:32.628000Z",
        "message": "I think the vast majority of people I know press Google first and foremost. You know, if other people have programs like, you know, a rewards program with Bing, then they would probably do something like that. And I know other people do use ChatGPT and Grok and some other other AI situations. But I think the vast majority of people I know personally and work with, Google is the 1 stop for shop."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79fc5855cf2c4c238e7dc6001",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:54:02.108000Z",
        "message": "That paints a clear picture. For you and the most people around you. Google is the default answer engine. Unless there's a nudge like rewards or a specific AI tool for something special. As a final step, how was this interview with me? Friendly AI? Any thoughts on the experience or things you didn't expect? And feel free to end the call whenever you'd like."
