  {
    "id": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
    "responseId": "0719d098751548c28a7d8fa39",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:38:35.753000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:38:43.553000Z",
        "message": "Fine. Thank you. How about you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:38:46.003000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for asking. Um, I'm doing well and looking forward to learning about your experiences today. Let's start with something simple. When you need answers online, what's what's the first thing you usually do? Walk me through your typical process for looking something up."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:39:00.103000Z",
        "message": "I just go to Google, and then I search for it. Pretty much it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:39:06.703000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Straight to Google. If you think back to the last time you needed an answer, can you tell me the full story? What were you looking for? And what steps did you take once you landed on Google? Are you still there? Are you still there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:39:36.363000Z",
        "message": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:39:38.593000Z",
        "message": "Great. Thanks for confirming. So thinking back to that last time you used Google, what exactly were you searching for? Once you typed in your question, what did you do next? Did you click a link? Read the featured snippet, scroll around, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:39:52.973000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. I just read what they answered in the top part of it. Basically, it's just a question about don't even remember the question it was about, but I just read the the snippet that I gave you, the reading. Then it answered my question that way."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:40:08.463000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like you pretty much got what you needed from the snippet up top. Without even clicking through. How did that feel? Was there anything about that experience that felt especially helpful or maybe a little frustrating?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:40:22.743000Z",
        "message": "No. I was just glad that the question was answered."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:40:27.312000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Quick and simple does the trick. You mentioned you usually use Google. Are there ever times when you reach for a different tool like Chat GPT perplexity or Gemini instead of Google? If so, what's going on in those situations?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:41:01.493000Z",
        "message": "I appreciate it, Chad. Did you please answer? It was good."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:41:05.663000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Um, just to clarify, have you used ChatGPT or similar AI answer tools before when looking something up, or do you mostly rely on Google? If you have used any others, can you think of a time when you chose 1 of them like ChatGPT or Gemini, and tell me about what led you there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:41:26.102000Z",
        "message": "Chat g p"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:41:31.483000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. So thinking about the last time you used ChatGPT to look something up, can you walk me through that experience? What did you need? And how did you use ChatGPT to get your answer? What stood out to you? Anything that felt different from using Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:42:10.473000Z",
        "message": "Hello? I'm going there right now. Over there in 2 minutes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:42:14.393000Z",
        "message": "No rush at all. Take No worries. Take your time. Just let me know when you're ready. And, uh, we'll pick right up"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:42:20.043000Z",
        "message": "Ready."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:42:23.463000Z",
        "message": "Perfect. Thanks for letting me know. So thinking about your last experience using ChatGPT, what kind of question did you ask it? And once you entered your question, what did you do next? How did the whole process feel? Compared to when you search on Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:43:11.523000Z",
        "message": "From the perspective of, you know, where I was coming from. Which is pretty cool."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:43:17.693000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So it sounds like ChatGPT gave you an answer. That felt tailored to your own perspective. Can you tell me a bit more about what made it feel pretty cool? Was it the way the answer was written? Or maybe how it responded to what you asked?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:43:34.083000Z",
        "message": "How I respond to what I asked and, like, how it gave me a perspective from the perspective I was coming from. Gave me a relevant perspective, which was cool."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:43:48.263000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So ChatGPT kind of gets where you're coming from and talks back in a way that feels relevant to you. Thinking about that, did you feel more confident in the answer maybe just more satisfied with how it was explained? Or was there something else about that experience that stood out for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:44:06.263000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. I felt more confident in the answer, and it was was it, like, appeased my emotions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:44:18.202000Z",
        "message": "That's really interesting. It sounds like ChatGPT not only gave you useful info, but also made you fell made you feel reassured. If you compare that emotional feeling with getting answers from Google, would you say it's noticeably different? Or is it mostly about the information for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:44:33.623000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. It's noticeably different. I've never ever asked Google a question like that before."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:44:39.112000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. So when is the question? Where your own perspective or feelings matter, it sounds like ChatGPT is your go to. For more straightforward questions though, you're sticking with Google. If you line up Google and ChatCPT side by side, what do you see as the strengths and weaknesses of each just from your own experience?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:45:01.403000Z",
        "message": "That Google has just, like, the website you can just go to and, like, ask the question. It's type it in. Gives you like the answer plus 1 links. That's cool. And then chat to t t p. It's, like, toxic like you're talking to a person, which nice too."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:45:17.743000Z",
        "message": "That's a helpful comparison. So with Google, you get, uh, quick links and answers, almost like flipping through a directory. And with Chat GPT, it feels more like having a conversation with someone who gets your situation If you had to pick which 1 is most helpful for you overall, which would you choose, and what makes that 1 stand out for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:45:38.713000Z",
        "message": "I mean, I probably picked that Jeep GPT because I'm sure it can answer the same kind of questions that Google can. You know? But that's that's why I stand up. It's like talking to somebody. Just like this competition right now."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:45:57.353000Z",
        "message": "That's a really clear way to put it. Sounds like the conversation style is a big deal for you. Not just the info, but feeling like there's someone on the other end who understands. Has this changed the way you usually look up answers lately? Are you finding"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:46:09.973000Z",
        "message": "No."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:46:13.503000Z",
        "message": "understood. So even though you like how ChatGPT feels more personal, you haven't changed your usual habits of using Google first. Do you think would need to happen for you to switch and use ChatGPT as your main answer tool? Most of the time instead of Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:46:28.103000Z",
        "message": "Well, I just why why would I bother it was something just getting personal or something?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:46:34.723000Z",
        "message": "So it sounds like for you, the reason to use ChatGPT would be if your question was personal or needed that conversational touch. But for regular stuff, Google still does the job."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:46:43.313000Z",
        "message": "Right."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:46:45.763000Z",
        "message": "Has anyone, you know, friends, coworkers, family, ever suggested using ChatGPT or other AI tools for looking things up? If so, what kind of advice have you heard?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:46:54.683000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. Nothing."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:46:59.573000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for letting me know. Sounds like it's pretty much your own choice so far. Just to wrap up, you from all the tools out there. What's 1 feature or thing you wish any of these answer engines could do would make your life easier or better?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:47:14.763000Z",
        "message": "They already pretty much have it covered."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:47:18.083000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate your honesty. Sounds like your needs are being met by what's out there now. Thanks for sharing your experiences with me today. And just a quick check-in, how was how about this interview for you? Chatting with an AI about your search habits. Can end the call whenever you'd like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2f63ef42493e499f947340586",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:47:33.743000Z",
        "message": "It's pretty good. You seem pretty real to me. I felt like I was talking to somebody. That's cool. Thanks."
      }
