  {
    "id": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
    "responseId": "8285e101b4d342ee857ae6d1c",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:39.707000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:48.246000Z",
        "message": "Good Very good."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:55.447000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. Let's start with something easy. When you need answers online, like, quick fax advice or solving a problem, what's the very first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:37:07.707000Z",
        "message": "Ask Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:37:10.447000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. Google's been the classic choice for a while now. Can you walk me through your usual process? When you look something up on Google? What steps do you take from start to finish?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:37:22.766000Z",
        "message": "I just say to my phone, hey, Google. And it will answer all of my questions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:37:31.107000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like it's pretty hands off and streamlined. Tell me more about the last time you did you did that. What was the question, and what happened after you asked your phone?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:37:41.487000Z",
        "message": "The last time I asked was about a football game. And I believe I asked what channel was the football game on. DIRECTV."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:37:57.157000Z",
        "message": "Got it. You wanted to know what channel the football game was on once Google gave you the answer. DirecTV, How did that feel for you? Was anything especially helpful or maybe a little frustrating about that experience?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:38:10.267000Z",
        "message": "No. It's very good. I love Hey Google. It's the best feature of my phone."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:38:21.587000Z",
        "message": "That's a strong endorsement. What is about, hey, Google, as a feature that stands out for you? Maybe compared to other ways you've looked things up or gotten answers?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:38:32.277000Z",
        "message": "It's always been there me, and it has never been wrong."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:38:39.637000Z",
        "message": "Reliability definitely counts for a lot. So you think about other answer engines, like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini, have you ever used any of those do you mostly stick with Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:38:52.127000Z",
        "message": "I tried to use a Gemini. But I can't figure it out."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:39:00.337000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Tell me a bit more what happened when you tried Gemini. What were you trying to do? And what made it feel tricky compared to your usual Google experience?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:39:10.947000Z",
        "message": "I try to use it as if it is Google and say, hey, Gemini. And it doesn't work. So I've actually clicked on the Gemini button and asked a few questions. And I won't do it anymore because, hey. Google works so good for me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:39:30.007000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful. So with Gemini, it sounds like you expected it to work by voice. The same way Google does, but it didn't. When you did use the Gemini button, and typed a few questions, how did the answers feel? And were they confusing? Helpful, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:39:45.947000Z",
        "message": "They were helpful. They they were helpful."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:39:50.967000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate that. Even though Gemini's answers were helpful, it sounds like something about the experience, maybe the way you interact with it, didn't quite fit what you you wanted. Is it mainly because you couldn't use voice commands? Or was there anything else about Gemini that didn't feel right for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:40:08.377000Z",
        "message": "Mainly the voice commands."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:40:12.206000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. That's clear. Besides voice commands, if you imagine your ideal answer engine, is there anything else you wish it could do that Google doesn't already cover for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:40:23.647000Z",
        "message": "No, actually."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:40:27.367000Z",
        "message": "Alright. Sounds like Google really ticks all the boxes for you. If you line up Google, Gemini, and any others you've tried, which 1 feels most trustworthy or credible when you share an answer with someone else? Why is that?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:40:43.587000Z",
        "message": "Google. Because it's always been there trustworthy."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:40:50.457000Z",
        "message": "That's a strong brand association. Google feels reliable. Because it's familiar and and has a track record with you. Thinking back over the past year, do you notice any changes in how often you use Google compared to before? Or has it mostly stayed the same for your answer needs?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:41:06.467000Z",
        "message": "It has mostly stayed the same."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:41:11.827000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Last thing, do friends or coworkers ever recommend other engines? Or tools for getting answers? Or do most people around you"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:41:19.577000Z",
        "message": "Right."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:41:21.287000Z",
        "message": "seem to use Google as well?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:41:23.967000Z",
        "message": "Most people around me use Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:41:28.457000Z",
        "message": "Got it. That's really clear. Google's the default. For you and most folks you know. Thanks for walking me through how you search. And for sharing your thoughts about these answer engines. Any feedback about, uh, this AI interview experience or anything you wish I'd asked about? If not, you're all set and can end the call whenever you'd like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f9325eab7fb84664b57a83976",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:41:51.667000Z",
        "message": "Thank you. You've been very helpful."
      }
