  {
    "id": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
    "responseId": "32941bade1da4ebb84b59a580",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:16.352000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:24.842000Z",
        "message": "Good. And you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:27.961000Z",
        "message": "Doing well. Thanks for asking. So let's jump in. When you need to look something up or get an answer online. What's the first thing you usually do? Can you walk me through your typical process?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:40.122000Z",
        "message": "I usually go to Safari, and I immediately search up what I'm looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:46.752000Z",
        "message": "Got it. When you say search up, do you mean you use Google? Or is there a different site or tool you tend to type your question into first? Tell me a bit more about what pops up and what you do next."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:59.832000Z",
        "message": "What pops up is usually what I'm currently looking for, videos, AI, uh, helping, chat GPT, and things like that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:13.792000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Thinking about the last time you searched for something, can you walk me through the full story? Start with what you needed, then each step you took and what happened as you found the answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:26.072000Z",
        "message": "Well, I was currently looking for surveys, and I stumbled upon a survey app called Free Cash. And it ended up actually giving me what I wanted."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:39.482000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So you started by searching for survey options, and free cash popped up as a result. Can you tell me more about that experience? What exactly did you type in? What made you trust that result? And what did you do after you found free cash?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:56.132000Z",
        "message": "Okay. So what made me find free cash is I was just looking for a little side hustle And what I do when I've seen it, it I clicked on it, and it sent me to a option to log in through Google or Apple."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:37:16.982000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful. When you saw the free cash results, did you look at any other answers or sites, or did you click into it right away? And once inside, did you do anything to double check or confirm if it was legit before signing up? Tell me about that part."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:37:33.072000Z",
        "message": "Okay. Yes. It was the only thing I, uh, I into free cash immediately. And what I did to see if it was legit is I actually participated in playing the games and you know, digging through the website."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:37:50.512000Z",
        "message": "So you tested it out by actually using the site. And interacting with the games yourself. Did you notice anything about the site or the way you found it that made you feel confident or maybe a little uncertain about trusting it at first? Did Answers from Google or AI fit in here, if at all?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:38:08.682000Z",
        "message": "Well, the AI actually gave me information that you could actually withdraw from the site. Any amount, but you will have to currently have a 20 dollar withdraw first. And yeah."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:38:29.132000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. You got withdrawal info from AI. Thinking back, was that info from, uh, ChatGPT, Perplex or another AI tool, or was it 1 of Google's summaries? How did you feel about the accuracy or helpfulness of that answer?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:38:43.802000Z",
        "message": "It was 1 of Google's summaries. It was 1 of their AI, uh, 1 of their new AI summaries. And I felt great about that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:38:54.272000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like those new Google AI summaries worked well for you. When you got that, got that info, did you feel like you could trust it right away? Or was there any part that made you want to check elsewhere? Was helpful about that summary compared to, say, a regular search result or even using ChatGPT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:39:13.002000Z",
        "message": "Well, you know, I fairly trust AI these days, and, you know, AI is pretty smart. So, uh, genuinely, you know, trust AI. So know, I trust I trusted it in the beginning."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:39:29.252000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate you sharing that. Sounds like you have a good level of trust in in AI. When you compare Google's AI summaries to answers from something like ChatGPT or even Perplexity, do you notice any differences in how the answer feels? What you like about it?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:39:45.832000Z",
        "message": "I mean, I'm not sure if it feels different. I think it feels the same, and I think it's pretty good. You know? It gives a good opportunity to learn new things."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:39:57.312000Z",
        "message": "That's good to know. So for you, whether it's Google's AI summary or something from ChatGPT, it feels pretty similar, both helpful and informative. If you lined up all these engines, Google AI summaries, ChatGPT, maybe Perplexity or Gemini, Would you say you have a favorite for getting quick answers lately? What puts 1 ahead of the others for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:40:19.282000Z",
        "message": "Well, I would say check GP just because it's the most popular you know, AI out there. And I'll just put it above everyone else because it's it's the most popular 1."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:40:33.062000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Popularity stands out for you with Chatty When you think about ChatGPT, what words or feelings come to mind? Same for Google AI summaries or Perplexity, if they have any clear associations for you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:40:51.882000Z",
        "message": "You get what you get, and you don't throw a fit."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:40:55.972000Z",
        "message": "That's a classic phrase. Sounds like there's a sense of acceptance with what these engines give you. Can you tell me a little more does that feeling of take what you get make you feel satisfied with the answers, or does it ever leave you wishing you could dig deeper or get something different?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:41:14.502000Z",
        "message": "You know, I usually take what I can get, but sometimes I would dig deeper"
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:41:21.882000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for being honest about that. When you do dig deeper, your next move? Do you switch engines? Tweak your search, or look for answers in a totally different way? Tell me how that usually goes for you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:41:36.422000Z",
        "message": "I usually tweak my search sometimes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:41:43.172000Z",
        "message": "So, mostly, you adjust your search. Rather than switch engines. When you look back over the past year, you feel like anything shifted in how you look things up, maybe using AI summaries more or reaching for different tools? Than you used to. If anything's changed, what led to that shift?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:42:01.362000Z",
        "message": "Well, if it doesn't have, you know, I'm looking for, if it's, you know, not in the category of what I'm looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:42:12.862000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. So if the answer doesn't match your needs or the right category, you adjust your approach. Have friends or coworkers ever recommended certain engines, for example, ChatGPT or Google AI, for specific types of questions or tasks? If so, what kind of advice have you heard?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:42:30.352000Z",
        "message": "No. None of my coworkers have ever given me any such a info."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:42:37.492000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to know. Last quick question. Looking ahead, if you could change or add anything about how these answer engines work, is there something you wish they could do for you? Or any pain points you'd love to see fixed?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:42:50.422000Z",
        "message": "I wish they can give us character voices that actually speak back to you and you can use them to give you information."
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:43:00.652000Z",
        "message": "Love that idea. Character voices and spoken info could make searches way more engaging. Before we wrap up, any final thoughts on your experience with AI tools or how you feel about these engines these days? Anything you wish more people knew?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:43:15.092000Z",
        "message": "I feel like, uh, AI is a big deal"
      },
      {
        "callId": "86bd6a5372cb4ece87ef8edfb",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:43:21.412000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate you sharing that. AI definitely seems to be making a big impact for you. Thanks for talking with me today, and sharing your experiences. If you'd like, you can end the call whenever you're ready."
      }
