  {
    "id": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
    "responseId": "509a36e4f8c944b9a9340d3c3",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:06.893000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:15.273000Z",
        "message": "My day is great. How about yours?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:18.763000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. I'm doing well too. Thanks for asking. Let's jump in. When you're looking for answers online, what's usually your first move?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:28.803000Z",
        "message": "My first move is usually to research the question that I'm looking for, like, for the answer. So I think I mainly go"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:39.613000Z",
        "message": "You mentioned you mainly go do you end up turning first when you start that kind of research. Can you walk me through what you typically do in that moment?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:51.823000Z",
        "message": "I usually go to Google. Try to find the best results to whatever question or whatever answer I'm looking for. I try to find the best answer at the time. And then if Google don't work, I use ChatGPT, or I will go to Gemini Google Gemini. And, hopefully, that would help me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:12.523000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like Google is your first stop most of the time. And then if that doesn't deliver, you try ChatGPT or Gemini. Thinking back to your last search, can you tell me the full story starting with what you needed? Then what steps you took?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:27.113000Z",
        "message": "My last search, I was looking for a certain La Boo Boo doll for a friend of mine. I couldn't find it on the website, so the first thing I did was go to Google, and I searched it on Google, which it was kinda hard to weigh out the options on which 1 was real, which 1 cost the most, which 1 is the most quality, the best quality, and the most durable to have. So I use ChatGPT to narrow down the websites that I was looking at ChatGPT let me know what websites was a scam and which ones wasn't."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:54.973000Z",
        "message": "That's an interesting journey. When you were using Google, what part felt most helpful and what part felt frustrating or tricky for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:03.982000Z",
        "message": "I believe when it comes to Google, everything is helpful. Every little thing I find, I can always piece everything together and and hopefully find what I'm looking for. And the most frustrating thing is when I'm not really sure on what I'm looking at."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:18.863000Z",
        "message": "You mentioned sometimes you're unsure about what you're looking at, that piecing things together, but it's tricky. Can you tell me more about a moment when you weren't sure about a result or a website? What did you do next?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:30.723000Z",
        "message": "A a moment when I wasn't sure about a result or website, I did what I normally always do, and I always phoned a friend or call someone that I trust a parent or a sister or brother, and, hopefully, they can help me out."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:43.953000Z",
        "message": "That's really interesting. You bring in someone you trust. When things get uncertain. Thinking about your switch to ChatGPT for that search, what did ChatGPT do that felt different from Google in helping you figure things out?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:58.733000Z",
        "message": "Tat GPT actually gave me more of a search Like, it broke down everything that I was looking at and it gave me step by steps on what I was looking at. Or if it didn't give me step by steps, it would give me a great summary of what I was looking at. So I won't have to think about what I'm reading or about what I'm searching. It basically did all the reading and searching for for me itself. And summarize everything in 1."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:29.703000Z",
        "message": "It sounds like ChatGPT gave you clear breakdowns. Summaries, which made"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:33.462000Z",
        "message": "Always do."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:35.822000Z",
        "message": "so you feel confident getting those summaries. And step by step guidance from ChatGPT? If you compare the feeling you get from using Google versus ChatGPT for the same task, What's the main difference for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:48.383000Z",
        "message": "The main difference for me would be the accuracy and how chat GPT is like talking to another person as in Google, just a search Chat GPT is like Google with a voice. Which is better for me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:04.873000Z",
        "message": "That's a strong way to put it. Google feels like a search. ChatGPT feels like a conversation. You mentioned accuracy too. Can you tell me more about how you judge whether an answer is accurate or not, whether it's from Google or ChatGPT?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:20.503000Z",
        "message": "Well, from Google, I'm not gonna say that I always trust what I'm reading, but I like to do a little bit more diving into what I'm reading. So for ChatGPT, I will will rely on Google. And for Google, I always rely back on to ChatGPT to see if the answer is accurate and makes sense and it's true or not."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:39.252000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. You sort of cross check 1 against the other. Can you think of a recent time you fact checked something between Google and ChatGPT? What was the question? And what did you discover in that process? Feel free to ask me any questions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:04.393000Z",
        "message": "That's all from me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9e3311663b784f5a8c1aaeb20",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:06.103000Z",
        "message": "Thank you for calling."
      }
