  {
    "id": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
    "responseId": "62a8df4fedbd403aab1976b6e",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:28.889000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:36.589000Z",
        "message": "It's going pretty well, please, for asking."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:40.079000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. When you need to look something up or get an answer online, what's the what's the very first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:47.629000Z",
        "message": "I usually either use Google Google search engine or I go to ChatGPT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:54.609000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Can you tell me more about what prompts you to choose Google versus ChatGPT in a typical situation? What kinds of"
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:03.339000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. I was gonna say, I think I used Google because it's the search engine that I probably used for the last decade. So the 1 I'm most familiar with and and think it gives most efficient and effective results. And, usually, I'm looking to go to another website. So for example, I wanna go to Texas a and m college website, so that's what I would type into the Google. If I have a very specific question looking for an answer, then I will use ChatGPT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:34.878000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for walking me through that. Focusing on the most recent time, you used ChatGPT for a specific question. You tell me the full story? Start with what you needed and what happened step by step."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:46.379000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. So I had a question regarding a tax issue in Minnesota and I had somebody a friend who was asking me, and I thought I knew the answer. So I went to chat GPT, input the information, It spitted out the first response. I knew that it was only partially correct. So then I kinda asked it to drill down a little bit. Just said, hey. Can you clarify x y z? And it came back and said, yes. We kind of failed to address that. So pretty straightforward."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:21.369000Z",
        "message": "Really clear walk through. Thanks. Thinking back on that story, what part of using ChatGPT felt the most helpful? And what part, if any, was a little annoying or frustrating?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:33.999000Z",
        "message": "I think it was helpful in the sense that I got a fairly comprehensive and detailed response. However, I knew right away that a failed to consider 1 element of the question that I had asked. So that was frustrating. As far as what I thought was best is then it actually gave me props at the end of, like, 2 or 3. It says, would you like citation? Would you like it's in a memo. And I did want the citations. It did give me the citations. I thought they were okay. Again, I think they were missing 1 or 2 key citations, and it also did citations of, like, just pinning another article to to it, which I didn't really feel like was a thwart authority that I could rely upon for a tax issue."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:18.699000Z",
        "message": "Interesting details. Thanks for sharing those specifics. When you get an answer like that, from ChatGPT, do you ever do any extra steps to double check what it gave you? If so, what do you usually do next?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:30.989000Z",
        "message": "Yes. I do do I'm trying to verify it. Usually, what I'll do is I'll look at the citations. I will also do my own research. I may use, like, a thing like Google Gemini, whatever, just to kinda bounce it off and see if the responses are similar as ChatGPT. I don't you know, I I well, I think I trust chat p GPT. I also verify for questions where I'm uncertain if they're actually giving me a true and concise response."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:07.069000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. Thinking of a time you compared answers? Like using ChatGPT and then checking with Google Gemini or another tool. Can you walk me through a specific example? How did the answers feel different to you? And what did you notice about their strengths or weaknesses?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:25.279000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. So I was I was looking a couple of weeks ago to ways to drive from San Diego to Minneapolis looking for the most efficient way, but I wanted to avoid going to the Colorado Rockies. I actually in that instance, I actually tried Google Gemini first, and it never gave me response. So then, actually, I went into chat GPT. And, again, they didn't neither 1 was able to really give me a clear, concise way to do it. I don't remember what I used, but I eventually did get a response. But it was frustrating that really neither of the AI search has yielded the results I hope they would."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:13.088000Z",
        "message": "That's a good story. Thinking about that frustration, it more about the tools missing the mark or about how they presented the info? What if anything stood out about how Gemini and ChatGPT responded or handled your question differently."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:27.659000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. I definitely think it was missing the mark because I thought my response is pretty pretty clear. I said I wanna drive from San Diego to Minneapolis. I wanna do it in 3 days. Please find me the most efficient of way to do that without going through the Colorado Rockies. Again, I was looking just for here's the root. Here's the here's the cities you can stop in. Would you like me to help you book a hotel for those nights? Right? And it just never did that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:58.749000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like you were hoping for a step by step route. And maybe some extra help along the way. If you can that experience to searching on regular Google, how do the answers and the way they're presented feel different? Is there anything about Google that stands out in, uh, those kinds of situations?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:16.259000Z",
        "message": "That's a good good question. Because I what I would say about that is what I do like about Google is like, in questions like that, Google will will in the responses, give you a Reddit. Or give you another kind of message board with what people have truly experienced where you don't get that with Jet GPT or Gemini, you're getting more you know, just data that they're scraping from the Internet. Where sometimes, like, hey. What's the best way to do x y z? It is nice to get somebody's opinion who's had this similar experience in the past."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:53.889000Z",
        "message": "That's a really interesting distinction. Getting lived experiences from real people versus scraped info. When it comes to trust and credibility, does Google feel different than ChatGPT or Gemini to you? Are there words or feelings you associate with each 1?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:10.679000Z",
        "message": "I would say Google is more personal and simple searches. I would say ChatGPT is more for the technical research You know, I can type in kind of a a narrative with the question. Where Google will be more just like, hey. What doctors are in the area? Blah blah blah. We're come up with a list."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:38.169000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate that breakdown. If each engine were a person at a party, who would Google be Who would ChatGPT be? You can describe how they act or what kind of person they seem like. In your mind."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:50.618000Z",
        "message": "Google would be the steady social extrovert who everybody liked, I think Chad GPT would be the stuffy know it all that is trying to impress people with its brilliance And while that person might be brilliant, they're not as brilliant as they think they are."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:37:19.219000Z",
        "message": "Love those images. Very vivid. So thinking back a year, has anything changed about how you look things up or which engines you default to? Any moments come to mind? When you switched your habit even for 1 search?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:37:33.429000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. So I think started probably using chat GPT maybe 12 to 18 months ago. I don't remember exactly. And I think over time, I use it more and more. Kind of wondering in a year from now, I'll say hey. I mean, not even using Google anymore. I just wanted to check GPT. Don't think that'll be the case. I will say since chat GPT and I started using it, I used to use Google and Yahoo search engines. I never use Yahoo. I haven't used Yahoo search engine for 6 months like that. Because, again, I'll go to Google or I'll go chat GPT. I generally get what I need. And then I'll move on to my next next project."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:38:12.228000Z",
        "message": "That's a strong shift, dropping Yahoo entirely using ChatGPT more. Has anyone in your circle, friends, coworkers ever recommended 1 of these AI engines for certain tasks? What sort of things do do people talk about or suggest?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:38:26.839000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. So I was having lunch with some former co and they told me that since I had left 2 years ago, they basically have used chat GPT for all of their kind of searches or internal record keeping so now when you, like, type something in and want it to be searched, it'll go out across the entire department and scrape all the information that's in a publicly shared folder. If it's a privately private folder does a But they were just talking about their use of it and how it really has advanced their job and what they're doing. It just made it a lot easier to kinda take those mundane tasks. The kind of basic blocking and tackling, and take that off their plate, and now that's what Jet GPT does."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:39:20.809000Z",
        "message": "That's really helpful context. So before we wrap, is there anything you wish these engines could do that they can't Any features or capabilities you think would make a big difference for you personally?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:39:33.699000Z",
        "message": "I think charging beats GPT could just be more reliable. You know, again, I've used it for various searches and just found it to be sometimes wrong. And then you'll even type in and say, hey. Why didn't you pick up this? And they acknowledge that they missed it. So, again, I think if ChatGPT become kinda become an expert, if I ever get to the confidence level that I have a, like, a Google search, where I know what I'm seeing is accurate and correct. That'll be great."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:40:06.598000Z",
        "message": "That's clear. Sounds like reliability and getting truly expert accurate info is key for you. Thanks a ton for sharing all these stories and insights today. Before we end, how did you find this this interview with an AI? Any feedback, or is there anything else you wanted to add? And you can end the call whenever you'd like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4bd270db73414ed98b76848b5",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:40:24.658000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. I actually really enjoyed it. I think I it is a lot easier to speak and try to articulate your thoughts and answer, like, a survey where you just have radio buttons to click or typing in a response for you know, sometimes you wanna just rush through it just to be done with it. I think it just allowed me to to share my thoughts, articulate my ideas, and give honest and hopefully constructive feedback. So I appreciate your time, and you have a wonderful day."
      }
