  {
    "id": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
    "responseId": "f85cdf78a9474e5e8881403d2",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:50.292000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:58.012000Z",
        "message": "It's going great."
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:01.252000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. When you need to find answers online, say you're curious about something, or need quick info, what's the very first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:10.032000Z",
        "message": "Search Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:13.291000Z",
        "message": "Walk me through what that process looks like for you step by step. Let's say, you had a question pop into your head. Happens next?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:21.232000Z",
        "message": "I would open up my browser on my phone. Search Google in whatever terms I'm looking for, whether it be directions or restaurant menu?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:33.662000Z",
        "message": "Once you type in your question or or keywords in Google, what do you usually do next? So you click on the first link, read the snippets, scroll, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:43.442000Z",
        "message": "I usually scroll down to the bottom of the screen And if I don't get a good enough result, I'll scroll up and go from top answer to the bottom."
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:57.052000Z",
        "message": "When you do that, scrolling and checking different results, what are you looking for that tells you, yep, this is the right answer? What signals or details help you feel confident about the answer you choose?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:09.952000Z",
        "message": "The legitimate legitimate the legit websites, uh, is what I look for, or I look for either a Reddit subform with multiple responses."
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:21.332000Z",
        "message": "Tell me more about how you decide a site is legit."
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:26.472000Z",
        "message": "I look at a site as legit when it uses accurate resources to come up with their answers."
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:36.592000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. Can you think of the last time you searched for something and found yourself double checking if a site's resources were accurate? What was the question, and what did you do to verify?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:48.942000Z",
        "message": "I look was looking for stats on a baseball player I made sure that the website was legit. Because it was backed and sponsored by MLB baseball."
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:05.932000Z",
        "message": "And when you got it. So you were searching for baseball player stats and seeing the MLB sponsorship made you trust the information? When you saw that, did you feel totally confident in the stats? Or did you do anything else to check them?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:23.272000Z",
        "message": "Yes. I felt totally confident in those stats."
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:28.721000Z",
        "message": "Got it. For searches like that, stats, factual info, would you ever use tools besides Google? Like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini, or do you always stick with Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:39.762000Z",
        "message": "I normally usually stick with Google because it has the most resources."
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:45.722000Z",
        "message": "Thinking about Google, what do you find most helpful about using it for your questions and searches?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:53.292000Z",
        "message": "The simplicity of being able to search anything and it also recommend new terms."
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:02.292000Z",
        "message": "Is there anything that ever feel was there ever a time when Google didn't give you what you needed? Or you found it frustrating? Can you tell me about that?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:10.852000Z",
        "message": "Yep. Yes. There has been times where Google wasn't able to accommodate with my search in which I would go to other forums like Reddit. Or Facebook or YouTube."
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:26.752000Z",
        "message": "Can you think of a specific search? That happened, where Google came up short and you turned to Reddit, Facebook, or YouTube instead. What were you looking for and what made you switch?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:41.182000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. So when it's normally a newer product, like, looking for something on a new vehicle, I couldn't find anything on Google. I looked it up on YouTube and found a video about it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:55.032000Z",
        "message": "When you found that video on YouTube, about it may"
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:57.092000Z",
        "message": "I'll take care."
      },
      {
        "callId": "515eeb6afb7146f29fba78afb",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:59.002000Z",
        "message": "thank you for calling."
      }
