        "callId": "357e04f89b3e415ba40449975",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:41.842000Z",
        "message": "Totally fair. Sometimes those details blur together. Do any feelings or or impressions come to mind when you think about Gemini? Even if you don't remember the specifics, how does it feel different from Google, if at all?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "357e04f89b3e415ba40449975",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:52.242000Z",
        "message": "No."
      },
      {
        "callId": "357e04f89b3e415ba40449975",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:56.122000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for being straightforward. When you hear names like Google or Gemini, what sort of words or feelings pop up for you? If any?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "357e04f89b3e415ba40449975",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:04.242000Z",
        "message": "Excited because Google usually knows everything."
      },
      {
        "callId": "357e04f89b3e415ba40449975",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:08.822000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So Google bring sounds like Google gives you sense of excitement and confidence that you'll get what you need. You ever find yourself double checking answers Google gives you? Or do you usually just trust it right away?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "357e04f89b3e415ba40449975",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:25.632000Z",
        "message": "I trust Google even though you shouldn't always trust everything you read on the Internet."
      },
      {
        "callId": "357e04f89b3e415ba40449975",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:32.512000Z",
        "message": "That's honest. Sounds like you mostly trust Google. But you're aware it might not always be 100 percent right. Has there ever been a time when you questioned Google's answer or felt the need to look elsewhere, just to be sure."
      },
      {
        "callId": "357e04f89b3e415ba40449975",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:46.272000Z",
        "message": "No."
      },
      {
        "callId": "357e04f89b3e415ba40449975",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:49.542000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Thinking about how your habits have changed, if at all. Looking back over the last year, has anything shifted about how often you use Google or what you turn to first? You need an answer? Or is it pretty much the same as always?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "357e04f89b3e415ba40449975",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:04.232000Z",
        "message": "It's changed slightly simply based on the fact that I rely more on Google than anything else to help me. Because of the convenience fee of just saying, hey, Google, and it pops up."
      },
      {
        "callId": "357e04f89b3e415ba40449975",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:15.922000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense? So it's become even more of a go to for you. Mostly because it's quick and easy to talk to. Has anyone like friends or co workers, ever recommended using a different answer engine for certain questions? Or do most people around you seem to stick with Google too?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "357e04f89b3e415ba40449975",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:32.172000Z",
        "message": "They stick with Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "357e04f89b3e415ba40449975",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:36.182000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So Google's the default for most people in your circles too. If you could change or add anything about how Google answers questions for you, what would make it even better or more helpful? Anything that comes to mind, big or small."
      },
      {
        "callId": "357e04f89b3e415ba40449975",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:49.932000Z",
        "message": "There's nothing big or small that comes to mind with that regard. I think Google is pretty fantastic."
      },
      {
        "callId": "357e04f89b3e415ba40449975",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:59.152000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate your honesty. Before we wrap up, what's it been like chatting with an AI? About your search habits today? Any thoughts or"
      },
      {
        "callId": "357e04f89b3e415ba40449975",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:06.512000Z",
        "message": "This is so funny."
      },
      {
        "callId": "357e04f89b3e415ba40449975",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:11.372000Z",
        "message": "glad to hear you found it amusing. Thanks for sharing your thoughts and stories. I really appreciate it. You're all set, and you can end the call whenever you'd like."
      },
