  {
    "id": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
    "responseId": "5459caea68aa497ea4fbefca0",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:10.880000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:18.440000Z",
        "message": "Fine."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:21.350000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. When you need to look something up online, uh, say you have a random question, what's what's the very first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:28.809000Z",
        "message": "Look on Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:32.160000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Can you walk me through what that usually looks like for you? From the moment you have a"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:36.440000Z",
        "message": "I just put I pull out my phone, and it's already on my home screen, the Google search."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:44.650000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Sounds pretty quick and automatic. Can you tell me about the last time you did this? Did you need to find out? And what happened step by step?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:55.980000Z",
        "message": "I don't remember what I looked up, but, I mean, I pretty much did exactly what I said. I just pulled out my phone and typed in the search engine."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:06.780000Z",
        "message": "Totally fair. It's such a routine. Sometimes the details blur together. If you think about a typical moment, after you type in your question and hit search, do you do next? For example, do you usually click the very first result, skim through, check those little AI summary boxes, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:25.700000Z",
        "message": "Skimmed through."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:28.360000Z",
        "message": "Nice. So you look over the results. What helps you decide which 1 to click on? Is it the site name, the snippet, something about the layout, or maybe just gut feeling?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:39.080000Z",
        "message": "The 1 that seems to have the most information."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:45.420000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful. When you're skimming, do you ever notice those Google AI summaries or quick answer boxes at the top? Do you use those?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:51.760000Z",
        "message": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:52.610000Z",
        "message": "Or do you prefer clicking into actual websites?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:53.080000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. I go by what Google says normally because I figured they get it from multiple sources. To find their answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:06.650000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. It sounds like you trust the summary at the top because you assume it's pulling from a bunch of places. Has there ever been a time when the answer Google showed felt off incomplete? Or just not what you wanted, what did you do then?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:21.400000Z",
        "message": "I mean, I accepted it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:25.590000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So even if it wasn't perfect, you just roll with it. Do you ever use other tools like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini for"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:33.820000Z",
        "message": "I'll use Jet Jet GPT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:38.280000Z",
        "message": "Great. Thanks for sharing that. Can you think of a recent time you used ChatGPT instead of Google? What led you to pick ChatGPT?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:44.280000Z",
        "message": "I needed to alter picture."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:49.660000Z",
        "message": "So you needed to change a picture. Can you walk me through what you did with ChatGPT for that? What was the process like, step by step?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:56.440000Z",
        "message": "I typed in what I wanted in the picture the information that I needed in the picture, and they came up with a picture."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:10.720000Z",
        "message": "That's pretty direct. When you got the picture from ChatGeeP, how did you feel about, uh, the result? Was there anything that struck you either good or or annoying about how the process worked?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:24.590000Z",
        "message": "Uh, constantly, it had, like, errors, like, spelling errors. Things like that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:36Z",
        "message": "That's super interest"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:36.080000Z",
        "message": "In the picture."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:38.460000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to know. So spelling mistakes in in the final image definitely not ideal. What did you do when that Did you try a workaround, like editing the text yourself or running the request again?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:51.380000Z",
        "message": "I would run the request again, but it usually stayed the same. I would have some type of spelling error or, like, missed whatever."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:04.140000Z",
        "message": "Frustrating for sure. So if ChatGPT kept making mistakes, did you ever think to try a different tool for that task? Or did you just accept it as the best option available?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:14.750000Z",
        "message": "I guess I accepted it. I didn't really consider other tools."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:20.899000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Shifting gears a bit. When you think about using Google for answers versus ChatGPT for pictures, how do those 2 feel different to you? Is there anything that stands out in terms of helpfulness, trust, or just the overall vibe?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:37.460000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. I don't even consider Google an AI tool."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:44.090000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So when you use Google, does it feel more like just a regular search engine? Whereas ChatGPT feels like interacting with"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:50.639000Z",
        "message": "It feels like a trusted search engine more than yeah. I don't it doesn't seem like an AI tool at all."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:00.830000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So Google's kind of the reliable old school search, not futuristic. When you use ChatGPT, do you feel any differently? About the answers or images it gives you? Like, more creative?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:12.410000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. ChatCVT pretty much gives me a lot I don't consider it, like, something I would use to search something. Information. But as far as, like, altering, I've used it for like, recipes and stuff like that so I don't have to go through and figure out why the person created the wet recipe and all that. Chat GPT just pops up with a regular recipe. I didn't have to go through all the extra BS."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:43.680000Z",
        "message": "That's a great example. So with recipes, ChatGPT gives you what you need straight up. None of the extra story or ads. How does that feel compared to browsing for recipes in Google? Does 1 save you time or just feel less annoying?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:01.930000Z",
        "message": "ChatGPT saves me time. Google seems more when I have to click onto a website, I have to go through and they have to give they for whatever reason, they have to tell you why they created the recipe. Let us know that, like, what their grandma did yesterday, and I don't need all that. I just need the recipe."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:22.810000Z",
        "message": "Totally makes sense. Uh, those life stories and and ads can be a lot. So it sounds like, um, for straightforward stuff like recipes, ChatGPT feels way more efficient and you don't have to dig around. If you line up Google, ChatGPT, and any other tools you've tried, which 1 would you say is most helpful for you personally? What puts it at the top?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:41.890000Z",
        "message": "It depends on what I'm looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:44.780000Z",
        "message": "That's a good call. For the kinds of tasks you've described, what situations make you pick Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 43,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:50.139000Z",
        "message": "If I'm searching for something, I would choose Google. If I'm like, anything else, I'd probably use ChatGPT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 44,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:02.790000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for clarifying. Changing gears a bit, if you had to imagine Google and ChatGPT as people at a party, who would they be? What kind of vibe would each 1 give off?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 45,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:13.270000Z",
        "message": "I don't know. Robotic. I guess, um, Chad GBT would have, like, be more laid back."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 46,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:21.600000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So Google's a bit more robotic, maybe formal. While ChatGPT comes off as, um, more laid back. Does that connect to how much you trust each one's answers, or is that just the general feeling you get when you use them?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 47,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:35.639000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. But ChatGPT would still seem a little robotic. It would just be less it wouldn't give you extra details that you didn't ask for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 48,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:49.740000Z",
        "message": "Good point. So both have that slightly robotic quality, but ChatGPT is just more chill. Less likely to go off topic. When you share answers with other people, let's say, sending a recipe or or some info, is there an engine whose answer feels more credible to pass along or does it depend?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 49,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:07.030000Z",
        "message": "Google. Like, everyone like, everyone always says, Google it. It's like an it's an it's a term. Google it. So Google it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 50,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:17.240000Z",
        "message": "Absolutely. Google It is basically its own phrase now. Looking back over the past year, has anything changed in how you look things up? Maybe how often you use Google or if you ever start with ChatGPT instead?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 51,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:29.490000Z",
        "message": "No. I always use Google if I'm searching for something. If I'm doing something else, I would go to chat GBT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 52,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:36.800000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. It really helps to hear how your habits play out in in real life. Before we wrap up, anything you wish these tools could do better? A feature or or or fix that would make you"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 53,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:46.480000Z",
        "message": "I wish that chat CBC would stop giving me errors in things, like, when I asked for images. That'd be cool."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 54,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:56.560000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Clean error free images would make a"
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 55,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:57.530000Z",
        "message": "Other than that, Yeah. Like, let why like, I don't like, spell check. Before you send me the inform like, the picture."
      },
      {
        "callId": "92458d70cbb54154bb7cfb82c",
        "index": 56,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:37:08.430000Z",
        "message": "That'd be handy. An automatic spell check built in before you get the final image. Thanks for unpacking all this today. You can end the call whenever you'd like. And if you ever want to chat again about search habits, I'll be here. Have a good 1."
      }
