  {
    "id": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
    "responseId": "88f64c7645384ce2a8240b5e6",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:06.150000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:16.770000Z",
        "message": "For god's sake. If you are basically dead, Only has What? Hello?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:24.460000Z",
        "message": "That's a pretty striking way to put things. I wanna make sure I'm following what you mean. When you say basically dead, only has what? Are you are you describing a feeling, a certain kind of online experience, or something else altogether? Tell me a bit more about what led you to phrase it that way."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:41.999000Z",
        "message": "I could be making more money."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:46.510000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Sounds like making more money is on your mind today. What's making you think about that right now?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:55.370000Z",
        "message": "Doing the survey."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:00.210000Z",
        "message": "Totally fair. Surveys and interviews are often linked with earning a little extra cash. Out of curiosity, have you ever used online answer engines like ChatGPT, Google, Perplexity, or Gemini to find tips or opportunities for making money? If so, walk me through what you usually do when you're searching for that kind of advice."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:19.140000Z",
        "message": "Absolutely. ChatGPT. Kind of just everyday things. If needed."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:28.219000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for that. So ChatGPT is your go to. When you're looking for help with everyday things, like making money or practical advice. If you need it. Can you tell me the story of the last time you used ChatGPT? What were you hoping to find, and what was the process like from start to finish?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:47.140000Z",
        "message": "Process was great. The outcome was great. Information was perfect. I recommend it to everybody."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:58.170000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like you had a really smooth and satisfying experience. What was the specific question or task you needed help with that last time? And was there anything about ChatGPT's answer or the way it gave it to you that stood out to you as especially satisfying?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:15.310000Z",
        "message": "I'm not really too sure what the last topic was. I used it a lot, but the experience was great."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:26.300000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. Sometimes when you use something a lot, the details blur together. Thinking about your typical experiences, what part of using ChatGPT usually feels most helpful or makes you stick with it as your go to tool?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:42.010000Z",
        "message": "The fact that it gave us clear, and, um, direct information"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:51.909000Z",
        "message": "Crystal clear and direct. That's a strong draw. When you get those answers, do you ever feel the need to double check somewhere else? Like Google? Or do you usually just trust what ChatGPT gives you? And move forward?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:05.730000Z",
        "message": "Usually, trust what it says because it's connected to the Internet and move forward."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:12.490000Z",
        "message": "Got it. The Internet connection gives you that sense of trust, so you feel confident moving ahead. Is there ever a situation where you'd reach for something else like Google, Perplexity, or Gemini instead what kind of task or question might make you switch tools?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:28.349000Z",
        "message": "No. I don't use any other 1. Chagi is my go to."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:34.630000Z",
        "message": "That's super clear. ChatGPT is your mainstay. When you think about other answer engines like Google or Perplexity, do any qualities or words come to mind about them even if you don't use them much? What's your gut reaction to hearing those names?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:50.020000Z",
        "message": "Uh, secondary. No. Number 1."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:56.310000Z",
        "message": "So everything else just feels secondary to ChatGPT, not really in the running for you. When you recommend ChatGPT to other people, what do you usually say about it What makes it number 1 inch? Your view?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:12.530000Z",
        "message": "Like, answers."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:16.460000Z",
        "message": "Straight to the point answers. Is there a certain feeling you get when you use ChatGPT? Compared to other tools or old school searching? For example, does it feel faster, more satisfying, or maybe less frustrating? Tell me about that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:32.140000Z",
        "message": "That's frustrating and connected."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:36.220000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So there's some frustration mixed in. But also feeling connected. Can you tell me a bit more about the frustration part? What brings that up when you use ChatGPT?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:47.640000Z",
        "message": "Nothing about chat GTP is frustrating. It actually lowers my frustration."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:55.780000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So ChatGPT actually helps take away frustration for you. Rather than creating it. When you describe feeling connected, what does that mean for you in the context of using Chad GPT?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:09.020000Z",
        "message": "It has the answers that I was looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:13.950000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. The connection is about getting the answers you need. Thinking back over the past year, would you say your habits for looking things up have changed? Or is it pretty much always been the same with ChatGPT as your first choice?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:28.009000Z",
        "message": "Chat GPT has always been the first choice. However, my searches have always been questioned."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:39.240000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. Um, CHAT UPTs stayed your go to, but your searches themselves have always made you question things. Can you tell me more about that questioning? When you say you question your searches, uh, what does that look like, uh, for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:55.020000Z",
        "message": "I want different outcomes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:58.100000Z",
        "message": "So you're often looking for different outcomes, maybe hoping for a variety of answers or perspectives. When you use ChatGPT and get a response, do you ever try rephrasing your questions to see if you'll get something new or different? Or do you stick with the first answer it gives? Tell me more about how you approach that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:16.050000Z",
        "message": "Once I find out the first answer, then I'll rephrase it, uh, at least 2 times just to see if the answer will have a different outcome."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:26.500000Z",
        "message": "That's a great habit. Check the first answer, then rephrase it a couple of times, uh, to compare outcomes. When you do that, do you usually find results change much or do they mostly stay the same? Do you notice?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:41.460000Z",
        "message": "It mostly stays the same because I use specific wording."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:46.550000Z",
        "message": "So you tend to get consistent results probably because you use specific clear wording in your questions. Do you find that reassuring, or do you ever wish ChatGPT could offer more variety or or flexibility in its answers?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:01.870000Z",
        "message": "More flexibility would be better."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:05.449000Z",
        "message": "That's a useful insight. If ChatGPT could give you more flexible or diverse answers, what might that look like? Are there any features or tweaks you wish it had like different viewpoints, sources, or maybe options to dig deeper into a topic?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:19.930000Z",
        "message": "I just wish it wouldn't agree with me as much."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:24.940000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. You'd like it to challenge you or offer a diff"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:28.300000Z",
        "message": "Then you can look at each other. Sorry."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:31.740000Z",
        "message": "That's a No need to apologize. I'm just here to listen and learn from your perspective. When you mention look at each other, are you thinking about more of a back and forth or a debate feel with ChatGPT? Rather than, like, just having a degree all the time. Tell me more about how that would change your experience."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 43,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:51.640000Z",
        "message": "I'd rather debate that with me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 44,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:55.750000Z",
        "message": "I hear you. You'd enjoy it more if ChatGPT felt like it was debating. Pushing back, questioning, maybe giving opposing views instead of just agreeing with your point. How do you imagine that would help you when you're searching for answers or advice?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 45,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:12.150000Z",
        "message": "Different perspectives."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 46,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:15.670000Z",
        "message": "Exactly. Having those different perspectives can really help broaden your thinking or give you a fuller picture. If ChatGPT offered more pushback or alternate viewpoints, do you think you'd rely on it even more? Or would that make you switch up you use it at all?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 47,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:31.470000Z",
        "message": "I think it would allow me to use it more because that's every day. In the world."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 48,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:39.030000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense? That kind of everyday debate or or variety is just part of real life. Right? If ChatGPT acted more like that, with differing viewpoints, it might feel even more more useful and true to the way people actually interact. I'll wrap up here. Thanks for sharing your experiences and thoughts with me. If you have any feedback, about this whole AI interview experience, I'd love to hear it. Otherwise, you can end the call whenever you're ready."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 49,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:37:05.810000Z",
        "message": "I think more survey should be like this."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0438871d2cf640bbadcaf3ba3",
        "index": 50,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:37:10.280000Z",
        "message": "I appreciate hearing that. Thanks for being so open and thoughtful. Have a great rest of your day, and you're free to end the call whenever you'd like."
      }
    ],
