  {
    "id": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
    "responseId": "8bb3ff8e6c374d26a451b177b",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:30.088000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:38.048000Z",
        "message": "Great."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:41.777000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. To start us off, when you need answers online, what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:50.248000Z",
        "message": "The first thing I usually do is go to Google search."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:56.618000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Google's your starting point. Can you walk me through your typical process for looking something up on Google? Do you do step by step?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:07.268000Z",
        "message": "I go to the Google search. And type in a question or words related to my search. And then I look at"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:17.498000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for breaking"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:19.598000Z",
        "message": "multiple answers."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:24.198000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. When you look at multiple answers, what do you tend to focus on first Like, are you scanning the first few links, checking snippets, something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:33.598000Z",
        "message": "Yes. I usually check the first few links and also look to see if there are dates. Because I look for the most current answers."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:44.478000Z",
        "message": "Helpful detail. So having, uh, recent up to date results, uh, is important for you. In your last search, do you remember what you were looking up Can you walk me through that full story, what you needed, what you typed, and how you decided which answer to trust?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:27:03.128000Z",
        "message": "I don't remember what the last thing I was looking up. I think it was I don't remember what it was."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:27:11.778000Z",
        "message": "No no worries. That happens. Thinking about your usual searches, what kinds of questions or topics do you most often turn to Google for? Is it news? Troubleshooting, no, troubleshooting, shopping, something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:27:32.078000Z",
        "message": "I use Google a lot to to expand on news coverage that I've seen. I look it up to find medical advice. I use it for shopping. I use it for travel."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:27:50.838000Z",
        "message": "That's a good mix. When you look up medical advice news or travel info, do you ever use any other tools besides Google? Like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or maybe the AI summaries you see popping up? Or is it mostly Google for those?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:06.478000Z",
        "message": "Mostly, I use Google for that. I do use ChatGPT for some things, but I haven't used it for medical."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:17.658000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So you turn to Chatuchipiti sometimes. But not for medical topics. When you do use ChatGPT, what kinds of questions or tasks are you using it for typically?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:26.488000Z",
        "message": "Generally, when I'm using ChatGPT, I'm using it at work to generate ideas for projects. Or to help me to create presentations or to give me a list of resource resources to use when creating presentations."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:46.068000Z",
        "message": "That's really clear. When it comes to those work tasks, like, brainstorming or making presentations, What made you choose ChatGPT over Google? Was there something you needed or a frustration with Google that made ChatGPT feel more useful?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:02.558000Z",
        "message": "Uh, we have been given professional development at work. Related to chat GPT and how we can use it. And I have found it to be very helpful."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:15.798000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. It sounds like professional development nudged you toward using ChatGPT. And it stuck because you find it helpful. Thinking back to the last time you used ChatGPT for work, what part of the experience felt especially useful? Or maybe even annoying?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:32.978000Z",
        "message": "It's very useful because it gave me a list of resources that I could use for a presentation. And in fact, it actually gave me an entire presentation So I was able to use that and make some modifications to it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:50.718000Z",
        "message": "That's a big help. Getting both the resources and almost a ready made presentation. When you were using ChatGPT for that, did you find yourself double checking the information elsewhere, or did you just use what it gave you pretty much as is?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:05.558000Z",
        "message": "Yes. I definitely double checked the information. The resources I got, of course, were links to different websites. So I didn't really have to check those."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:21.258000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Having Direct Links helps with trust. When you compare your experience getting answers or resources in ChatGPT versus just searching in Google, how does it feel different for you? Is there anything that stands out about speed, depth, or even how you interact with each 1?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:39.298000Z",
        "message": "I think I get more thorough answers when I use ChatBee GPT because it I can ask additional questions for more clarification. On Google search. I would have to keep typing in questions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:56.368000Z",
        "message": "I hear you. Uh, so continuing a conversation for follow-up, is easier in ChatGPT. Google feels a bit more manual, like you have to keep starting over each time, If you line them up, Google search and ChatGPT, which do you find most helpful for your main needs these days? And why?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:14.138000Z",
        "message": "If I just need a quick answer, I just use Google search. If I want a more extensive answer, or more work related material, I generally use chat GPT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:28.718000Z",
        "message": "That's a clear split. Quick hits, Google, deeper work, ChatGPT. Thinking beyond just usefulness. If you imagine Google and ChatGPT as people at a party, would they be? How would you describe how each of them acts or their vibe"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:47.198000Z",
        "message": "I think chat GPT would be more of a person that is into conversation because Google tends to just give you a direct answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:00.588000Z",
        "message": "Love that metaphor. ChatGPT is the chatty conversational 1, while Google's more direct straight to the point. When you share info or answers, from either with coworkers or friends, does 1 feel more credible or or trustworthy to you or them, or does it depend on the situation?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:19.497000Z",
        "message": "I feel the information I get from a Google search is more trustworthy. Because I feel that I have to do some additional research for clarification to make sure that what I'm getting on chat GPT is accurate."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:38.428000Z",
        "message": "Really helpful. So Google feels more trustworthy at first glance. While ChatGPT requires some fact checking, before you're fully confident."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:46.888000Z",
        "message": "Correct."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:46.978000Z",
        "message": "Looking back over the Thanks for clarifying. Looking back, say, over the past year, have your habits changed at all? Um, are you using any Answer Engines differently? Or more or less often than you did before?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:00.528000Z",
        "message": "I'm using chat GP much more than I probably was a year ago. I would say Google Search is about the same."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:10.208000Z",
        "message": "Interesting shift. So chat GPT use has increased. While Google's held steady. Can you remember a moment when you first started reaching for ChatGPT GPT instead of Google, or what triggered that change for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:23.148000Z",
        "message": "Receiving professional development at work is what triggered me starting to use chat be GPT. I learned from the session how useful it could be and then I started in integrating it into my work."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:40.048000Z",
        "message": "Super clear. That training opened the door and, uh, you decided to actually use it. Do friends or coworkers ever recommend Answer Engines to you for specific things, or is it mostly your own experimenting that guides what you use?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:55.738000Z",
        "message": "Um, it's my own experimenting, but I believe most of my coworkers also use a combination of ChatGPT and Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:05.938000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful. Sounds like mix is pretty common in your circle. Last question. If you could wish for any feature or improvement in either Google or ChatGPT to make your answer finding even better. What would it be?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:23.098000Z",
        "message": "I would like to be able to do more extensive searching through Google like I do on ChatGPT because when I'm on ChatGPT, it opens up more links for me to get into more depth with the topic. Google does not do that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dd9a563bceb3493f9f4dd5236",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:46.188000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So you'd like Google to work more like ChatGPT, letting you go deeper and branch out with relevant links, not quick answers. Thanks for sharing that, and thanks for the conversation. If you have any feedback about chatting with an AI or wanna add anything else, let me let me know. Otherwise, you're all set and can end the call whenever you'd like."
      }
    ],
