  {
    "id": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
    "responseId": "e8bd8ead2e134e4a832d1826a",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:26.431000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:34.771000Z",
        "message": "It's going well. How's yours going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:38.571000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for asking. I'm doing well. Always curious to learn how people actually use these answer tools. In real life. So let's start pretty casually. When you need to look something up online, say you have a random question, what's what's the very first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:54.940000Z",
        "message": "The very first thing I usually do is swipe to Google. And then I go from there."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:04.451000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Google's the default starting point. Walk me through what happens after that swipe. What do you do next step by step? The moment you open Google to when you get your answer?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:15.291000Z",
        "message": "I will either automatically say my question or what my what I'm inquiring about. Or I will type it in depending on if my hands are available. Then I look at the answers and I will compare the answers before I figure out which 1 is the best."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:43.421000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful. When you say compare the answers, what exactly are you looking at? Or 4? Is it headlines, snippets, links, something else? Tell me a bit more about what helps you choose which answer feels best."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:57.661000Z",
        "message": "I look at where the response is coming from. Let's say whether it's about the news, I'll look to see if it's local news. I'll look to see if maybe it's Fox News. Or MSN News. Um, I look to see where the response is coming from."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:27:20.391000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense? Checking the source of the answer. Uh, how do you feel when you see you know, certain sources come up? For example, if it's Fox News versus MSN or local news, does that change your confidence? Or how much you trust the answer?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:27:36.291000Z",
        "message": "If it's local news, it does change my confidence in the answer. I will trust more national news than I will local news."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:27:49.590000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So national news sources feel more reliable to you than local ones. Can you tell me about a recent time when when you did this? What was the topic? And how did you decide which answer to trust?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:02.670000Z",
        "message": "The most recent topic was the shooting of Charles Kirk. I felt more comfortable hearing from national news rather than I did local news. About the facts that actually what actually occurred and everything."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:24.791000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that example. When you were sorting through those answers, was there anything about the way Google presented information, like the layout, summaries, or types of links that made the process easier or tougher for you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:39.561000Z",
        "message": "It did make it a little bit tougher because it did apply the local news first, but I understand that being the case because most people do prefer local news where as I myself prefer national news."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:00.571000Z",
        "message": "That's a great observation. So Google's preference for local news didn't quite match what you wanted. And you had to scroll or look harder for the national coverage. When that happens, when the results don't quite line up with what you want, do you ever switch to a different, you know, tool or app or do you mostly stick with Google and just dig deeper?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:20.151000Z",
        "message": "I mostly stick with Google and deep"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:26.541000Z",
        "message": "Got it. You stick with Google and keep searching until you find what you're after. Have you tried AI based engines like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini? To look up answers before? Or is Google pretty much your go to for most questions?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:40.911000Z",
        "message": "Google is pretty much my go to. CAT GPT and the AI involved I have been kind of hesitant to use them just out of its kind of fear of the unknown."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:00.771000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for being honest about that. You say fear of the unknown, what does that feel like for you? Is it concerns about accuracy, privacy, or just not being sure how it works? Tell me a little more about what gives you pause."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:14.231000Z",
        "message": "It's not being sure how it works. And also a fear of privacy being invaded. Or being taken advantage of at at some point in time."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:26.601000Z",
        "message": "That makes a lot of sense. Knowing exactly what happens with your info or how these AI tools get their answers. Can definitely create hesitation. If you think about would help you feel more comfortable trying out something like ChatGPT or Perplexity. But what comes to mind? Is there anything these tools could do or show you that might earn your trust or or make you curious to give them a shot?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:30:51.741000Z",
        "message": "Being a little bit more available and a little bit more user friendly, I guess you could say. I'm in my forties so I'm already kind of used to using Google and everything. Like Safari and everything, to help look up at you know, my type of it my type of answers and everything. So just finding more information about what it actually does. And what it would incorporate."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:27.391000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate that. So if AI engines felt more approachable, and explain clearly what they do with your info, and maybe even showed up right alongside the tools you're already used to you'd be more open to trying them out. When you hear the name ChatGPT or Perplexity,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:40.511000Z",
        "message": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:42.591000Z",
        "message": "are there any particular feelings, words, or images that pop into your mind? Or is it just kind of a blank, not much of association yet?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:31:51.561000Z",
        "message": "It's at actually it brings up the word just advanced technology. Just those words. And it does like I've said before, it, you know, brings a little bit of fear into me as to, oh 0 gosh. I don't know what to do with it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:08.861000Z",
        "message": "I hear you. The advanced technology label feels a bit intimidating and unfamiliar. When you chat with friends or coworkers, does anyone mention using these AI engines for searching answers? Instead of Google? Or does most conversations still revolve around Google or more familiar tools?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:26.600000Z",
        "message": "Some of my younger friends and everything do talk about using chat and Gemini, and, you know, I just I listen to them, but it's like I'm not really hearing exactly what it can do. Um, it's kind of like they're speaking a whole another language to me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:44.101000Z",
        "message": "That's really vivid. The idea of it feeling like another language. Do you ever feel curious to to try using those tools after hearing them talk? Or does it mostly reinforce wanting to stick with what, you know?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:32:56.281000Z",
        "message": "I do. Definitely want to try CAT GPT or Gemini whenever after speaking with them and everything and especially seeing them use it in action. But it's just that kind of underlying fear"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:18.211000Z",
        "message": "That sounds like you're on the edge of curiosity and hesitation. Seeing it in action helps, but there's still that barrier. If you imagine your ideal way to try out an AI answer engine for the first time, what would help you feel safe and confident? Could be anything, step by step guide, a clear privacy statement, a friend walking you through it. Whatever pops into your mind."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:40.921000Z",
        "message": "A friend walking me through it would be very helpful."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:33:46.061000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Having someone you you trust there, showing you how it works, and answering your questions would help bridge that unknown. Shifting gears just a bit, thinking back to your habits. A year ago, do you notice any change in how you look things up online? Or is it mostly the same as it's always been?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:04.971000Z",
        "message": "I use a lot of talk to text more, and I use the Google image more."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:14.871000Z",
        "message": "Interesting shift. So using talk to tech and Google image searches more often now. Uh, can you remember what led you to start using those features more? Was it convenience? A specific situation, or or or just something you explored and liked?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:28.821000Z",
        "message": "It was something that I explored in life and found the convenience of using it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:36.781000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for clarifying. So exploring those features and realizing how convenient they were made them part of your routine. When you share answers with other people, say, sending a link or screenshot, do you feel like the answer Google is received as credible? Or do people sometimes question it? Tell me about what that's like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:34:55.540000Z",
        "message": "I think it is received as credible. Majority of my friends are older, and so they are used to using Google already. And to them, Google is extremely credible."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:09.041000Z",
        "message": "That's useful to know Google's built in credibility among your circle, especially older friends. If you imagine a future where something else might become your main go to for answers instead of Google, what do you think would need to happen or or change or change to make that switch feel right?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:35:27.761000Z",
        "message": "I think just learning more about it and becoming more familiar with what it does and having it be at the ready. Just like Google is so it's always ready. It's always prepared. You know, I don't have to wait for answers. Everything is just right there. So I think just having it slowly just kind of put into my everyday average use."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:00.430000Z",
        "message": "Makes total sense. A tool being reliable, instantly available, and easy to weave into your normal routine would make"
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:07.121000Z",
        "message": "Okay."
      },
      {
        "callId": "900d92c3a7ce4744aa33573e3",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:36:11.001000Z",
        "message": "That's all the questions I had for you today. Thanks for sharing your honest thoughts. It's been really helpful. If you ever wanna talk more about search engines or tech, I'm here. You can end the call whenever you'd like."
      }
    ],
