      {
        "callId": "c4a994d3708848b9be794a168",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:56.360000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. Was it something personal or related to relationships maybe? Tell me a little more about what you were hoping to find and what sort of results Instagram gave you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c4a994d3708848b9be794a168",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:08.710000Z",
        "message": "Oh, it's personal?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c4a994d3708848b9be794a168",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:11.300000Z",
        "message": "No worries at all. Share only what you're comfortable with. Even just a sense of what type of guidance or answers you were looking for. Advice, experiences, community support, etcetera. Is helpful. Well, it made Instagram feel like the right place for that compared to Google. Are you still there? Feel free to ask me any questions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c4a994d3708848b9be794a168",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:51.370000Z",
        "message": "Instagram is more family oriented."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c4a994d3708848b9be794a168",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:54.760000Z",
        "message": "That's really interesting. So when you say Instagram is more family oriented, does it feel like you get advice or stories from people who feel familiar or relatable? What's it like compared to getting answers from Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c4a994d3708848b9be794a168",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:09.660000Z",
        "message": "Deja's is more family oriented online. Some people that could give you more advice through family."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c4a994d3708848b9be794a168",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:18.580000Z",
        "message": "That makes a lot of sense. It sounds like when you're looking for advice or support about family topics, you find it more helpful to get answers from people with shared experiences on platforms like Instagram or even from accounts like Deja's, rather than the info you get from Google. How do you feel about the answers you get from Instagram compared to Google? Do they feel more useful, trustworthy, or maybe just more comforting?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c4a994d3708848b9be794a168",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
