        "callId": "c4a994d3708848b9be794a168",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:00.639000Z",
        "message": "Because some of the people have went through what I'm searching for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c4a994d3708848b9be794a168",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:07.840000Z",
        "message": "Makes a lot of sense. Knowing someone's actually lived through a similar experience probably gives you more trust in their advice. Thinking about Google for a second, when you use it to look things up, do you ever find yourself, like, double checking or looking for personal stories elsewhere? Or do you usually stick with the results Google gives you?"
      },
      {
