        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:26.790000Z",
        "message": "I sometimes go out if it's personal."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c4a994d3708848b9be794a168",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:33.550000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So for personal topics, you look beyond Google and seek out other places or people. When it comes to things that aren't personal, like facts or how to's, do you trust Google more? Or do you ever use tools like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or the AI summaries you see in Google searches?"
      },
