      {
        "callId": "7e7d79921e704072a5c3d6877",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:22.293000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "7e7d79921e704072a5c3d6877",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:31.103000Z",
        "message": "Fine. How's yours?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "7e7d79921e704072a5c3d6877",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:33.803000Z",
        "message": "I'm doing well. Thanks for asking. So let's start simple. When you need answers online, say, you're curious about something need to solve a problem, what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "7e7d79921e704072a5c3d6877",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:46.593000Z",
        "message": "Normally, would go to Google. But lately, I've discovered Gemini, so sometimes I go there."
      },
      {
        "callId": "7e7d79921e704072a5c3d6877",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:55.583000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. Sounds like you're mixing things up a bit lately. Can you walk me through a recent time when you needed to look something up? Which tool did you end up using first, and what was the situation?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "7e7d79921e704072a5c3d6877",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:08.763000Z",
        "message": "Actually, I can't remember the last thing I actually looked up. It was a while ago."
      },
      {
        "callId": "7e7d79921e704072a5c3d6877",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:21.233000Z",
        "message": "No worries. Happens to the best of us. Thinking about those times, in general, when you do go searching for an answer, what tends to make you pick Google or Gemini first? Is there anything about the situation or the kind of question that nudges you 1 way or the other?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "7e7d79921e704072a5c3d6877",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:36.943000Z",
        "message": "I think if it's something I don't think Google can answer then I go to Gemini."
      },
      {
        "callId": "7e7d79921e704072a5c3d6877",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:45.163000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So when you sense Google might not cut it, Gemini gets the call."
      },
      {
        "callId": "7e7d79921e704072a5c3d6877",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:49.283000Z",
        "message": "Right."
      },
      {
        "callId": "7e7d79921e704072a5c3d6877",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:49.353000Z",
        "message": "Can you think of the kinds of questions or topics where Google can't answer what does that usually mean for you?"
