  {
    "id": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
    "responseId": "a3efc7da516e48e883e895c9f",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:50.255000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:58.775000Z",
        "message": "Pretty good in yours?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:01.295000Z",
        "message": "I don't have days quite the same way, but I'm glad to be here and genuinely curious about how you find, uh, answers online. Let's start with the basics. When you need to look something up, or get an answer online, what's what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:16.475000Z",
        "message": "I asked Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:21.445000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So Google's your default starting point. Can you walk me through what that usually looks like for you step by step? For example, how do you decide what to search for and what do you do after you see the results?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:36.225000Z",
        "message": "Usually, if I'm engaging in a conversation or see something online, I don't actually understand, I'll go x Google for an explanation. And once I read it, I and I've got a clearer picture of what it is, then I can better respond to whoever I've engaged in the conversation with about it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:58.525000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for breaking that down. Thinking about the last time this this happened, can you tell me the full story starting from when you first realized you needed to look something up? What did you type in, and how did it unfold from there? Feel free to ask me any questions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:23.365000Z",
        "message": "Can you repeat that?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:25.705000Z",
        "message": "Of course. I was asking about the most recent time you looked something up. Using Google starting from when you realized you needed an answer. Can you walk me through what happened step by step? For example, what triggered"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:37.044000Z",
        "message": "Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah. I was actually having a conversation with someone over TikTok, and they asked me, had I heard about the activist that was recently killed at 1 of he was having some sort of public meeting at a school in Virginia, I believe. And he was killed. I didn't know who he was, so I went and Googled his name. And I had to figure out who he was and the topics that he talked about before I can actually engage further into that conversation with the TikToker."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:15.335000Z",
        "message": "That's a pretty vivid example. Uh, thanks for sharing it. When you googled his name, what did the search results look like? How did you decide which things to click on, or did you just read what was on the first page?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:28.315000Z",
        "message": "I just basically read, um, what was in the first page because it was like a biography of who he was and that he went to different states and different cities and talked about different political reviews. He talked about democrats, republics, He talked about the laws that were being enforced the new laws, the old laws, and stuff like that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:58.185000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. When you're looking at that first page, biographies, news stories, details, what helps you decide if you trust what you're reading? Are there any signs or clues you look for before you feel confident sharing that info back in your conversation?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:14.335000Z",
        "message": "Yes. I actually look for videos, um, that try that, like, corresponds with what I read. And I actually was able to find a video of the guy actually speaking at 1 of the press conferences with the president of the United States."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:36.905000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. You look for actual videos to match what you've read. When you find both written info and video, does that make you feel more confident about sharing or or quoting those details back? Or are there still any hesitations?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:51.475000Z",
        "message": "No. There's no hesitations. I feel pretty confident once I have enough evidence that I like, what I'm reading okay. Yeah. Now I believe it because this actual person, their self, is speaking on what this biography just said that they speak on."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:10.835000Z",
        "message": "That's clear. So for you, seeing the person in action kind of seals the deal. Shifting gears a little, does Google ever frustrate you when you're trying to find this kind of info? Uh, if so, can you tell me a story about a recent time that happened?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:27.494000Z",
        "message": "Yes. Sometimes when I know there's information out there about a certain thing or a certain person, but sometimes Google doesn't always pull it up. For instance, I was googling just the other week. I googled a fruit, and, uh, I know for sure that Google knows about this Mongolian fruit because it's a fruit. In fact, I just didn't know where to get the fruit. So it was kinda frustrating that Google couldn't tell me where to get the fruit, and I had to result to blogs and other forms to find out where to get the fruit in my state."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:14.125000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for describing that. It sounds like Google gave you general info, but not the answer you really needed. Like, where to actually buy the fruit. When you hit a wall like that, what's your next step? Do you ever try other tools like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or even social media? Or do you stick with Google and just dig deeper?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:33.905000Z",
        "message": "No. I actually dig deeper with other, like, chat BT, and I do go on TikTok. I'll go on Facebook. Places like that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:47.025000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So when you switch over to know, tools like ChatGPT or TikTok after Google, what's usually the reason? Is there something you're hoping those other places will do better or differently?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:59.665000Z",
        "message": "Yes. I'm actually, like, speaking with real people or AI generated things. It usually gives you the precise you know, information that you're really looking for. And it's it is different. Like, on Facebook, they're, like, like, actual people that can tell you like, thousands of millions of people that could tell you, like, exactly where to get it from."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:25.425000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Direct info from real people or a more targeted AI answer feels more precise for you. Thinking about ChatGP"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:31.695000Z",
        "message": "Correct."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:34.175000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for confirming. Um, thinking about the different tools you use, Google, ChatGPT, TikTok, Facebook, can you describe how the answers feel different from each 1? For example, is there 1 that feels more trustworthy, faster, or just easier to use?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:49.955000Z",
        "message": "Um, to me, they're all easier to use, and faster, and they're most definitely always on point or positive, uh, because some people even have receipts If they say they got something from this place, oh, well, I got it from this place, or I ordered it from this place, and I can show you my receipt. I ordered it online. And that's kinda I kinda feel, you know, it's trustworthy, and I'll be able to find what I'm looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:27:18.374000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. Especially when people share their own proof or experiences. Focusing on ChatGPT for a moment. When you use it for answers, how do its responses feel compared to, say, what you get from Google or someone on Facebook? Is there anything that stands out, or is it pretty similar in your experience?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:27:36.425000Z",
        "message": "It's it's all pretty similar in my experience."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:27:41.345000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to know. Thinking about trust for a second. When you share an answer with someone else, is there any tools response you'd feel more confident quoting? Or does it not matter much as long as you've confirmed the info? Yourself?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:27:55.675000Z",
        "message": "I feel like as long as I've confirmed the info, then it's it's pretty trustworthy."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:02.615000Z",
        "message": "Understood. So double checking is your main trust factor. No matter where the answer comes from. If you think about your own habits over the past year, has anything changed in how you things up or which engines you choose first? Or does it feel pretty much the same as before?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:18.305000Z",
        "message": "No. It's pretty much the same as before, but only the added the newer app that they've come out with and the new AI generated apps that they came up with, I have added those instead of just going to social media. I now have the capabilities to go and ask, uh, chat BT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:37.995000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So the main change is adding new AI tools alongside your usual social media searches. Not necessarily switching away from Google. Thinking about the future for a second, is there anything you wish these answer engines or AI apps could do for you that none of them do yet? Any wish list features or things that would make your life noticeably easier?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:00.424000Z",
        "message": "No. Not really. I mean, they do everything as expected or, you know, what I expect out of them."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:07.935000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Sounds like you're pretty satisfied, uh, with what's out there. Right now. Last thing, just curious. How did chatting with an AI interviewer feel compared to your usual online conversations or searches? All set to go whenever you'd like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:23.914000Z",
        "message": "I honestly feel comfortable chatting with AI. Just knowing like, I'm chatting with somebody that's nonjudgmental, so I really I really like it. I enjoy it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ae3fe9a930644b84bfa5c54f3",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:36.385000Z",
        "message": "I'm really glad to hear that. Thanks again for sharing your stories and experiences so openly. If you ever feel like chatting again about how you search or use AI tools, I'm here for it. You can end the call. You'd like."
      }
