  {
    "id": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
    "responseId": "a8d97015dc3c445ebc6d0596b",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:55.492000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:03.691000Z",
        "message": "Good."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:06.061000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. Let's start with something simple. When you need answers online, say, for a quick fact or some advice, what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:17.132000Z",
        "message": "Go to Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:19.802000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing. When you head to Google for answers, can you walk me through your typical process? What steps do you take from the moment you think of your question to when you feel satisfied? With the answer"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:34.872000Z",
        "message": "I go on Google. I type in what I'm looking for, and then I see the result. And I pick what's going and read it. And then I go by the 1 that I feel is more suitable for what my question is."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:47.982000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Thinking about the last time you went through that process, what kind of question were you looking up? Can you tell me a bit about what you needed and how you decided which result felt right for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:00.442000Z",
        "message": "Well, I was looking up because I was having some serious foot change. And I was trying to look up why this pain was happening. Like, what could be the cause"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:13.942000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. When you typed your question about your foot pain into Google, what kind of results did you see? Was it articles, forms, images, something else? And how did you decide which 1 to click"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:24.802000Z",
        "message": "There was yeah. There was images of, like, where my foot pain is hurting in my foot. So I actually clicked on that, and the result popped up."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:39.152000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. The images grabbed your attention. First, when you saw the image, and the info that popped up, did it give you what you needed right away? Or did you still have to look at other results or or dig deeper?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:53.842000Z",
        "message": "Actually, no. I felt comfortable with the result I see right away, actually."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:01.172000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Thinking about that experience, what part, you know, of using Google felt most helpful to you? Was it the speed, the images, how easy it was to decide, or maybe something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:12.802000Z",
        "message": "I would have to say the images. Definitely. Because it's so right where I was having the pain at."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:21.272000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to know. So in that moment, seeing the image that matched your pain made you comfortable and confident in the answer you found. If you haven't used Google, let's say, for some reason you couldn't, what do you think you would have done instead? To figure out what was going on?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:38.401000Z",
        "message": "Probably just contact my doctor."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:42.792000Z",
        "message": "I hear you. Turning to a medical professional would be your next move. Without Google. Now, sometimes people use other other answer engines. Like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Perplexity, or Google's own AI summaries. Can you think of a time when you use something besides Google to get an answer? What led you there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:05.692000Z",
        "message": "There is none."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:09.152000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for being clear. So for you, Google is your main tool for finding answers. Are there ever times when you've noticed Google's answers don't quite give you what you need or maybe you felt frustrated using it? Can you think of an example?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:24.172000Z",
        "message": "No. I honestly can't."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:28.412000Z",
        "message": "Alright. That's good to hear. It sounds like Google does the job for you most of the time. When you think about Google as a brand, what sort of feelings or associations come to mind? If Google were a person at a party, how would they act?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:43.812000Z",
        "message": "Happy, honest, believable,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:51.262000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate that. So happy, honest, and believable. That's how Google feels to you. If you had to share an answer, you found online with a friend or family member, would Google's result feel credible enough to send, or are there certain types of questions where you'd double check first?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:08.872000Z",
        "message": "I would say definitely credible."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:12.032000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for that. Looking back over the past year or so, has anything changed in how often or how you use Google to look things up? Or would you say your habits have stayed about the same?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:22.892000Z",
        "message": "My habit's been about the same."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:28.692000Z",
        "message": "Understood. And do friends, family, or coworkers ever suggest using other tools for looking things up, like ChatGPT or anything besides Google? Or does everyone in your circle mainly stick to Google too?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:42.572000Z",
        "message": "I run on my circle sticks to Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:47.602000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So it sounds like Google is pretty established for you in your circle. Kind of the default choice. Before we finish up, is there anything you wish Google could do differently or better when you're searching for answers? Any dream features or a frustration? It could solve?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:03.302000Z",
        "message": "No. No. Not at all."
      },
      {
        "callId": "0c6e98b7f01845088dc799580",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:06.872000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for being so open with your thoughts. That's all I had for today. You've been really helpful. You ever want to share more stories, I'm here. You can end the call whenever you'd like."
      }
    ],
    "attributes": [
