  {
    "id": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
    "responseId": "2fa963f1653c48fca29815911",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:32.456000Z",
        "message": "Hello?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:32.856000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:40.506000Z",
        "message": "It's going great. Going absolutely wonderful."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:44.126000Z",
        "message": "Glad love to hear that. So just to get started, when you're looking for answers online, what's what's the very first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:57.566000Z",
        "message": "I usually go to Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:02.766000Z",
        "message": "Got it. You start with Google. Can you walk me through what that looks like for you step by step? For example, say you need an answer about something. What's your process from the moment that need pops up?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:16.176000Z",
        "message": "It depends. If it's recently in the news, a lot of times, I'll click on the news section of Google But if not, I just go straight to a website and start to research. Wikipedia is 1 that I use often as well. Through Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:35.836000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So sometimes you use Google's news tab if it's a current event. But otherwise, you look for websites or Wikipedia through Google, thinking about your most recent search, what was the topic, and how did you decide where to click or what to read?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:54.106000Z",
        "message": "The most recent topic was the Charlie Kirk shooting, and I wound up using the news section and clicking on several different websites."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:08.126000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for walking me through that. When you used Google's news section for the Charlie Kirk shooting, what helped you decide which articles to click on? Was it the headline? The website source, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:21.176000Z",
        "message": "Usually, the website source"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:26.656000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. Are there certain sources you trust more than others or any you tend to avoid when searching through Google News?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:35.336000Z",
        "message": "I pretty much tend to avoid MSNBC because I do not believe they are unbiased. But other than that, it really just depends on the headline of the article."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:53.116000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So aside from avoiding MSNBC, you let the headline guide you. When you read an article from a source you trust, do you usually stick with just that? Or do you find yourself checking multiple sources for the same topic? Tell me about how you decide when you've done enough searching."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:16.146000Z",
        "message": "It's hard to determine when I've done enough searching because it's different for most subjects. But the most recent with the Charlie Kirk, it was when I found out the information I was looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:30.435000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like it really depends on the question and how satisfied you are with the information you find. Thinking about that last search using Google News. What part of the experience felt most helpful, and was there anything that frustrated or annoyed you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:47.295000Z",
        "message": "Well, certain updates minute by minute or hour by hour updates helped out a lot. But it was a recent event so certain lack of information that was present frustrated me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:06.976000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. So the constant updates were helpful, but limited information early on, you know, was frustrating. If Google didn't have enough info at the moment, do you ever turn to another tool like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or maybe social media for answers? Tell me how you handle those gaps."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:27.696000Z",
        "message": "Sometimes I'll check on chat chat GPT, but for the most part, I'll go to a source such as Twitter or Facebook and see if I can find any extra information that way."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:40.576000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. When you check ChatGPT or social media, like, Twitter or Facebook after Google, what kind of info are you hoping to find there that Google wasn't giving you? Can you give me an example of how the answers or experience felt different?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:55.176000Z",
        "message": "Honestly, at that point, I'm not really looking for any correct information as much as I'm looking to see if I can find any different or new information."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:08.205000Z",
        "message": "I hear you. You're scanning for fresh angles or details that aren't showing up in Google yet."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:12.985000Z",
        "message": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:15.886000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for clarifying. Thinking about those moments when you use ChatGPT or social media for answers, What stands out about how you experience those tools compared to Google? Is there anything you find stronger, weaker, or just noticeably different?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:32.776000Z",
        "message": "Not really."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:36.076000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate the honesty. So for you, Google still feels pretty much like the default. And using other tools doesn't stand out in a big way. Is there anything that would actually make you switch your main search or answer engine away from Google Maybe a feature you wish existed or a frustration that would push you to try something else."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:57.746000Z",
        "message": "Not really. I trust Google and always have, and it's hard to trust new and interesting apps on the Internet, especially with AI. It's very hard to trust AI because AI presents a lot of false visuals and things like that, so you're not sure whether or not you're going to get correct information from AI either."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:25.566000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Sounds like trust in Google is a is a big factor. And there's some uncertainty around AI tools and the accuracy what they provide. If you were telling a friend or or coworker why you stick with Google, what words or feelings would you use to describe it? And how would you describe ChatGPT or other AI engines? If they came up in conversation?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:49.606000Z",
        "message": "I would describe Google as simple without a lot of ads and very informative, lots of news, The results for Google include news. You can get images. You can get shopping. You can get pretty much anything. But with ChatGPT, I feel like you pretty much just get the answer you're looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:12.986000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for painting that picture. So Google feels simple, wide ranging, and gives access to lots of types of info. News, images, shopping, all in 1 place. With ChatGPT, it's more straightforward. You get just an answer. If you stacked up Google ChatGPT and maybe Perplexity or Gemini, which 1 feels most helpful for you personally and why?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:34.306000Z",
        "message": "Gemini has always been the most helpful to me because it's on my phone, and it it's it's just simple and easy to use."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:45.936000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. Gemini's helpfulness comes down to it being simple, easy, and right on your phone. Thinking about a recent time you used Gemini, what was the task, and how did it feel compared to using Google or ChatGPT?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:27:03.496000Z",
        "message": "I used it to create an image to send to my niece. So I asked it to paint a picture of a kitty, and it did, and I sent it to my niece."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:27:14.746000Z",
        "message": "That's a fun and specific use. When Gemini made the kitty image for your niece, what part of that process felt especially smooth or maybe not so smooth? Did you need to tweak your request or fact check anything, or was it exactly what you wanted?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:27:29.806000Z",
        "message": "Yes. I had to tweak my request because, apparently, it couldn't create the image that I wanted initially due to some kind of copyright issue or something. But it was able we were able to I was able to tweak my wording and get it to create pretty much what I wanted."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:27:47.626000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that detail. So you ran into a copyright issue. But by adjusting your request, Gemini was able to deliver. How did you feel about the final result? Did it feel satisfying, or or was there anything you wished was different about the experience?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:07.126000Z",
        "message": "I wish they didn't have the copyright issues"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:14.226000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. If those copyright limits weren't there, sounds like you'd be happier with the experience. Thinking more broadly, is there anything else you wish Answer Engines, like Gemini, Google, or ChatGPT could do for you in the future Any features or improvements you'd put on a wish list?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:33.486000Z",
        "message": "No. Not really."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:37.706000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate your honesty. Thanks for, uh, walking me through your search habits and use of these use of these tools. Before we wrap up, how did you find talking to an AI moderator like me? Any feedback or thoughts on the experience?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:28:51.836000Z",
        "message": "Very interesting. I highly enjoyed it, and this is probably the favorite survey I've ever done because different, unique, and new."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:03.235000Z",
        "message": "That's awesome to hear. Thanks for sharing and for being so open throughout our chat. You're all set for today. You can end the call whenever you'd like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:12.856000Z",
        "message": "Thank you. You have a great day."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e92e36814e274e73b1afdfa79",
        "index": 43,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:29:15.786000Z",
        "message": "Thank you for calling."
      }
    ],
    "attributes": [
