        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:03.320000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. So when you reached for Google for answers about that situation, can you walk me through exactly what you did and what you were hoping to find? What was the process like for you step by step?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "43780cc5e93049c690a458a17",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:17.559000Z",
        "message": "So I searched for it on Google, and then AI comes up. And gives me an idea about where I can look for answers."
      },
      {
        "callId": "43780cc5e93049c690a458a17",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:32.640000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So now when you search, sometimes Google gives you an AI generated summary or suggestion first. When that happens, how do you feel about it? Do you tend to trust those AI answers? Or do you scroll down to look for other results or sources?"
      },
      {
