        "callId": "43780cc5e93049c690a458a17",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:25.860000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So it sounds like sometimes Google's AI suggestions actually help you discover an even better answer than you expected. On other occasions, you find exactly what you're looking for right away. Has there ever been a time where the Google AI answer didn't quite work for you? Or maybe left you wanting more information? What did you do next in that situation?"
