  {
    "id": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
    "responseId": "f4268c2fd8d44184a6cca9ad6",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:52.478000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:00.438000Z",
        "message": "It's going good. How are you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:04.137000Z",
        "message": "I'm glad to hear that. I'm doing well. Thanks for asking. I'm really interested in learning about how you look things up online these days. When you need an answer or info, big or small, what's what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:17.568000Z",
        "message": "You go to Google? And I put it on AI mode sometimes and sometimes I do all just to get all the options."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:26.858000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful. So Google's your starting point. And you sometimes switch on the AI mode for answers. Can you walk me through your typical process? Say, you're curious about something. You open Google, then what happens step by step after that?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:41.187000Z",
        "message": "I type in my search criteria. You know, whatever it is I'm looking for. And then I choose the options. Do I wanna see pictures? Do I wanna see AI mode? Do I wanna see everything? And then I just click on what looks more you know, more cohesive or more complete. And I choose based on that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:08.418000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for breaking that down. When you look at those options, like pictures, AI mode, or seeing everything, what usually helps you decide which 1 to check out first?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:21.298000Z",
        "message": "If the answer is seems a little sketchy or the source of the answer is a little bit sketchy, then I'll skip right over. If it looks more like what I'm I'm looking for, if it looks more like the correct answer, if it's, you know you know, the website of you know, let's say I'm looking at a product. If it's if it's the the man manufacturer's website, then I'm more apt to believe it than if it's just some random answer, like Reddit, where someone just posted a bunch of stuff. So it just depends."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:00.708000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. So it sounds like the trustworthiness of the source is a big deal for you. Thinking about the last time you used Google's AI mode, can you tell me the whole story, what you needed, how you searched, and what stood out about the experience?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:16.507000Z",
        "message": "I was looking for I had heard about the death of, uh, Charlie Kirk, and I wanted to look and see what had happened. So I just typed it in, and, of course, every news outlet was reporting it. So I just picked a few that I thought were more trustworthy, more unbiased, and use those. If it was a website, that was more left leaning or, you know, then I probably won't because I want a balanced and truthful answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:51.928000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate you sharing that example. As you looked through the AI results, and multiple news outlets, was there anything about Google's AI summary or regular results that felt especially helpful or maybe frustrating in that moment?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:05.867000Z",
        "message": "I wasn't frustrated. They did give me just a brief synopsis of what had been reported. So it wasn't really a particular outlet When I put it on AI mode, it just kinda summarizes what's been reported. So I think it takes a culmination of what everybody's reporting and kinda summarized it. And then you can go and choose which news outlet that you want to look at. If you want more information."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:35.028000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So the AI summary gave you that quick overview, and then you could pick specific sources for deeper details. In that moment, did the AI summary feel like enough or did you end up clicking into a news outlet for more context? So tell me how you decided."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:50.828000Z",
        "message": "It was as far as he was shot and killed, but I wanted to know, like, more. Like, what happened? Who was it? You know, has it been found you know, has the person been found? Why did he do it? That kind of thing. And, of course, that information is still being rolled out. So that was not all immediately available at the time."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:13.718000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for explaining your thought process. When the summary didn't cover all the details you wanted, did you do anything specific, like scroll further, adjust your search, or compare answers between AI mode and regular results. Tell me a bit about what steps you took next."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:31.558000Z",
        "message": "I clicked on a couple of news outlets that I thought was not politically motivated because they are politicizing this story. I was really not interested in that. I just scrolled to another, you know, to another source just see if there was any additional information that was available."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:52.358000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. So you were actively steering away from sources that felt biased. And looking for more factual info. When you're searching like this,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:59.148000Z",
        "message": "Right."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:00.448000Z",
        "message": "have you ever felt the need to check answers on another tool? Like ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini? Or do you mostly stick with Google and it's options?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:11.098000Z",
        "message": "I have not tried to compare it with with other AI sources. Because, like, Meta will always come up when you use certain social media searches. Just because it's it's what's available. But, no, I did not compare it with other AI modes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:34.028000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So for now, it's mostly Google. For these kinds of searches. Other engines don't really factor in for you yet. Thinking about Google AI mode specifically, what would you say is its biggest strength for you? And is there any part of it that you wish worked differently?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:53.008000Z",
        "message": "Um, even AI mode is a little biased. I've learned that. They you know? But I guess everybody is to some extent. I just want straight information. And so I tend to if I if I do see bias, I will go to an alternative source immediately. And that's not to say everything that was reported is wrong. It just means that I'm not going to get the straight answer that I'm looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:23.718000Z",
        "message": "Really clear points. When you spot bias in the AI summary, and you switch to another source, what does that alternative source look like for you? Is it another website, a news outlet, or do you ever open another engine or app Tell me about your usual workaround when the answer doesn't feel straight."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:41.248000Z",
        "message": "I will use another web browser. Instead of Google. I may go to Safari or I may go to you know, another, um, a third a third option, or I may go straight to a news website that I trust more."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:56.667000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. You actually switched browsers or head straight to a trusted site. When you do that, does it feel different from using Google's AI mode?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:05.107000Z",
        "message": "It is yeah, it is different. Like, Safari and Google are different. So you may get a few different options, and then you can choose it from those options. As to which source you want to trust."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:19.308000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for clarifying. If you lined up Google AI mode, Safari search results and maybe a direct visit to a new site, how would you describe describe the differences you noticed in the answers or experience? What stands out with each 1?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:34.848000Z",
        "message": "Google is I think because I use them so much, they are they're pretty standard as far as I wanted news, they're gonna do CNN. They're gonna do MSNBC. You know, they're gonna do all of the left leaning sources first, and then you'll get few of the right leaning sources when in reality, I just want information. I want the truth. I want information. Um, that's typically what I've noticed with with Google. Um, and if I go to to Safari, it seems to be a healthier mix. Of sources."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:14.668000Z",
        "message": "That's a really interesting distinction. So with Google, feel like the lineup skews in a certain direction, while Safari feels more"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:22.648000Z",
        "message": "Right. Because that is right."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:28.688000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for confirming. When you think about a tool like ChatGPT, even if you haven't used it much, what's your impression of it compared to something like Google's AI mode or searching in Safari? Any words or feelings come to mind?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:41.268000Z",
        "message": "I've used CHED GPT once on just on a something that I was looking up. Chad GPT seemed more detailed is what I think. Like, you got a lot more information than you would have gotten otherwise."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:03.488000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful. So ChatGPT felt extra detailed when you tried it. Was it a good thing, or did it ever feel like too much info? Or maybe less focused? How did you respond to that level of detail?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:17.428000Z",
        "message": "I didn't ask it a question that would that could be politicized, so I didn't notice it was left or right leaning, but I didn't notice that it gave me quite a bit of information for what I was looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:33.038000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Uh, for the kind of search you did, having more information felt useful. If you think back, did you feel more confident sharing ChatGPT's answer with someone else? Compared to sharing something you'd found on Google? Or does it feel about the same?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:23:51.728000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. Because details do matter and of just a brief snapshot. So, yes, I would probably feel more confident sharing that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:03.618000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. For you, it sounds like having that extra detail boosts confidence when you're sharing info. You had to line up Google AI mode, Safari and ChatGPT from most to least helpful for your own searches, how would you rank them and what's your thinking behind that order?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:21.678000Z",
        "message": "I would do Safari, then I would do Google. Because Google only gets political if you ask a a question that could be politicized. It doesn't always do that. But sadly, the death of Chad Charlie Kirk is very political because he was a right wing commentator political commentator. So of course, that's immediately going to get politicized."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:51.148000Z",
        "message": "So for you, Safari comes first for a good mix of sources. Google, second. Mostly reliable, but with occasional bias depending on the topic. And ChatGPT, you see as especially helpful for extra detail,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:24:58.988000Z",
        "message": "Right."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:02.788000Z",
        "message": "Is there any feature tool or improvement you wish any of these engines had that would make you much more likely to use it as your main go to in the future?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:12.017000Z",
        "message": "Stop politicizing everything. Some of us just want the truth."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:20.448000Z",
        "message": "That's direct and clear, less biased, more straightforward, truth, is what you're after. Last quick question."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 43,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:25.768000Z",
        "message": "Correct."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 44,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:27.587000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for your candor. Last quick question. Have friends or coworkers ever suggested a search tool or AI engine to you or talked about which ones they trust for getting answers. If so, tell me about what you've heard. If not, totally fine too."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 45,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:25:43.818000Z",
        "message": "Well, I have heard that a lot of people are trusting more in ChatGPT. That's seems to be the go to, is what I've been hearing. I don't use them much. Like I said, I've only used it once. I use Copilot once. So yeah, Chad GPT seems to be very popular nowadays."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 46,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:06.258000Z",
        "message": "That's good to know. So you're hearing more buzz about ChatGPT as a trusted source even if you haven't made it your own go to yet. Thanks so much for sharing your experiences and insights with me today. Before we wrap up"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b562cf75328f4f908e0e0a55b",
        "index": 47,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:26:17.948000Z",
        "message": "Okay. Okay."
      }
