        "callId": "2430eb66d40c4ca5b5a527075",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:19.211000Z",
        "message": "Pretty much answer searching."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2430eb66d40c4ca5b5a527075",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:21.981000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Uh, for you, it's just about getting that answer. No major difference in trust or presentation. If you were telling a friend about Google and Gemini as answer engines, What words or feelings would you use to describe each 1? Just whatever pops into your head."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2430eb66d40c4ca5b5a527075",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:38.170000Z",
        "message": "That is very helpful."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2430eb66d40c4ca5b5a527075",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:43.061000Z",
        "message": "Both feel helpful to you. Thinking about trust, say, if you needed to share an answer for homework or with friends, does it matter which engine's answer you quote, or do you feel equally confident sharing info from Google or Gemini?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2430eb66d40c4ca5b5a527075",
