  {
    "id": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
    "responseId": "559c70dbd05e40c996143bd63",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:14.610000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:22.950000Z",
        "message": "Just fine. How about you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:25.520000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. I'm doing well too. Thanks for asking. Let's start with something every day. When you need to find an answer online, what's what's the very first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:37.070000Z",
        "message": "I pull up Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:40.090000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Google's your first stop. Can you can you walk me through what that usually looks like for you? For example, what happens from the moment you decide you need an answer?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:52.150000Z",
        "message": "I pull up Google type what I need in the search bar, and hit enter."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:58.120000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for the play by play. Once you type your question and hit enter, what do you typically do Are you looking at the top result, scrolling, checking for certain things? Tell me about what catches your eye first."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:12.220000Z",
        "message": "I scroll to see which 1 would answer my question the best, and then I click on it. And if that 1 doesn't answer my question, I go back and look at other ones."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:27.880000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Sounds like you scan for whichever result seems like it'll help most. And sometimes need to try a few before finding what you're after. What helps you decide which link looks promising? Are there signals or clues you look for while scrolling?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:44.080000Z",
        "message": "No. Just click on whatever 1 I think would be the best."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:49.700000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate the honesty. So it's more of a gut feeling and and quick scan. Let's zoom in on the last time you used Google for an answer. What was the question or or topic? And can you walk me through everything you did starting from what prompted you to search?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:05.990000Z",
        "message": "I was looking to find a Jiffy Lube near me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:12.930000Z",
        "message": "Perfect example. What happened from the moment you realized you needed to find a Jiffy Lube? Walk me through each step. What you typed, what you noticed on the results page, anything you clicked and how you decided which location to check out."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:27.980000Z",
        "message": "I typed in Jiffy Lube near me. And it pulled up the 1 nearest to me, told me how many miles away it was, and their hours."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:37.530000Z",
        "message": "Sounds pretty straightforward. Did you get your answer right away? Or did you have to click through, um, any links or check a map? Anything about that experience that felt especially helpful or annoying?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:48.670000Z",
        "message": "No. I got my answer right away."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:53.280000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like it was quick and easy. Out of curiosity, if Google hadn't given you that answer upfront, let's say the info wasn't there, what would you have tried next?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:06.540000Z",
        "message": "I would have probably typed in oil change stores near me. Because I needed an oil change."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:16.830000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. You'd broaden the search. To cover more options. When you do a search like that search like that for something local, do you ever use any other tools or apps besides Google? Or is it pretty much always Google for those kinds of things?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:29.600000Z",
        "message": "Always Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:33.370000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Google's your go to every time. Have you ever tried any of those newer AI answer engines? Like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini for questions whether about places, facts, or anything else? Or is your habit still mostly sticking with Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:49Z",
        "message": "It's always Google. The only time I use the AI chats is if I'm on a website and I need another answer, from that website."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:01.530000Z",
        "message": "That's really interesting. So you use AI chats mainly when you're already on a specific website and need help within that context. Can you tell me about a recent time that happened"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:10.420000Z",
        "message": "Correct."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:12.690000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for clearing that up. Thinking about those times when you do use an AI chat on a website, Can you describe a recent situation? What were you trying to find out and how did it go?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:26.410000Z",
        "message": "Yes. If I'm on Facebook and below the article that I'm reading, it has an option to click on the AI answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:38.980000Z",
        "message": "That's a great example. When you click to the AI answer option on Facebook, what kind of question did you ask? Or what were you curious about? How did the AI response compare to what you'd get by just searching Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:54.070000Z",
        "message": "Well, I didn't type the question. The question was already there. There were 4 or 5 different questions for me to clarify what I wanted to know in the article."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:07.250000Z",
        "message": "Got it. The AI suggested questions for you. Almost like conversation starters. You click on 1 of the suggested questions? If so, what happened next?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:15.080000Z",
        "message": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:15.839000Z",
        "message": "How did you feel about the answer it gave you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:18.579000Z",
        "message": "Yes. I did, and it pulled up what the answer was. 1 of them was for they were showing a recipe, and I wanted the ingredients for the recipe. And clicked on the option that said get the ingredients for this recipe, and it pulled it up and gave me all the ingredients."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:42.330000Z",
        "message": "That's handy. Um, when it pulled up the ingredients for you, did you feel confident that answer was accurate, or did you double check anywhere else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:49.780000Z",
        "message": "Yeah."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:50.899000Z",
        "message": "How did you decide?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:51.130000Z",
        "message": "No. I knew it was accurate."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:54.140000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for explaining that. So in that situation, you trusted the AI's answer. Without needing to cross check. If you think about using Google for"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:01.020000Z",
        "message": "Correct."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:03.380000Z",
        "message": "interesting. Thinking about Google versus AI, answers like the 1 on Facebook, what feels different if anything, about how you use them or what you expect from each?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:14.390000Z",
        "message": "I feel Google is more accurate."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:20.040000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful. Uh, when you think of Google being more accurate, what's behind that feeling for you? Is it reputation? Past experience, something about how answers are shown, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:32.809000Z",
        "message": "Reputation and past experience."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:36.210000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So a sense of trust that's built over time If you had to describe Google and those AI answer engines, like ChatGPT or the Facebook AI, as if they were people at a party Who do you think they'd each be and how would they act?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 43,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:52.110000Z",
        "message": "Google would be a professor, and AI would be the life of the party."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 44,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:01.460000Z",
        "message": "I love that analogy. So Google's more expert, maybe a bit formal. AI is more lively and engaging. If you were sharing an answer with a friend, say, recipe ingredients, which one's answer would you feel more comfortable quoting? And why?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 45,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:17.970000Z",
        "message": "AI because it's all right there. With Google, you have to go into each website to find the recipe that you're looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 46,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:28.390000Z",
        "message": "That's an interesting distinction. So AI makes it feel more direct and shareable. While Google sometimes means extra steps. Looking back over the past year, has anything changed in how you search for answers? Even just little habits? Or is it pretty much the same?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 47,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:43.060000Z",
        "message": "It's pretty much the same. I go to Google 99 percent of the time. The only time I use AI is if I'm on Facebook, and I don't wanna read the article. The AI will give me a like, cheat notes or, like, cliff notes of what the article's about."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 48,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:03.010000Z",
        "message": "That's super clear. So Google's your staple. But AI chats help. When you want quick summarized info, especially on Facebook. Has anyone you know friends, family, coworkers, ever suggested using anything besides Google for answers or talked about their own habits."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 49,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:21.040000Z",
        "message": "No."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 50,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:24.619000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate your honesty. That really helps paint a picture of your habits. And preferences. Last thing, from your experience so far, is there anything you wish these tools could do better or differently? Anything missing from Google or those AI answer engines that would make them more for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 51,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:42.399000Z",
        "message": "No. I like the way they are."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 52,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:20:46.860000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing all that. I really appreciate you taking the time and being so open. Before we wrap up, how did it feel having this kind of interview with an AI? And just so you know, whenever you're ready, you can end the call."
      },
      {
        "callId": "62c3d2f2f44e41ca8f36c8df8",
        "index": 53,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:04.050000Z",
        "message": "Feels like I'm talking to a real person."
      }
