      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:54.005000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:01.865000Z",
        "message": "My day is going well. Thank you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:05.085000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. I'll be asking about how you look up answers online. To start, when you need to find information or solve a quick question, what's typically the very first thing you do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:16.865000Z",
        "message": "I opened Gemini. And I asked the assistant"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:25.555000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So Gemini is where you usually start. You walk me through the last time you used Gemini? For a question, what did you need to find out, and what steps did you take from start to finish?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:37.165000Z",
        "message": "Cool. Yeah. I needed to find out a movie time. So I opened Gemini, and then I told them what theater I wanted and movie times for a certain movie."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:50.205000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for giving me that example. After you typed your question into Gemini, what did the answer look like? Was there anything about the response that felt particularly helpful or not so helpful?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:03.205000Z",
        "message": "The answers were really helpful because it gave me times and the movies I were playing and what movies had discounts."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:13.815000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like Gemini covered a lot for you in 1 go. Showed times, listed the movies, and even highlighted discounts. Was there any part of that experience found annoying or wished works differently? Or did it do the job perfectly for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:28.885000Z",
        "message": "I think it did a job perfectly for me. As it gave me all the information I needed."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:35.655000Z",
        "message": "Nice. So for that kind of task, finding movie times and deals, Gemini hit the mark for you. If Gemini wasn't available, what would you have done to get that?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:41.365000Z",
        "message": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:44.615000Z",
        "message": "Info? Can you walk me through your backup plan?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:48.024000Z",
        "message": "The backup plan would have been just to head over online and hit Google. For and ask for movie movie times my preferred movie theater."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:01.145000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense when you use Google for movie times, how does that experience compare with Gemini? Is there anything that feels different, better, or worse? Between the 2?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:12.145000Z",
        "message": "Which M and I give me detail detail detail answers and an array of different answers, whereas Google will be just giving me general not nonspecific details."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:27.415000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So Gemini gives you detailed, specific answers more tailored to what you ask. Google tends to be broader, less specific. When you get those more general results from Google, what do you usually do next? You find yourself clicking around, refining your search, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:45.995000Z",
        "message": "Yes. Usually, I have to refine my fines depending on the answer it gives me. And, you know, keep searching and clicking till I find what I want."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:58.435000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So with Google, it takes a few extra steps refining, clicking around while Gemini gets you there faster and more directly. How does"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:07.225000Z",
        "message": "Exactly."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:10.455000Z",
        "message": "thanks for spelling that out. Now outside of Gemini and Google, have you ever used other tools like ChatGPT or Perplexity to look up things? If so, what led you to try them, or how did those experiences feel different?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:24.785000Z",
        "message": "I wanted to try and see what was the difference which 1 would work better for me, and which 1 would be tailored for me better. I did try them for a couple of times, but at the end, I think Gemini was more specific to me, easier to use, and gave me more detail answers that I was always looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:47.315000Z",
        "message": "That's really clear. When you tried tools like ChatGPT or Perplexity, was there anything about their answers or experience that stood out Maybe something notably good, frustrating, or just different from Gemini?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:01.535000Z",
        "message": "It was it was it was detailed, but not as detailed as Gemini. It was a little bit broader. So for me, more comfortable comfortably using Gemini because it gave me this specific answers I wanted, and it's more easier to to use."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:23.275000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for breaking that down. So comfort and specificity seem big for you with Gemini. Thinking about these engines as personalities, if Gemini, Google, ChatGPT, and Perplexity were people at a party, let's see. How would you describe each of them? What kind of vibe or traits might they have?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:41.665000Z",
        "message": "Well, for me, Jim and I would be different that is know it all, you know, that has the details and knows all the places and it's right there for you. Where the other ones would be, yeah, good friends, and they know the stuff, but seminar would be different. Everybody goes through for any anything."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:05.995000Z",
        "message": "Love that image. A know it all who's always got the details at hand. You think about sharing an answer with friends or colleagues, whose answer do do you feel most confident quoting? Does Gemini feel most credible to pass on, or would you sometimes lean on Google, ChatGPT, or Perplexity instead?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:24.675000Z",
        "message": "Usually, just that with my level of comfort, I just go to Gemini. Gemini."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:31.875000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Looking back over the past year, do you feel your habits for looking things up have changed at all? Any moments or triggers that led you to choose Gemini as your default? Instead of Google or the others."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:48.525000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. You can webinar is a lot more intuitive. And easier. So whatever question I have, no matter how big or small, I know Gemini will have the answer for me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:03.025000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like intuition and reliability really matter for you. There anything you wish these answer engines could do that? They don't yet. Any unmet need or wish list feature even if it sounds out there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:16.085000Z",
        "message": "I would say suggestions little bit. Suggestions like, oh, well, what about this? Or, you know, something more you know, more like answers and, you know, suggestions. You know?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:34.154000Z",
        "message": "That's a good idea. More proactive suggestions. Maybe offering up related info or options you hadn't thought to ask. When you think about the future, would that kind of feature make you use Gemini even more or could it ever make you switch back to something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:48.415000Z",
        "message": "If they come up with a with that feature, it would be perfect, you know. It would make me use it even more than I use it now."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d97478d5124247d7a0ef8eec6",
        "index": 34,
