        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:13.626000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:21.426000Z",
        "message": "It's going well. Thank you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:24.296000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. Let's start with something simple. When you need answers online, whether it's for work, personal stuff, just curiosity. What's the very first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:34.816000Z",
        "message": "I go to Google search."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:38.836000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Google's your go to? Take me through your typical process. Say you have a question or need to look something up. What's the step by step from the moment the thought pops into your head?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:50.445000Z",
        "message": "Well, I accessed the Google app on my phone. I generally use my phone, period. And then I cycle I me. I simply type in what I'm looking for. Either a word or a sentence. I'm not sure what you're needing."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:01.965000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for walk that's perfect. Thanks. You mostly use your phone, um, open the Google app, and type in your question, whether it's a single word"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:13.165000Z",
        "message": "Yeah."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:14.436000Z",
        "message": "or a full sentence. Thinking back to the last time you did this,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:16.246000Z",
        "message": "Yeah."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:18.486000Z",
        "message": "what were you looking up? And after you typed it in, what did you do next?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:23.596000Z",
        "message": "I actually was looking up information about Al Pacino. As I've I'm currently listening to his memoir. So I I was wondering how old he was. So I typed in how old is Al Pacino. And I got a response. Oh my goodness. There's a back row over here."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:38.456000Z",
        "message": "Nice. That's a great exam. Listening to Al Pacino's memoir sounds pretty interesting, So you typed in how old is Al Pacino? And Google served up an answer. Did you just read the snippet or did you tap into any of the links or scroll further? Tell me more about what you did after seeing the initial result."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:01.316000Z",
        "message": "I just read the snippet."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:06.186000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. And when you read that snippet, how did it feel Did you feel totally confident in the answer? Or did you ever have the urge to double check elsewhere?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:16.276000Z",
        "message": "No. I was totally confident in the answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:22.016000Z",
        "message": "Sounds straightforward. For quick facts like that, Google seems to to nail it for you. Is that pretty typical? Do you usually stop you get that first answer? Or are there times you dig deeper or use other tools?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:35.156000Z",
        "message": "There are times I dig deeper. I usually start with Google, And sometimes when they give me the answer, I'll access Wikipedia. Through through Google, through the search."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:48.656000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful. So if you feel like you need a bit more detail, you'll tap into Wikipedia. But you get there starting from Google. Can you think of a recent time when just reading the snippet wasn't enough? What made you want to click through or find more information?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:07.256000Z",
        "message": "Oh, actually, it was yesterday. I was thinking I was looking at an old actor and I wanted to know what their cause of death was. But I can't remember who it was now, but I did I with Google, and then I went through Wikipedia to read more about their life and their death. Oh, William Holden."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:29.716000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So with William Holden, the quick answer wasn't quite enough. And you wanted more detail. When you got to Wikipedia, what felt different?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:35.406000Z",
        "message": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:37.956000Z",
        "message": "Compared to just sticking with the snippet from Google? Was it more about depth trust, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:44.466000Z",
        "message": "It was more about death. It was just there was just more detailed and information about what happened."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:51.616000Z",
        "message": "Makes total sense. The snippet gave the basics, but Wikipedia filled in the context and story. When you're looking for answers that aren't just a quick fact, do you ever turn to other tools besides Google and Wikipedia? For example, things like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or any AI driven answer engines? Or do you pretty much stick with Google and Wikipedia?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:11.486000Z",
        "message": "I stick with Google and Wikipedia."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:16.786000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for clarifying. When you hear about tools like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini, what comes to mind? Any gut feeling, curiosity, or words that pop up?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:28.226000Z",
        "message": "Well, I have noticed that there's a lot of of, like, fake pictures that are I guess they're created by AI. I'm not sure if that's what you're referring to or not. So I don't really trust it, I guess, I should say."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:46.125000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful. So when you think of AI tools, trust is a bit of a concern, especially with things like fake images. Has that made you less interested in using those tools for getting answers to questions compared to your usual Google searches?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:00.786000Z",
        "message": "Yes. It has."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:03.106000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Sticking with what feels trustworthy is important. You think about Google and Wikipedia, what words or feelings would you use to describe them? How do they how do they feel compared to the newer AI tools you've mentioned?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:17.666000Z",
        "message": "I think they are more trustworthy to me. If I read something on Wikipedia, I believe it. I I'm not doubtful at all about the information and with Google as well."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:31.076000Z",
        "message": "That's really clear. Trust and belief in the info stand out for both. About how you've used these tools over the past year, would you say your habits have changed at all? Or do you pretty much use Google and Wikipedia like you always have?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:44.196000Z",
        "message": "I use it like I always have."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:49.786000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing. Uh, last question. When you're talking with friends or family, do conversations ever come up about which tool is best for looking up info? For instance, does anyone recommend certain engines or talk about AI tools? Or is it just sort of a given that Google and Wikipedia are the way to go?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "fed3a0de06f04bd399ceb50b1",
        "index": 35,
