  {
    "id": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
    "responseId": "9d6cc9afeff14c89958859b01",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:15.411000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:23.441000Z",
        "message": "Great. That's right."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:30.061000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. Let's start with something simple. When you need answers online, maybe you're curious about something or trying to solve a problem. What's the first thing you usually"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:35.711000Z",
        "message": "Yeah."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:39.711000Z",
        "message": "do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:42.121000Z",
        "message": "Yo. Hey, Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:45.351000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Sounds like Google's your usual starting point. Can you walk me through what that looks like? For example, last time you needed an answer online, what did you do step by step?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:57.951000Z",
        "message": "Hear you now. Said, hey, Google. And then waited for them to give me possible solutions, then picked that solution. It took me to that website, site."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:10:13.001000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for describing that process. So after saying, hey, Google. You checked out the possible solutions. Chose 1, and followed the link to a website. Thinking about that experience, what part of using Google felt the most helpful to you? And was there anything that felt annoying or frustrating during those steps?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:10:31.871000Z",
        "message": "When it could not understand my words and kept taking me to incorrect avenues, for my answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:10:40.850000Z",
        "message": "That sounds frustrating when it misunderstands and sends you somewhere off base. Can you tell me more about a specific time that that happened? What were you trying to find out, and how did Google misinterpret your question?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:10:54.421000Z",
        "message": "Trying to go to a website or a specific store, Actually, it was Dollar General. And trying to find out what time they closed, and it continuously gave me incorrect information."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:10.851000Z",
        "message": "Really clear example. Thank you. So you were asking about Dollar General's closing time. But Google kept giving you information that wasn't accurate. What did you end up doing to get the correct answer? Did you try rephrasing, use another engine, check a different site, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:28.180000Z",
        "message": "Something else."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:30.790000Z",
        "message": "Tell me more about that. What did you do instead to finally get the closing time you needed?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:36.501000Z",
        "message": "Went on to Safari and typed it in to find it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:41.571000Z",
        "message": "Interesting switch. So you use Safari and, uh, typed your question in there. When you did that, was the experience different from what you had with your Google? What made it work better or not for for for for you that time?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:55.151000Z",
        "message": "I found my answer. It understood me with my fingers, not my voice."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:02.561000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Sounds like typing worked better than voice in that moment. When you're using your fingers instead of your voice, do you usually feel like you get more accurate or satisfying answers? Or does it depend on what you're looking for?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:16.421000Z",
        "message": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:18.181000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for that. Thinking about these different ways you look for answers, voice it with Google, typing with Safari, Do you ever use other tools like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Google's AI summaries? Or do you mostly stick with Google and Safari?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:33.951000Z",
        "message": "Google and Safari."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:36.901000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So mostly Google and Safari. If you compare those 2, is there 1 you trust more when when you really need the the right answer? What makes you lean toward 1 over the other in those moments?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:49.661000Z",
        "message": "Safari normally because I don't have the time or patient. To keep repeating myself."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:58.410000Z",
        "message": "That's really clear. So Safari wins out when you need a quick reliable answer, especially because you don't have to keep repeating yourself. When you do use Google, what kinds of questions or situations make you reach for it instead of typing in Safari?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:15.650000Z",
        "message": "Repeat."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:18.121000Z",
        "message": "Sure thing. When you decide to use Google, what types of questions or situations make you choose it instead of typing your query? Into Safari."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:29.551000Z",
        "message": "If I try it once or twice and it understands my voice, and can respond quickly, then I will stick with Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:41.940000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. So if Google catches your voice clearly and gives a fast response, you use it. If it doesn't work after trying a couple times, you switch to typing. When you do get"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:52.291000Z",
        "message": "Correct."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:54.681000Z",
        "message": "thanks for clearing that up. Thinking about how these tools feel to you, if Google and Safari were people at a party, how would you describe each of them? What kind of personality or or vibe would they have?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:10.111000Z",
        "message": "Google would be the socialite that only half takes the time to listen to what I'm saying. And is too busy socializing with everybody else to really pay attention. Safari knows my heart. It knows my soul. It knows my very being."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:26.961000Z",
        "message": "Wow. I love those descriptions. So Google's kind of distracted and only half listening. While Safari feels deeply in tune with what you really need. Does that sense of being understood by Safari"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:36.211000Z",
        "message": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:38.370000Z",
        "message": "you more likely to share answers from it with friends or family, or do you ever quote Google when you help someone else out?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:46.591000Z",
        "message": "I do both."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:50.881000Z",
        "message": "Nice. When you share an answer that you found using Safari or Google, do people ever ask where you got it? And if so, do you feel more confident? Naming 1 source over the other?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:03.710000Z",
        "message": "Always Usually, Safari."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:10.690000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So you you usually mention Safari when you share an answer. What makes Safari feel more credible or worth quoting to others compared to Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:20.741000Z",
        "message": "Normally, my friends are there when I'm trying to find something out. And start laughing because Google don't understand me. I go to Safari, and I give them what we're looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:34.861000Z",
        "message": "That paints a clear picture. So it sounds like your friends see you struggling with Google. Then you switch to Safari, and you all get the answer you need. Sometimes with a laugh. Does having their reactions nearby influence which engine you use? Or is it mostly about how quickly you can get to the real answer?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:54.661000Z",
        "message": "How quickly?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:58.731000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. So speed matters most. Just curious looking back over the past year, has anything changed about how you search for answers online? Or is your process and choice of tools pretty much the same as it's always been?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 43,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:12.691000Z",
        "message": "Switched phones from Apple to to Android and it seems like I would have more clear understanding and more relatable conversation with Suri. Than what I have with Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 44,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:36.341000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. Switching from Apple to Android changed your experience. It sounds like you found Siri more understanding and relatable than Google. Can you tell me about something you liked about using Siri? That you don't get from Google now?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 45,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:52.220000Z",
        "message": "I didn't have to repeat myself."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 46,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:56.271000Z",
        "message": "Makes total sound."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 47,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:56.481000Z",
        "message": "And if I did, was not near as much."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 48,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:01.521000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to know. So with Siri, repeating yourself was rare. And with Google, it happens a lot more. If you could change 1 thing about Google to make it more like Siri, what would you wish for?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 49,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:15.381000Z",
        "message": "They could program it to understand at the first attempt. Rather than being misdirected by what you're saying and going somewhere that you're not even talking about. Or having to repeat yourself multiple times and still not receiving an answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 50,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:36.940000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for that. So you'd want Google to catch what you you say on the first try and take you straight to the right answer, not somewhere random. Sounds like accuracy and responsiveness matter a lot. In moments when you need help. Before we wrap up, is there anything else you wish? Search engines or answer engines could do to make your life easier? Something you haven't mentioned yet?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 51,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:58.121000Z",
        "message": "No. Not necessarily."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 52,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:02.791000Z",
        "message": "Great. Thanks for sharing your stories and thoughts with me. I really appreciate how honest and clear you've been. Before we end, any feedback on this AI interview experience? How did it feel talking with me today? And just so you know, you're free to end the call whenever you'd like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 53,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:20.831000Z",
        "message": "I feel great my children are present, and I show them how smart their mother is by answering a survey and making money."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ac42bdb5eb65481baf30ec4fb",
        "index": 54,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:31.190000Z",
        "message": "That's awesome. And what a fun way to show your kids your smarts. Again for taking the time to share your experiences. You can end the call now. Whenever you're ready."
      }
