        "callId": "4c293f44d4774b8d817a7cedf",
        "index": 44,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:33.074000Z",
        "message": "So Google stood out for speed, especially for getting quick introductions to something. Can you remember how the answers you got from Google felt compared to what you might get from glucocortone? Was there anything that made it noticeably different? For example, how thorough the response was, the sources, or the way info was presented?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "4c293f44d4774b8d817a7cedf",
        "index": 45,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:53.844000Z",
        "message": "The response was more trustworthy."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4c293f44d4774b8d817a7cedf",
        "index": 46,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:18:58.694000Z",
        "message": "That's useful to know. So Google's response felt more trustworthy to you. Can you think of a moment when you wanted to share an answer you found with someone else maybe a friend or coworker, engine's answer felt most credible to quote or pass along, and why?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "4c293f44d4774b8d817a7cedf",
        "index": 47,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:16.684000Z",
        "message": "Good girl felt the most trustworthy."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4c293f44d4774b8d817a7cedf",
        "index": 48,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:23.164000Z",
        "message": "So Google felt the most trustworthy when sharing answers with others. What words or feelings come to mind when you think about Google answers versus ones from glucocortone or other engines. Any specific associations or vibes that stick out to you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "4c293f44d4774b8d817a7cedf",
        "index": 49,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:40.064000Z",
        "message": "Transparent information."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4c293f44d4774b8d817a7cedf",
        "index": 50,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:19:43.204000Z",
        "message": "You associate Google with transparent information. That's interesting. When when you're deciding which tool to use, for a search, does transparency play a big role for you? Or are there other things that sway you in the moment?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "4c293f44d4774b8d817a7cedf",
        "index": 51,
