        "index": 58,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:08.394000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. You feel tempted to try new things sometimes. If an answer engine wanted to win you over and become your go to, what's 1 thing it could offer that would truly make you switch? Or even just give it a serious try?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "4c293f44d4774b8d817a7cedf",
        "index": 59,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:22.604000Z",
        "message": "Offer more."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4c293f44d4774b8d817a7cedf",
        "index": 60,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:21:26.314000Z",
        "message": "So if an engine could offer more, maybe features, info, support, or something extra, you'd give it a try. What's on the 1 example of more that would actually make the difference for you? Could be faster results, deeper info, better guidance, or anything else that comes to mind. You'd switch for deeper information. What does deeper look like to you when you're searching? Is it more details, expert insight, explanations, or something else entirely?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "4c293f44d4774b8d817a7cedf",
        "index": 61,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:22:02.444000Z",
        "message": "Expert information."
      },
      {
        "callId": "4c293f44d4774b8d817a7cedf",
