        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:26.525000Z",
        "message": "Fantastic description. So to recap, GPT would be the sociable 1 mingling with everyone. Google would be the nerd, the go to for a specific info. In Gemini, more like a casual acquaintance. Friendly, but not the first person you'd seek out. What words come to mind when you think of each engine? Like, the first few things you'd associate with Google answers, GPT, and Gemini."
