        "index": 46,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:34.596000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for putting that into words. Google feels cluttered or maybe a bit sterile GPT feels convenient. Gemini is kind of just a backup choice. When you share an answer with someone like, sending a link or copying a response, which engine's answer, do you feel most comfortable quoting or passing along? Why?"
