        "index": 49,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:11.886000Z",
        "message": "Probably Google because, culturally, everyone's kinda accepted Google as, uh, the number 1 source for information. Some people still have you know, refrain from AI, so I think a lot of people don't trust AI. Compared to Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e88fd710633c4d479aa8d1139",
        "index": 50,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:31.366000Z",
        "message": "That's a really insightful point. Google feels like the accepted authority for most people while some folks are still hesitant about trusting AI Answers. Looking back over the past year, have you noticed any changes in your own habits, like do you search differently now than you did a year ago?"
      },
