        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:52.005000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So it helps you really grasp the answer. Almost like it's talking directly to you. Switching gears bit. If you had to line up Google and ChatGPT from most helpful to least, which would be first for you and why?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "98cfee3f3e6949e2a599fd062",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:04.205000Z",
        "message": "Oh, I feel like Chatbet too because it goes in-depth. Better than Google, and it show you step by step to show you a picture images. You can send me pictures, and they explain it out to you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "98cfee3f3e6949e2a599fd062",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:21.405000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So ChatGPT or ChatBet as you called it, takes the top spot for you because it gives deeper explanations, step by step breakdowns. And can show images right when you need them, which Google doesn't always do. That that's that's helpful. If you think about how you trust each 1, which 1 feels more reliable or or official, when you share an answer with someone else? Why do you think that is?"
      },
