        "callId": "fc4076e3f5eb40f79f4a86a02",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:28.997000Z",
        "message": "They will be, um, down to earth. But also knowledgeable and can have a deep conversation. About things that's going on in the world because that's also what I like to use those platforms for to see things about conspiracies and stuff like that, see what they will say compared to, like, you know, when I do my own research, I try to compare and contrast. So, yeah, down to earth, knowledgeable type of person at a party."
      },
      {
        "callId": "fc4076e3f5eb40f79f4a86a02",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:00.697000Z",
        "message": "That's a cool way to see it. Each 1 is down to earth and able to dig into deep, thoughtful conversations. Is there any difference in trust or credibility you feel when you get answers from say, Google versus ChatGPT or Perplexity. If you were to share an answer with someone else, does it matter which engine it comes from?"
