    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:26.789000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:34.669000Z",
        "message": "It's going well. Thank you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:37.939000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. Let's start simple. When you need an answer online, what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:45.649000Z",
        "message": "Chat GPT or DeepSeek?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:49.089000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. What tends to make you reach for ChatGPT or DeepSeek first? Can you walk me through how you decide which 1 to use for a question?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:07:00.609000Z",
        "message": "ChatGPT has limits per day. So I'm more selective what I use ChatGPT for. Whereas DeepSeek is unlimited. So I would usually decide between the 2 the more important stuff goes to ChatGPT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:07:19.999000Z",
        "message": "That's really clear. Can you describe the last time you used ChatGPT for something important? What did you need, and how did the experience play out step by step?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:07:31.459000Z",
        "message": "I uploaded my blood results from the lab and asked Chet GPT to give me a layman's terms overview of my blood sample."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:07:48.189000Z",
        "message": "That's a great example. So starting from the moment you got your lab results, can you tell me all the steps you went through? How you prepared your question, uploaded the results, and interacted with ChatGPT along the way."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:08:01.709000Z",
        "message": "I uploaded a PDF after looking through the guide that comes with the PDF that tells you what normal ranges are and then frames my question to chat TPT how concerned I should be about the ones that were out of range."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:08:21.059000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for walking me through that. When you got ChatGPT's response, what felt most helpful about its answer And was there anything about the experience that felt frustrating or made you second guess its advice?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:08:35.339000Z",
        "message": "I take chat GPT's information as a grain of salt. It's not an end all answer. Nor are they med a medical professional. But it gave me a baseline to approach my actual doctor with questions when I go to see them."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:08:55.609000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. So it sounds like it's a starting point for you. But not the final call. What's it about ChatGPT's answer or style that makes you trusted enough for that baseline? But still wanna double check with your doctor?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:10.369000Z",
        "message": "Well, SatTP, he's not a doctor. So I definitely wanna talk to my doctor, but it helps me get in the direction of what to pay attention to."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:24.819000Z",
        "message": "That totally tracks. When you use DeepSeek instead, how does the experience compare? For example, if you'd uploaded your blood results there, what would you expect to be different, if anything?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:37.099000Z",
        "message": "I've noticed that DeepSeek has a little bit of a bias. The more I interact with it, I think its answers sometimes tend to be catered towards what I want to hear its programming is focused on a pleasant user experience over unbiased information in my experience."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:10:03.869000Z",
        "message": "Interesting observation. Can you recall a specific time when DeepSeek's answer felt like it was telling you what you what you wanted to hear rather than giving a more neutral or critical answer. What happened in that moment?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:10:18.939000Z",
        "message": "I asked DeepSeek to proofread some technical writing I was working on and I noticed that it was complementing my work more than being a critic So I asked the model to remember that their role in this interaction is to be a critical editor rather than a cheerleader. And it changed its answer to something a little bit more critical."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:10:59.078000Z",
        "message": "That's a cool workaround. Actually, resetting its role in the conversation. How did it feel when it switched into that more critical mode? Did that make you trust DeepSeek's answers more, or did you still feel cautious?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:12.839000Z",
        "message": "It's more about understanding how the model actually is programmed to work. If you don't prompt it in the right way, it's only going to be as good as the instructions that give it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:25.689000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So giving clear direct instructions is key. Otherwise, you might just get a pleasant answer, not a useful 1. Thinking about these engines overall. Which do you feel gives the most useful answers for you most often? And what makes you say that?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:40.839000Z",
        "message": "I've done more training with the DeepSeek model than I have with ChatGPT. Overall, I've learned that specificity is key. And creating rules, boundaries, and guidelines will help the model achieve the results you want."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:00.019000Z",
        "message": "Really interesting. So the more you train DeepSeek, giving it rules and guidelines, the more useful it becomes for you. Can you tell me about a time when you set up those boundaries for DeepSeek and saw a clear difference in the quality of the answer you got?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:17.109000Z",
        "message": "Like in the example before where it was more of a cheerleader than an editor. It started giving me more constructive feedback rather than compliments."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:30.529000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Sounds like you shifted the experience. Just by tightening your instructions. Thinking about this, does that make you prefer DeepSeek for tasks where you want deeper feedback or or critique? Or do you still switch it between the 2 engines? For certain kinds of questions?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:45.729000Z",
        "message": "I tend to lean towards DeepSeek because it's unlimited, which gives me more opportunities to fine tailor my prompting strategies."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:55.479000Z",
        "message": "That's practical. The unlimited aspect gives you room to experiment. In situations where you need a quick factual answer versus deep feedback do you still reach for deep seek first or do you ever try something else, like, Google or ChatGPT? Can you walk me through how you pick for that? Kind of quick task?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:14.488000Z",
        "message": "There's so many AI programs. Right? Now that I really am just trying to stick with small handful, which is just DeepSeek and ChatGPT. Also, Gemini has gotten some reviews that I'm not particularly keen on."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:33.119000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like you're intentionally limiting the tools you use. What prompted you to stick with just DeepSeek and ChatGPT instead of bouncing between more options? Was there a specific moment or experience that led to this just these 2 approach?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:49.319000Z",
        "message": "Not particularly. There's, like I said, too there's too many programs out there. You can get lost really fast with all the different types of GPTs that are out there. I'm trying to get good at 1 or 2 of them and then branch out. Some of the other ones."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:08.759000Z",
        "message": "That makes a lot of sense. Focusing on mastering a few before exploring more. Stepping back for a second, if you lined up DeepSeek, ChatGPT, and Gemini, and imagined each 1 as a person at a party, how would you describe their personalities or the vibe each 1 gives off?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:27.389000Z",
        "message": "I think Gemini would be a social justice warrior that virtue signals ChatGPT would be kind of a nerdy guy who's full of good information. And DeepSeek would be the fun bubbly, but seriously smart 1 at the party."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:52.399000Z",
        "message": "Love those descriptions. When you think about quoting information or or sharing answers with someone else, like a friend, coworker, or even your doctor, engine's answer would you feel most comfortable sharing? What gives you that sense of confidence or not?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:09.389000Z",
        "message": "Probably DeepSeek because I've trained it so much."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:15.149000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. You have a sort of working relationship with Deep Seek now. When you say you've trained it, what does that process actually look like on your end? What do you do to get it giving the answers you want?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:27.589000Z",
        "message": "I have established some small rules."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:32.989000Z",
        "message": "Can you share an example of those those small rules you've set up for DeepSeek? How do you communicate them? And what's the biggest impact you've noticed from doing this?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:42.569000Z",
        "message": "I'll give you an example. I'm trying to get better with grammar. So I made a rule with DeepSeek that when I ask it a question, the first thing that it does is give me a 1 sentence suggestion on how to improve my grammar following with the response."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:01.339000Z",
        "message": "That's a clever strategy since setting that grammar rule, how has your experience with DeepSeek's answers changed? Do you find yourself actually adopting its suggestions? Or is it more just an extra layer for you to consider?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:15.159000Z",
        "message": "Extra layer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:17.639000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Looking back, say, over the last year, has anything changed in how often or when you reach for DeepSeek ChatGPT? Any moments that stand out where you pick them over something like Google first,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:30.789000Z",
        "message": "No."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:34.059000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate your honesty. We wrap up, is there anything you wish these engines could do that they can't yet? Any features or abilities that would make you switch your main tool? Or rethink what you use most?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 43,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:46.669000Z",
        "message": "It'd be nice if I could speak to it like I do with Siri where I can just say out loud, hey. DeepSeek. What do you think about this? And it would respond to me like you are right now."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 44,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:01.999000Z",
        "message": "That's a really clear wish. Having that kind of voice interaction would make it feel even more natural. And flexible for you. Thanks for talking through all this with me. Before we end, how did this AI interview experience feel for you compared to a regular survey or or or any other feedback you've given. And and whenever you're ready, you can end the call."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 45,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:22.389000Z",
        "message": "I like this 1 better than the other surveys I've taken."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b6c8f290d0034e3a9f9a0b23a",
        "index": 46,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:27.939000Z",
        "message": "I'm glad to hear that. Thanks for sharing your experiences and perspectives. It was great. Chatting with you. You're all set. So feel free to end the call whenever you'd like."
      }
    ],
