  {
    "id": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
    "responseId": "003c9e573cfa4985b3a02e51c",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:48.602000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:56.402000Z",
        "message": "It's fine. Thank you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:58.832000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear that. Let's jump in. When you need to find an answer online, what's the very first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:06.022000Z",
        "message": "I usually Google it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:10.511000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Walk me through a typical moment. Maybe the last time you did this. What was the question you had, and what steps did you take to look it up?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:19.292000Z",
        "message": "I needed to find the hours of my local library so I put Westmont Public Library into the toolbar, hit click, and found the website, then found the hours."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:36.902000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Uh, thinking about that experience, there anything about using Google that felt especially helpful or maybe a bit annoying?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:47.282000Z",
        "message": "No. It's a pretty experience of looking for something."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:53.032000Z",
        "message": "Seems like it just works for you. Straightforward. For that type of quick info, is Google always your go to? Do you sometimes reach for other tools, like ChatGPT or any AI powered answer engines?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:07:05.522000Z",
        "message": "Absolutely. I love chat GPT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:07:09.552000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. Tell me a story about the last time you used ChatGPT instead of Google. What did you need, and how did you use it from start to finish?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:07:18.972000Z",
        "message": "It would be a very long conversation, but used it this morning for a work project. I had to synthesize and organize and edit information from many different documents into just a few bullet points. And I spent quite a while working on a good prompt for ChatGPT, uploaded all of the documents, and asked me to help asked it to help me get this information together."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:07:57.532000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate you walking through that. Thinking about that experience, what stood out to you as especially helpful when using ChatGPT for your project? Any part of it that felt frustrating?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:08:11.832000Z",
        "message": "Well, yeah, it can be frustrating because sometimes it it offers to do something, and you ask it to, and it doesn't actually do that thing. But I'm still figuring out how to use ChatGPT the best that I can. So understand that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:08:32.942000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. It sounds like you're still learning how to get the most from it. When it doesn't follow through as"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:08:38.352000Z",
        "message": "Correct."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:08:40.932000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for confirming. When you're choosing between, uh, Google and Chat GPT, what drives your choice? Is it about the type of task, how much time you have, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:08:51.892000Z",
        "message": "Well, it's usually the complexity of the task and what I'm asking it to do. Google a Google search could never have done what I was asking chat GPT to do this morning. It was much more complex."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:10.952000Z",
        "message": "That's clear. So for simple fact based questions, you reach for Google. But when you need to synthesize, organize, or create, you lean on ChatGPT. Is that about right?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:23.272000Z",
        "message": "Yeah."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:26.561000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for clarifying. Thinking about both tools, Google and ChatGPT, how would you describe what each is really good at and where each 1 falls short for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:39.552000Z",
        "message": "Google is fair is good for finding fast facts or fast information, particularly when you then want to click through to the website or the link or whatever that is. Chat GPT is better for things that involve reflection, analysis, finding information from different sources, and trying to give me objective answers."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:10:16.762000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful. When you use ChatGPT, do you ever find yourself wanting to check its answers elsewhere? To make sure they're accurate or trustworthy? If so, how do you usually go about that?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:10:25.742000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. Can do that because usually a link is involved with with where they found a specific fact. So I don't often double check. Something would have to be very strange me to need to go double check because I see where they get the information from. And I trust where they got the information."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:10:50.642000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So seeing where the information comes from, and having those those links plays a big role in your trust. Out of curiosity, when it comes to quoting or or sharing an answer with someone else, which engine's response do you feel most comfortable passing along? And what makes you feel that way?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:09.022000Z",
        "message": "Well, I would use them in 2 different ways. If I just needed to know when the library closed, I would just use Google, and I would be confident that I had the right information and pass along. If, again, I was doing something more analytic based or something much more technical or advanced, I would use chat GPT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:33.612000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So you match the engine to the job. Quick facts from Google, deeper, or more complex info from ChatGPT. Thinking about brand or personality, if Google and ChatGPT were people at a party, how would you how do you describe each of them? How do they act or come across?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:50.982000Z",
        "message": "Google is more of the cheerleader. And ChatGPT is more of the brilliant studious nerd who ends up becoming Bill Gates."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:03.832000Z",
        "message": "I like those descriptions. What words or feelings come to mind when you think about each 1? Google's cheerleader vibe versus ChatGPT's studious nerd?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:15.652000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. I don't understand what you're asking me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:21.222000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for being honest. Me try this. Different way. When you think about Google, does anything specific come to mind, like trust, speed, reliability, or maybe something else? And then for ChatGPT, are there certain feelings curiosity, excitement, or caution that pop up for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:42.712000Z",
        "message": "Trust all of the reliability and so on work for both Google and Chat GPT. They actually have many of the same they share many of the same traits even though, essentially, they're entirely different animals. Nobody should ever use chat GPT the way they would use a a search engine like Google. It they're just not making use of that. I definitely trust but verify information that I get from chat GPT. An example would be I have started to use it for shopping recommendations. I'm interested in skincare. So I asked so the other day, I asked her to find a skin serum for mature skin that was budget friendly and could be purchased on Amazon. And it gave me 5 or 6 different options."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:46.102000Z",
        "message": "That's a great example."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:46.682000Z",
        "message": "A lot of Yeah. Pros and cons, and I purchased something directly based upon that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:13:54.092000Z",
        "message": "Really interesting. You went from a recommendation straight to purchase."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:00.491000Z",
        "message": "Yeah."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:00.502000Z",
        "message": "When Chattypakti suggested those serums, what made you feel confident enough to buy? Was it how it described the options? Way it organized the info, or or maybe something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:10.271000Z",
        "message": "All of the above there, but also this is a field that I'm familiar with. So I, for the most part, knew the brand names and probably had I had some kind of relationship with these brands or knew of them beforehand. So what I did do then was to click on the link that chat gave me and went directly to Amazon look to kind of double check what I thought I wanted to do, and then I purchased it myself directly on Amazon."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:45.722000Z",
        "message": "Very clear. So your own knowledge, the recognizable brands, plus the links to double check on Amazon, all works together as trust signals. Did you share any of those"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:54.402000Z",
        "message": "Yeah."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:14:59.332000Z",
        "message": "Great. 1 last thing. Since you started using ChatGPT and similar tools, has anything shifted in your habits compared to a year ago? Any moments where you reached for something besides Google first or found yourself relying on AI answers more often?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:15.832000Z",
        "message": "All of the above. I actually now am thinking more in how to structure prompts to get the information I want out of ChatGPT. Because"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:34.292000Z",
        "message": "At the notable shift, moving toward thinking in prompts first. Was there a moment or"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 43,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:37.582000Z",
        "message": "yeah."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 44,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:39.451000Z",
        "message": "specific reason that nudged you into relying on ChatGPT more, or did it just happen gradually as you discovered what it could do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 45,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:15:48.172000Z",
        "message": "Both. It happened gradually because I played around with it. Then I also listened to some free webinars about what it could do, and I kind of had a quantum shift. In my thinking as to what it could do for me both personally and in my business life. So I'm devoting a fair amount of time right now to figuring out how to master it for my personal needs and my business needs."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 46,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:22.142000Z",
        "message": "Love hearing you had that quantum shift. Sounds like a big moment. As you're learning to master it, are there features or things you wish ChatGPT or any answer engine could do? But don't yet. Maybe anything that would make it even more useful or trustworthy for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 47,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:37.292000Z",
        "message": "Well, yeah, 1, I'd like it to be able to include pictures. It would be very nice."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 48,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:43.292000Z",
        "message": "That's a good wish list item."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 49,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:16:43.432000Z",
        "message": "Another would be yeah. I I would like that. The other is very honestly, I would like it to be able to have access to 1 of my external drives that have that has all of my writings and things on it that it could kind of learn how I write rather than me uploading and giving links to all of the different things that I've done over the past. I'd rather that be a more automatic process."
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 50,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:15.782000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. So seamless access to your materials so it could learn your style without all that manual uploading, plus being able to handle pictures. Those are both pretty powerful unmet needs. That's all for me. Thanks again for sharing your stories and thoughtful answers. Before we wrap, anything else you want to add about your experience with these AI tools or with this interview itself? When you're ready, you're free to"
      },
      {
        "callId": "871663fa0a2145aca6894cced",
        "index": 51,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:17:40.011000Z",
        "message": "Nope. I will."
      }
