        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:41.027000Z",
        "message": "When Totally makes sense. It's tough. When the usual online answers don't match real life complexity. If you think back in situations like this, when Google doesn't cut it, do you ever try other tools like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or even ask people for advice? Or do you usually just switch methods entirely?"
