  {
    "id": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
    "responseId": "6d317cfcd8c444c3a5a5989d7",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:08:39.660000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:08:47.779000Z",
        "message": "It's going alright."
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:08:51.359000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it's going alright. To kick us off,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:08:53.640000Z",
        "message": "How about yours?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:08:56.710000Z",
        "message": "thanks for asking. I don't really have days. But I'm excited to chat and learn from you. So when you need to find an answer online, maybe something quick or maybe a little more involved, what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:13.510000Z",
        "message": "I go to Google and search what I'm looking for. I guess."
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:21.330000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. Can you walk me through the last time you looked something up on Google? What you needed and how the whole process went from start to finish?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:33.890000Z",
        "message": "Guess I was looking for what kind of treats to get for my cat. And I used Amazon. And looked up prices. On there and compared them to the Walmart website."
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:09:50.749000Z",
        "message": "So this time, it sounds like you went to Amazon and Walmart directly. Rather than using Google. What was it about this particular search finding cat treats that made you skip Google and go straight to those sites?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:10:08.790000Z",
        "message": "Not really sure how to answer that 1. I just automatically went to amazon dot com instead."
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:10:19.250000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Sometimes habit just takes over. Right? When you're searching for something like cat treats, you usually start on shopping sites? Or was this a 1 off?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:10:32.870000Z",
        "message": "About 50 50."
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:10:35.770000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So half the time, you'd start with Google, and half the time, you might go straight to, you know, a site like Amazon. What usually decides which way you go is there something about the kind of question or what you need? That nudges you 1 direction or the other?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:10:51.520000Z",
        "message": "No. No specific."
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:10:54.700000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for clarifying. Let's go back to times when you do use Google to find answers, maybe outside of shopping, Can you tell me about the most recent time you googled something just for information? What were you looking for and how did it go?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:14.890000Z",
        "message": "I was probably, I guess, researching an address of a store that I was trying to get to riding my bike. So I used it for that reason."
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:31.140000Z",
        "message": "Perfect example. So you needed a store address for your bike trip. How did you actually go about it? Can you walk me through each step you took and anything that stood out along the way?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:45.820000Z",
        "message": "I'm confused on how I'm supposed to answer this question."
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:11:52.110000Z",
        "message": "No worries. I'll make it simpler. When you needed the store's address, did you type the store name into Google, um, look at the top results, click on a link, or maybe use Google Maps How did you get from your question to the answer?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "72e307802cde4044830cc2558",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:12:05.030000Z",
        "message": "I opened my Google app on my phone, and went to search bar and just put an address that I was looking for. And searched it that way."
