  {
    "id": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
    "responseId": "28259fb4dc11483e98aecd08b",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:43.092000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:50.782000Z",
        "message": "It's going really well."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:55.032000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. To get us started, when you need an answer to something online, maybe a quick fact or a how to, what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:58:05.102000Z",
        "message": "The first thing I usually do is ask Siri on my smartphone."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:58:12.852000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. Can you walk me through the last time you asked Siri for for something? What was the situation, and what did you need an answer to?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:58:22.432000Z",
        "message": "I actually needed an answer to a restaurant that I couldn't think of the name of, but yet I knew where it was located."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:58:34.741000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for that. Can you tell me step by that sounds familiar. So you had the location in mind, but just couldn't remember the restaurant's name. Can you take me through exactly what you said to Siri? And, uh, what happened next?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:58:53.272000Z",
        "message": "I said, Siri. I am, uh, looking for the name of an Italian restaurant that is located at Main Street and Fourth Avenue in Brooklyn, New York."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:59:10.662000Z",
        "message": "Great detail. After you"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:59:10.772000Z",
        "message": "You want a sour"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:59:15.622000Z",
        "message": "No worries. Sounds like Siri may have misunderstood you mid sentence. There. What happened after you asked Siri about the Italian restaurant? At that location? Did Siri give you a helpful answer? Or did you have to try something else? To get what you needed?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:59:32.752000Z",
        "message": "After giving Siri the address, location, Siri was able to narrow down and give me the name of the restaurant correctly."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:59:44.791000Z",
        "message": "That's pretty handy. Thinking back to that moment, what did you find most helpful about using Siri for your search? And there anything that felt a bit annoying? Or got in the way?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:59:59.152000Z",
        "message": "I felt that Siri was very helpful. And I thought it was very convenient. And, also, she was very helpful. Um, I didn't come across any issues or, uh, things I had to repeat for her. So I was very satisfied with, that, you know, interaction with Siri."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:00:29.572000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like that was a smooth experience. If Siri wasn't available to you at that moment, what would you have done instead? Try and get the restaurant's name?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:00:40.391000Z",
        "message": "I probably would have asked chat GPT, um, which I've been using recently, and I'm finding that is very in multiple different areas."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:00:54.732000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. You're turning to ChatGPT more often, uh, these days. Can you tell me about a recent time you used ChatGPT to get an answer? What was the situation, and how did it go?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:01:06.792000Z",
        "message": "So it was for my business. Purposes, and, uh, I was trying to compose an email and I just wasn't, um, getting the words and the tone down perfectly. By myself. So I did speak into ChatGPT. And they gave me a much more polished version. And then also did give me different options, uh, to be a little more professional or a little more you know, not as professional."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:01:46.672000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for breaking that down. When you use ChatGPT for your email, what stood out to you as especially helpful? And was there anything about the experience that frustrated you or slowed you down?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:02:00.632000Z",
        "message": "There was absolutely nothing that's slowed me down or nothing that was frustrating me at all. I basically spoke into what I wanted my email to say. And I felt that the option that it gave me back was along the lines of exactly how I liked it to sound. So I was really very satisfied. And, um, like I said, absolutely no issues whatsoever."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:02:30.372000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate your detail. Thinking about both Siri and ChatGPT, is there a situation where you'd pick 1 over the other? What makes you reach for Siri sometimes? ChatGPT other times?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:02:42.322000Z",
        "message": "Well, recently, I well, I mean, in the past, I've always used Siri, but now that I have found chat GPT, I can honestly say that chat GPT, I would probably go uh, would be my first choice. Um, recently, because I'm just learning how to use it, and and it's been very helpful. Sometimes when I use Siri, I do have to repeat myself or don't get, you know, the correct, thing I want right away. So I would probably go more with chat GPT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:03:19.042000Z",
        "message": "That's a shift. Sounds like discovering ChatGPT is changing your habits a bit. Can you think of a specific moment when you chose ChatGPT first? Even though you might have used Siri before? What led you to make that switch?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:03:33.092000Z",
        "message": "Um, it was just recently because of the more I was using ChatGPT, I kind of felt a little more secure. And the fact that it would save time where I knew I didn't have to um, basically, you know, speak into it more than once, which, like I've said, I've found with CRE sometimes she doesn't understand me or doesn't give me the correct, you know, thing I'm looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:04:05.701000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. You mentioned feeling more secure with ChatGPT. And saving time by not having to repeat yourself. How about trust? When you get an answer from Siri versus ChatGPT, do you feel differently about whether you can rely on those answers? Can you say a bit about that?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:04:23.922000Z",
        "message": "It basically feel the same with Siri and ChatGPT. I I do feel like I can trust both of those tools."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:04:37.362000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Switching gears just a little Have you ever used other answer engines like Google's AI summaries Perplexity, or Gemini? If so, what tasks led you to try those out?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:04:50.172000Z",
        "message": "While I have heard of those search engines, I really have not used them at all. Uh, you know, maybe in the future, will, but I am fairly satisfied with the chat GPT and Siri at this point in time. So I may, you know, check them out going forward. But I haven't in the past."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:16.772000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. When you think about Google Answers, ChatGPT, Siri, or some of these other tools, do any words, feelings, or images come to mind for each 1? For example, if they were people at a party, how would you describe how each 1 acts?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:34.592000Z",
        "message": "That I feel like they are loyal. They listen."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:43.712000Z",
        "message": "That's an interesting take."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:43.872000Z",
        "message": "And I feel like they yeah. And I feel like they I do trust the information they're giving me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:55.602000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for clarifying. Um, when you get an answer, and want to share it with someone else, maybe forwarding a recommendation or info, do you feel more comfortable quoting Siri, chat GPT, or another engine? What makes 1 feel more credible to share than another?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:12.652000Z",
        "message": "Like I've said before, I feel like Siri and GPT are pretty much neck and neck with how I feel with getting any information from them. And I feel that what they tell me, I can pretty much trust."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:28.872000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Looking back to about a year ago, do you notice any changes in how you look things up now compared to then? Any shifts in your habits or in your go to answer engine?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:42.682000Z",
        "message": "No. I don't have any shifts, uh, with any of the information."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:48.842000Z",
        "message": "Understood. Last question. Do friends or coworkers ever mention which answer engines they use and recommend? If so, which ones tend to come up?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:59.102000Z",
        "message": "Most of the time, um, so friends and coworkers do tell me that they use ChatGPT. More than anything else. So that's what led me to try them out as well."
      },
      {
        "callId": "31dd54e0e983434a8bfa463bd",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:07:13.812000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to know. Thanks so much for walking through all this with me and sharing your stories. I really appreciate it. Just to wrap up, how was this interview experience for you? Chatting within"
