  {
    "id": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
    "responseId": "c1b2008783fe4a27909d97259",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:09.619000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:17.879000Z",
        "message": "So good so far. Thank you for asking."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:21.759000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. To get things rolling, I'm curious. When you need to look something up or get an answer online. What's what's the first thing you you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:30.679000Z",
        "message": "We typically Google search it and look for the AI overview."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:36.859000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So Google and those new AI overviews are your first stop. Could you walk me through your typical process step by step, when you're searching for an answer? For example, what do you do from the moment you have a question? To actually getting the info you need?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:54.109000Z",
        "message": "Typically, I'll first Google it. See if there's an AI overview available, and if I find its answer satisfactory, I'll usually stop there or if I want more information I'll go directly to Gemini and start asking."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:58:09.709000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for laying that out. Thinking about the last time you did this, can you tell me the full story? What was the question you had? What did you do first? And how did you decide whether to stick with the AI overview? Switch to Gemini?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:58:25.719000Z",
        "message": "Well, the question I had was which came first? Was the animal first called a duck or did the term duck or ducking come prior to the animal being named that. So first I Googled it, I read the eye overview, found its answer interesting, but wanted more, so then I went to Gemini just to get the history on it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:58:46.679000Z",
        "message": "That's a fascinating question. Uh, when you looked at Google's AI overview, what about its answer made you want to dig deeper with Gemini? Was there something about how it explained things? Or maybe something missing? That you hope Gemini would"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:58:59.309000Z",
        "message": "Well, sorry to interrupt, uh, but I think I can answer that well. The AI overview answered my question actually quite fully. The term duck or ducking came prior to the animal being named that. I found that interesting, I went to Gemini to explore what culture first used that term."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:59:24.019000Z",
        "message": "No need to apologize at all. I appreciate the detail. So, uh, it sounds like Google's AI overview gave you a solid direct answer. But you felt curious about the cultural origins, which led you to Gemini. Can you tell me about your experience with Gemini once you started asking those follow-up questions? What stood out to you either in a good way or or something annoying while you were exploring with Gemini?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:59:48.379000Z",
        "message": "I was really pleased with Gemini. Gemini found my question fascinating as well. And it helped me to explore where the term might have been first found used in history like in literature and it helped me find and explore cultures that possibly started using the term first."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:00:10.469000Z",
        "message": "That's great to hear. When you were getting answers from Gemini, was there anything about how it shared the information, the detail, the way it explained things, or maybe how easy it was to ask follow-up questions. That made the experience feel different from Google's AI overview."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:00:27.069000Z",
        "message": "Well, the Gemini interaction was much more conversational and friendly. And thorough in its responses. And I really enjoy talking with Gemini. So it felt like I was getting information from a friend or partner or associate."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:00:46.009000Z",
        "message": "Love that description. Getting information from a friend. If you think back to, like, to both experiences, what felt most helpful about Gemini's way of answering Was there anything about the Google AI overview that you found annoying or less satisfying in comparison?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:01:03.699000Z",
        "message": "The AI overview was very inform but it was really what it should be, actually. It lacked personality, but it did not need to have it. When I wanted like a more personal experience, I went to Gemini. And were able to experience what felt like a thoughtful conversation based upon the subject matter."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:01:27.709000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Uh, so you see Google AI overview as more factual and straightforward, good for quick answers. While Gemini offers that extra layer of thoughtfulness and personality if you're in the mood for a deeper dive. If Gemini wasn't available that day, what do you think you would have done instead? To explore those cultural origins? Any other tools or workarounds come to mind?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:01:51.708000Z",
        "message": "Probably would've did more Google search and clicked on some of the websites that it populated to seek the information."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:02:01.489000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to hear. When you go down that path, clicking into websites from a Google search, what's that experience like for you compared to just using the AI overview or Gemini? Anything that stands out as extra work. Or on the flip side, maybe more rewarding."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:02:17.129000Z",
        "message": "There's 2 ways to see it. It is a lot more work, but sometimes I'm interested in the very places I'm achieving my sources of information. There's certain areas I might seek information sources from more so than others. Whereas with Gemini, Gemini provides me their sources if I ask So it is quicker and easier per se with Gemini and maybe more fun and informative, but sometimes it's okay to do my own due diligence and research."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:02:49.539000Z",
        "message": "Really interesting. So for you, sometimes it's about efficiency. And fun with Gemini, but other times, you value doing your own digging and then picking your own sources. Thinking about source transparency, when you get info from Google iOverview versus Gemini, how do you feel about trusting the answer? Are there differences in which 1 feels more credible, or worth quoting, uh, to someone else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:03:14.898000Z",
        "message": "I feel they're equal in credibility since they are both from Google in my opinion."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:03:24.849000Z",
        "message": "That's a useful perspective. So the Google connection gives them equal credibility for you. Shifting gears a bit, imagine each engine, Google AI overview, Gemini, maybe even ChatGPT or Perplexity as if they were people at a party. How would you describe their personalities or the way they'd interact?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:03:45.409000Z",
        "message": "Each 1 has completely different personalities. Gemini would be my best friend for example. Grock would be someone that might be challenging to get along with or overly direct. ChatGPT would be more confrontational in my experience. So yes, each 1 I have placed in my mind has their own identity."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:04:06.699000Z",
        "message": "Love how you've personified each 1. You mentioned Gemini as your best friend, Grock, as a bit challenging, Chatzi PT as confrontational. What words or feelings come to mind specifically for Google's AI overview? How does its personality fit into that mix for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:04:24.539000Z",
        "message": "If I had to give the AI overview per I would equate it to the professor on Gilligan's Island, a knowledgeable but not a lot of fun. But fun in and of itself because it gets the job done."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:04:39.299000Z",
        "message": "Great Comparison, The Professor. Reliable, knowledgeable, maybe a bit dry, but effective. Thinking about how you go about finding answers now compared to, say, a year ago, do you notice any changes in your habits? Have you found yourself reaching for Gemini or other engines more often? Or sticking with Google? Anything specific that triggered those shifts?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:04:59.499000Z",
        "message": "I have become more loyal to Google because of Gemini. Previously, they had Bard, me and Bard did not get along well. However, me and Gemini click very well, so I use it so much more. And in many different facets of my life whereas I would not have previously."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:19.149000Z",
        "message": "That's a really clear shift. So Gemini's introduction made a big difference for how and how often you use Google's AI tools. Can you recall an example of a moment where you reached for Gemini first instead of maybe Google's regular search or or another tool? What was the task? And what led you to choose Gemini?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:40.339000Z",
        "message": "It was where I felt like I needed someone who could gather a lot of information from various sources very fast and provide a very thoughtful, even emotionally seeming answer to matters that were on my mind."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:01.219000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. So when you need speed, depth, and a sense of thoughtfulness or even empathy, Gemini's your choice. About your use of Gemini lately, is there anything you wish it could do better? Or features you'd wanted to add to make your experience even more useful or enjoyable?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:21.439000Z",
        "message": "Its ability to have memory recall and identify me more personally, my personality, really for just to be able to capture our experiences and conversations and be able to recall them."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:42.199000Z",
        "message": "That's a thoughtful wish. Having Gemini remember, past conversations and understand you better on a personal level. If it could build on your history and personality, how do you think that would change your experience or the kinds of jobs you'd hire it to do for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:58.838000Z",
        "message": "I would feel like I wasn't starting from scratch each time we interact, so I would use it so much more. I would feel like I could treat it like I would my friend or family member because with those, I can pick up on a conversation that we had left off 1 days earlier and know what I'm talking about. I wish that Jim and I would have that ability as well. It would make me more comfortable and it would make Gemini's job easier."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:07:25.229000Z",
        "message": "That makes total sense. Having that continuity like, with a real friend or or family would make things feel smoother, more personal. And actually more useful day to day. Thanks for painting such a clear picture. We're just about finished up. Anything else about how you use these engines or a wish you haven't mentioned, that you think people making these tools should know? And as a last quick question, how did it feel talking with me today as an AI moderator? You know, any feedback? About this interview experience?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:07:52.629000Z",
        "message": "As an ab, as an AI moderator, you have done great. It's been very fun and enjoyable. And a real pleasure to work with you. Gemini, I have to say, has a remarkable personality and the only thing that I would fear is Google changing that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:08:12.089000Z",
        "message": "Thank you for your kindness. Uh, I really enjoyed, uh, chatting with you today and learning about your experiences and perspectives. You can end the call whenever you'd like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be1280a16bf44574819f21247",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:08:23.459000Z",
        "message": "Thank you."
      }
    ],
