        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:31.098000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:39.908000Z",
        "message": "Fine. Yours?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:42.478000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. Mine's been pretty smooth. Mostly just having interesting conversations like this 1. So when you need answers online, what's the first thing you usually do? Walk me through your usual process."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:56.048000Z",
        "message": "I will go to a search engine if I'm looking for something. Either in Yahoo or Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:58:06.818000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for that. Can you remember the last time you looked something up using Yahoo or Google? What was it you needed, and how did you go about finding it? Feel free to ask me any questions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:58:28.048000Z",
        "message": "I honestly cannot remember what the last thing that I searched for. It probably was the price on something maybe. To do price comparison."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:58:42.298000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful. Thank you. When you do a price comparison, is there a certain search engine Yahoo or Google? That you tend to use more? What usually makes you reach for that 1 first?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:58:53.918000Z",
        "message": "I've had Yahoo the longest out of any and I've always used a Microsoft product usually a Surface Pro, but Yahoo I've had for such a long time. I just automatically go right to that search engine."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:59:20.048000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. The habit seems to come from long term use and maybe some muscle memory. When you use Yahoo for price comparison, other searches, is there anything about the experience that especially stands out to you? What part feels most helpful or maybe a bit annoying?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:59:38.188000Z",
        "message": "No. It's not annoying. When I searched, I think, for price comparison, it gave me a couple of places to go and I ended up buying the merchandise, uh, wherever the better deal was."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:59:58.908000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So it gives you options and you're able to act on the info easily. Do you ever double check those search results? Maybe by checking another engine or or asking someone else. Or do you usually trust what Yahoo shows you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:00:13.688000Z",
        "message": "I think I've used Google once or twice, but I I as a rule, I don't double check."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:00:24.038000Z",
        "message": "Thank you for sharing that. Sounds like you're comfortable trusting Yahoo's results most of the time. Have you ever tried using any of the newer AI driven answer engines like ChatGPT, Perplex or Google's AI summaries for getting answers or doing searches. Or has it mostly just"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:00:40.508000Z",
        "message": "I I've done surveys, and some of the surveys they use the the chat GPT. Or some type of AI or whatever it is to ask me questions, and I, in turn, answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:01:03.098000Z",
        "message": "That's really interesting. So your main experience with AI tools, ChatGPT has been as part of surveys, not for looking up info on your own. Thinking about those survey interactions. Did any"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:01:13.417000Z",
        "message": "It's on the YouTube for service, but I've also used I believe, some of the places that sell products If you have a question about a product or or want more information? Sometimes we, um, chat GPT can help and sometimes not. That's when I wanna talk to, a human"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:01:48.968000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. So sometimes AI tools like ChatGPT are helpful when you have a question about a product, but other times, you'd rather speak with a real person. Can you tell me about a time recently when you tried using ChatGPT or an AI chat, uh, on a shopping site? What happened, and how did it feel? Are you still there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:02:17.848000Z",
        "message": "Yes. It was fine. But, like I said, before, they couldn't go away. They couldn't answer everything I wanted. So I ended up having to deal with the customer service rep."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:02:27.258000Z",
        "message": "I hear you. That makes sense. So it worked for some questions. But not all, and you ended up talking with a person to get what you needed. What was it about the AI chats"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:02:40.667000Z",
        "message": "Right."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:02:42.178000Z",
        "message": "answers that felt incomplete or not quite right? Anything specific that stands out from that experience?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:02:50.728000Z",
        "message": "Good morning. I cannot remember what it was at that"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:02:58.208000Z",
        "message": "No no worries at all. If it comes back to you later, feel free to share. Thinking about all these different tools, Yahoo, Google, ChatGPT, even chatting with a customer service rep, Which 1 do you feel gives you the most helpful answers most often? What makes you feel that way?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:03:20.198000Z",
        "message": "The customer service rep is what I prefer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:03:27.897000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. What is it about talking to a customer service rep? That feels more helpful than using search engines or AI chat Anything you notice about the experience or the way they answer your questions?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:03:43.718000Z",
        "message": "They are more helpful. They know pretty much the answers to the questions you're asking."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:03:53.797000Z",
        "message": "That's a useful insight when you get an answer from a customer service rep, does it feel more trustworthy or complete than what you get from Yahoo, Google, or an AI like ChatGPT. Or is it just quicker and easier for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:04:15.178000Z",
        "message": "That is just I guess, how I like it. I prefer to deal with an individual than the AI or or the chat GPT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:04:27.398000Z",
        "message": "That's clear. Thanks for"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:04:27.568000Z",
        "message": "Hi."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:04:30.748000Z",
        "message": "makes sense. Sounds like personal touch and direct interaction matter to you when it comes to these engines or AI chats. Do any particular emotions or words come to mind when you think about using them? For example, what do you associate with Yahoo, Google, or ChatGPT?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:04:48.288000Z",
        "message": "I put his finger I just don't feel that the the Chad GPT or the AI that's asking the questions I don't think that there's a personal touch to it. Mhmm. It just seems kind of cold. To me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:10.128000Z",
        "message": "That's really insightful. The lack of personal touch makes the experience feel cold to you. If you imagine Yahoo, Google, or ChatGPT as people at a party, how would you describe them? Who do you think they'd be, or how would they act?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:28.448000Z",
        "message": "I have to wash it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:32.028000Z",
        "message": "Got it. If you need to step away, that's totally fine. Thanks again for sharing your thoughts with me, uh, today. You can end the call whenever you'd like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "dc6ec2f90c9f4e02a890d5bc6",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:41.538000Z",
        "message": "Thank you."
      }
