        "index": 46,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:04:44.894000Z",
        "message": "makes sense, you got more definitions and perspectives broken down in a way that was helpful for your paper. If you were picking between Google and Bing for a quick answer versus a more in-depth explanation. How do you decide which 1 to use?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5690a627fa5140479a2c2b1bf",
        "index": 47,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:01.354000Z",
        "message": "I would put bling more than Google because it breaks it down more and stuff."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5690a627fa5140479a2c2b1bf",
        "index": 48,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:13.234000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. That's really clear. For you, Bing's detailed breakdowns are more useful, especially when you need deeper explanations. When you're looking for something quick, just a fast simple answer, do you still go to Bing or does Google win there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5690a627fa5140479a2c2b1bf",
        "index": 49,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:28.283000Z",
        "message": "Google I gotta if I wanna quick answer, I go to Google. But if I want a more definition and more elaborate, I go to Bing."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5690a627fa5140479a2c2b1bf",
        "index": 50,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:38.374000Z",
        "message": "Super clear. So Google is your go to for speed, and Bing is for deeper dives. Thinking about both tools, what kinds of feelings or"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5690a627fa5140479a2c2b1bf",
        "index": 51,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:46.224000Z",
        "message": "Well, what kind of Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5690a627fa5140479a2c2b1bf",
        "index": 52,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:57.664000Z",
        "message": "I meant, like, what kinds of feelings or associations come up for you when you think about Google versus Bing? For example, do you feel more confident or do you do you trust 1 more than the other or do they both feel pretty similar to you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5690a627fa5140479a2c2b1bf",
        "index": 53,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:14.394000Z",
        "message": "I felt the same about both of them. I I mean, 1 gives me more. Than the other, but I still feel that it's it's same in some aspects."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5690a627fa5140479a2c2b1bf",
        "index": 54,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:32.094000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. They both get the job done just in different ways. If you had to recommend 1 to a friend for doing a school paper, Which 1 would you suggest what would you tell them about why?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5690a627fa5140479a2c2b1bf",
        "index": 55,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:45.454000Z",
        "message": "I would say bling because it gives you more of a definition, and it elaborates more. Than Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5690a627fa5140479a2c2b1bf",
        "index": 56,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:06:54.014000Z",
        "message": "That's clear. More depth and explanation from Bing. For papers. If you look back a year, do you notice any changes in how often you use Google versus Bing, or do you pretty much use them the same as before?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5690a627fa5140479a2c2b1bf",
