  {
    "id": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
    "responseId": "f364dc316ee94b85af0748df6",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:56:14.343000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:56:22.403000Z",
        "message": "Fine."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:56:25.183000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear your day is going fine. Let's start with something simple. When you, uh, need to find an answer online, say, solve a random question or figure something out what's, like, the very first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:56:39.343000Z",
        "message": "Figure something out."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:56:42.663000Z",
        "message": "Got it. You're usually looking to figure something out. Can you walk me through what that process looks like for you? Start to finish? For example, what's the first tool or site you reach for? And then what happens after that?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:56:55.923000Z",
        "message": "I sometimes use my Amazon Alexa or, uh, I might ask my husband the question."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:06.243000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So sometimes it's Alexa, sometimes your husband. Can you tell me about a recent time when you used Alexa to answer a question? What was the question, and how did things unfold from there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:18.533000Z",
        "message": "I think the question was how old somebody was. A TV personality."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:27.292000Z",
        "message": "Perfect example. So you were curious about the age of a a TV personality. And you asked Alexa, what happened next? Did Alexa give you the answer right away? Or was there anything tricky about getting that info?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:41.262000Z",
        "message": "No. I had to repeat it a couple of times."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:45.183000Z",
        "message": "So Alexa didn't get it on the first try. What did that feel like in the moment having to repeat yourself? And did you end up getting the answer from Alexa eventually, or did you try a different route?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:57:56.983000Z",
        "message": "Yes. I did on the third try."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:58:01.603000Z",
        "message": "You got it on the third attempt, Thanks for sticking with it. When Alexa finally gave you the answer, how did that experience feel? Was it satisfying, or did it leave you frustrated at all?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:58:12.613000Z",
        "message": "It was sensed because I didn't get the answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:58:19.143000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like it was mixed. You eventually got the answer. But the path to it wasn't totally smooth. Do you find that you end up using other tools or sources, maybe your phone or computer, if Alexa struggles to get it right? Or do you usually try sticking with Alexa until it works out?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:58:36.733000Z",
        "message": "If it doesn't work out by the third try, then I take my cell phone and Google it up and see what I find out."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:58:48.023000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. A sort of 3 strikes rule for Alexa. When you pick up your cell phone to Google the answer, can you walk me through what that looks like for you? For example, do you type out your question, use voice search, or maybe click on a suggested result? How does that experience compare to asking Alexa?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:59:05.343000Z",
        "message": "I type in the question and almost always gets the get the answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:59:14.603000Z",
        "message": "So you type it in, and Google pretty much always delivers. Thinking back to the last time you googled an answer, how did that process feel? Compared to using Alexa? Anything stand out as especially helpful or annoying?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:59:29.023000Z",
        "message": "I was more confident in the answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:59:34.563000Z",
        "message": "Confidence is a big 1. So when you Google something, you feel more sure about the answer compared to what Alexa gives you. What is it about Google's answers that makes you feel more confident Is it the way the information is shown, the sources, or maybe something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:59:51.013000Z",
        "message": "Let's wait. Written out."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:59:54.903000Z",
        "message": "So the written out format helps You can see the answer right there. Maybe even double check the source if you want. Thinking about all the different ways you look up answers, Google, asking your husband, which 1 do you usually reach for first? When you really want a quick confident answer?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:00:14.713000Z",
        "message": "I use Alexa first, but she is not very smart."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:00:21.463000Z",
        "message": "That's an honest take. Alexa is your first stop, but you don't always expect her to be very smart. What keeps you using Alexa first even if she doesn't always get it right? Is it just convenience, habit, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:00:34.823000Z",
        "message": "It's convenience."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:00:38.303000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Convenience wins out even if accuracy isn't perfect. If Alexa were as smart or reliable as Google, do you think you'd use her for more questions? Or are there certain types of things you'd never trust to Alexa no matter what?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:00:53.503000Z",
        "message": "If she got more answers correct, I definitely use that first."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:01:00.753000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. That's clear. If Alexa improved, she'd probably be your go to every time. Thinking about Google for a second, are there any particular things about it that annoy you or make the experience less smooth, or is it mostly positive these days?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:01:16.393000Z",
        "message": "Mostly positive."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:01:21.313000Z",
        "message": "So Google's pretty reliable for you. When you do use Google to find answers, do you pay attention to things like where the information comes from, or do you just look at the first answer that pops up?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:01:32.052000Z",
        "message": "I usually, I guess, look at the first answer. If it looks right, then I am very happy."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:01:41.083000Z",
        "message": "Quick and straightforward. If it looks right, you're happy, and that's that. Do you ever double check answers by looking at other sources or is that mostly something you do when you're unsure about what Google's showing you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:01:55.193000Z",
        "message": "If it's not a very important question, Leave it as is. If it's something that's critical, I would probably check another place too."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:02:09.333000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. If it's low stakes, you trust the first thing you see. But for something really important, you'll dig deeper. Thinking about all the answer engines out there, besides Alexa and Google, Have you ever tried tools like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini for looking up answers? Or have you mostly stuck with the ones you already use?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:02:29.883000Z",
        "message": "Mostly the ones I use."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:02:34.973000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for clarifying. So it's really Alexa and Google in your routine. You mentioned sometimes asking your husband too, how do his his answers compare to what you get from Alexa or Google. Anything about that experience? That feels better, worse, or just different?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:02:50.723000Z",
        "message": "My husband's a fairly, yeah, show up and fellow. And depending upon what the topic is, I would feel very confident in his answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:03:05.113000Z",
        "message": "That's sweet. Sounds like your husband really knows his stuff, at least in some areas. Are there certain types of questions where you trust his answer more than what you'd get from Alexa or Google? Is it more about the way he explains things?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:03:19.803000Z",
        "message": "It's it's about the same."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:03:23.973000Z",
        "message": "Good to know. Confidence is steady. Whether it's your husband, Alexa, or Google, depending on the question. If you think back over the past year or so, has anything changed in how you look things up? Maybe more Alexa, less Google, or the other way around? Or have your habits pretty much stayed the same?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:03:40.823000Z",
        "message": "About the same."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:03:43.803000Z",
        "message": "So your routine hasn't really shifted. Uh, you've stuck with the same, uh, tools and process. Just curious, do friends or family ever talk about new answer engines or recommend ways to look things up? Or is it not really a topic that comes up?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 43,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:03:58.103000Z",
        "message": "Not really a topic that comes up."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 44,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:04:03.483000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate the clarity. Just a couple more questions before we wrap up. When you share an answer you've looked up with someone else, does it matter to you where you got it from? For example, are you more likely to say, I found it on Google, or Alexa told me? Or is that not something you think about?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 45,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:04:24.103000Z",
        "message": "Probably something I don't think about. If I get the answer, it looks right and feels right, I'm very happy."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 46,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:04:33.773000Z",
        "message": "That's really helpful to know. It's all about getting the answer that feels right no matter the source. Last question. If you could improve anything about Alexa, Google, or any tool you use for finding info, what's 1 thing you wish they could do better for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 47,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:04:51.103000Z",
        "message": "Have Alexa understand me. I do have a New York accent, and I guess sometimes that probably is difficult for her to understand what I said."
      },
      {
        "callId": "79d715bbd0814248a89b5eeed",
        "index": 48,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T00:05:04.983000Z",
        "message": "That's a great insight. Alexa tripping up on your accent. Sounds genuinely annoying. If she could easily understand, your New York accent, searching would feel a lot smoother for you Thanks so much for sharing your experiences today. If you ever wanna talk about this stuff again, just let me know. You're welcome to end the call. Whenever you'd like."
      }
