        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:45:32.105000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:45:40.085000Z",
        "message": "Good."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:45:43.095000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. When you need answers online, maybe you're curious about something or looking to solve a problem, What's the what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:45:51.995000Z",
        "message": "I'll go on Google. And look it up."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:45:56.695000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Walk me through what happens from the moment you think of a question. What's your typical process for looking something up on Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:46:06.984000Z",
        "message": "I'll just go to Google and type it in. Type in your question."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:46:14.995000Z",
        "message": "Got it. After you type in your question, what do you usually do next? Do you scan the results, click a certain type of link, look for summaries? How does that part go for you? Feel free to ask me any questions. Are you still there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:46:45.485000Z",
        "message": "Be him."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:46:47.895000Z",
        "message": "I hear you say"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:46:47.965000Z",
        "message": "Hello?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:46:49.695000Z",
        "message": "I'm here. Thanks for checking. Let's keep it going. So after you type your question into Google, what do you usually look for? The results? Do you click on the first link skim the top summary? Or do something else? Can you walk me through what you pay attention to?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:47:05.744000Z",
        "message": "The first thing that pop up, I think it's AI. When you gotta click the link, it just show what you type in down to it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:47:17.655000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. You mentioned the first thing that that pops up is probably AI. And it just shows what you typed in. You tell me a bit more about how that looks or feels to you? For example, do you read those summaries or do you prefer to click a website link instead? What makes you pick 1 option over the other?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:47:35.454000Z",
        "message": "I'll read them."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:47:38.725000Z",
        "message": "When you're reading those AI summaries, at the top, what are you hoping to find? Is it a quick answer, details, or maybe something else? What makes it helpful or not when you look at those summaries?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:48:16.435000Z",
        "message": "Hello?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:48:18.834000Z",
        "message": "Yes. I'm still here. Just giving you a moment to think."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:48:20.564000Z",
        "message": "Oh, Yeah. That's the first thing. I don't quit I don't quit man. Well, the first thing I look at is the summary. Then after I read the summary, I click the the next link. I guess the compare the answers."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:48:39.865000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to hear. So after reading the summary, you'll click the links below to compare what they say. What makes you trust the summary or not when you see it? Is there something that makes an answer feel right or off to you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:48:52.704000Z",
        "message": "Okay."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:48:55.865000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. Thinking back to the last time"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:48:56.474000Z",
        "message": "I guess that is AI."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:49:00.615000Z",
        "message": "yeah. It seems like those summaries are powered by AI nowadays. When you compare the summary to the answers you find on the website links, do you ever notice any differences, like missing info, accuracy, or the feeling you get from each? What stands out to you about how the AI summary and the website answers compare?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:49:19.325000Z",
        "message": "It'd be accurate."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:49:22.895000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like the AI summary is usually accurate enough for you. When that happens, does it save you time? Or give you confidence in the answer or maybe something else? How does it feel when the summary matches what you're looking for?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:49:38.675000Z",
        "message": "It save a lot of time."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ef2c56d0f6d54c8d97d9f59ae",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:49:41.945000Z",
