        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:45:21.956000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it's okay. Just to warm up. When you need answers online, what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:45:29.196000Z",
        "message": "I use Google. Search."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:45:33.036000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing. Can you walk me through your typical process when you're looking something up on Google? Maybe step by step, starting with what usually triggers you to search."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:45:43.236000Z",
        "message": "If I'm looking for some learn about a certain topic or wanna find directions or wanna find out a website. I just use, um, top of this Usually, search the words in the bar. And search."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:45:59.766000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. Thinking back to the last time you used Google, what was it that you needed help with? You tell me the story of what happened? From what you wanted to know to how you use Google to you did with the answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:46:14.156000Z",
        "message": "I wanted to, um, see I was doing research on, um, sports statistics. Um, I usually do it for sports betting. So I want to see, um, stats for a player for a team. So I researched searched the name and or the player and the team and found the website that I wanted to find the stats for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:46:36.646000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So you were digging up sports stats for betting and started by searching the player or team name in Google. When you landed on the site with the stats, how did you decide it was the right 1? And was anything about that process particularly easy or frustrating?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:46:51.716000Z",
        "message": "Uh, the process was typically easy. I mean, this went straight to the, um, the site I needed. It was from ESPN dot com, so I know that's a trusted site. So that's how I knew it was legit."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:47:04.686000Z",
        "message": "Sounds straightforward. You trusted ESPN. So once you saw that in the results, you felt confident. In situations like this, do you ever use any tools besides Google maybe ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini for answers? Or is Google pretty much your default?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:47:21.676000Z",
        "message": "Google's my default. I only use CheckGPT if I want to find out information about a certain topic that I think I get more in-depth information on."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:47:34.576000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. Can you tell me about a time when you use ChatGPT instead of Google? What was the task, and what made you switch for that particular search?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:47:48.246000Z",
        "message": "I had a sports bet, and I wanted to see how chat GPT felt about it if it was a high confidence play. So I had took a picture of the screenshot of the the plays I had, and then I I'd sent it to check GPT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:48:04.296000Z",
        "message": "That's a fun use case, uh, getting ChatGPT's take on your sports bet. When you sent the screenshot and asked for its opinion, what did ChatGPT do that felt different from what Google might offer? Anything stand out about how it respond"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:48:15.886000Z",
        "message": "It it did a deep dive on my plays and gave me a very insightful answer on if it was a high probability play to win or not."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:48:31.926000Z",
        "message": "So you got a deep personalized breakdown from ChatGPT. How did that response feel compared to what you you usually get with Google? Did it seem more helpful, more trustworthy? Or just different in some way?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:48:44.926000Z",
        "message": "It was definitely more helpful because, um, just on Google, it doesn't give me in-depth information and analysis on what I want to, um, want to know about."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:48:56.306000Z",
        "message": "That's clear. Sounds like ChatGPT went deeper for your specific question while Google just pointed you to general info. When you get answers like that, from ChatGPT, do you ever double check them elsewhere? Or do you just take its word for it?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:49:11.146000Z",
        "message": "I'll just take the word for it. I I trust the info that they give me. It's very accurate most of the time."
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:49:18.505000Z",
        "message": "Got it. You feel confident in ChatGPT's replies. And don't feel the need, um, to double check. If you think about both tools side by side, what would you say are the biggest strengths and weaknesses of Google compared to ChatGPT for you personally?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "ce42995be87d4254a448ca82f",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:49:34.426000Z",
        "message": "Uh, Google is just the most used tool. I mean, I don't think it have its advantages against chat GPC. I think chat PC Jet gives more in-depth information. That's why I like it more than Google, but Google is just a default search engine I usually use. So that's why I would prefer to use that over ChatGPT in certain cases."
      },
      {
