        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:51:05.898000Z",
        "message": "That makes a lot of sense. If each of these if each of these tools were a person at a party, who do you think they'd be and how would they act? Just go with whatever comes to mind."
      },
      {
        "callId": "386db5b0e4b244e382d0b2917",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:51:16.828000Z",
        "message": "Chad GPT would definitely be the fun loving, yet very knowledgeable friend. Gemini would be knowledgeable and there to discuss things with you, but a little quieter. And Google would be the older friend that's a little out of touch with what's current and what the younger people are into."
      },
      {
        "callId": "386db5b0e4b244e382d0b2917",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:51:44.518000Z",
        "message": "Love those descriptions. Really capture the vibe you get from each tool. Thinking about trust for a second, when you want to share an answer with someone else, which engine's answer feels most credible for you to quote, and what gives you that feeling?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "386db5b0e4b244e382d0b2917",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:52:01.428000Z",
        "message": "TEDGPT definitely feels the most the most reliable to quote. And I feel his way because I feel as if the sensors are able to to give me information that's based off of factual, reputable articles or videos. Not just something that somebody wrote and might spread a rumor about."
      },
      {
        "callId": "386db5b0e4b244e382d0b2917",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:52:30.628000Z",
        "message": "That's clear and gives a lot of insight. Into what you value. Looking back over the past year, has anything changed about how you look things up or which tool you reach for first? You describe a moment that really showed that shift if there was 1?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "386db5b0e4b244e382d0b2917",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:52:47.008000Z",
        "message": "I definitely feel like I gravitate more towards ChatGPT, Gemini, and other AI sources. Over Google, I guess, more so in addition to to Google. I still like to Google things. To get information quickly. But then I do like to double check it with AI sources. I definitely feel like it's been a gradual shift between just using Google as my my only way of searching information versus implementing ChatGPT, Gemini, and other AI sources? I definitely feel like in the future, though, I might rely more on AI and a little less on Google in order to streamline. The whole situation."
      },
      {
        "callId": "386db5b0e4b244e382d0b2917",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:53:32.538000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing the story, and the gradual shift. If you imagine a future where you use AI even more for getting answers, is there anything you wish these engines could do that would make them even more useful for you? Any features or changes you'd love to see?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "386db5b0e4b244e382d0b2917",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:53:48.438000Z",
        "message": "I would definitely like to have more voice activation with ChatGPT and Gemini. I know they do have features, which you can hear voice. I just definitely feel like that would be a very good tool as well as possibly being able to text you or email you summaries of the things you searched directly to your inbox or to your phone. So that way you can easily act access it later without having to search these topics again."
      },
      {
        "callId": "386db5b0e4b244e382d0b2917",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:54:23.778000Z",
        "message": "Those are great ideas. Voice activation and, um, direct summaries. Sent to your phone or email. Sounds super convenient. I'm curious on a practical level, how do you imagine using those features in your daily life? Any particular scenarios come to mind where they'd really make a difference for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "386db5b0e4b244e382d0b2917",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:54:43.148000Z",
        "message": "I definitely feel like using social media, commenting on world topics, or just discussing information or things that's that are going on with my friends or family. Would make these resources very invaluable. Because if somebody disagreed with me or had another point of view and asked me to cite my sources, It would be a lot easier to just be able to show them very quickly on my phone or email. Where I got this information from so that we could continue to discussion without me having to resource my point all over again in order to show proof."
      },
      {
        "callId": "386db5b0e4b244e382d0b2917",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:55:27.398000Z",
        "message": "That paints a really clear picture. Having quick access to your searched info, would make sharing and backing up your views much smoother. In real conversations. Thanks for opening up about all this. Before we wrap up, just curious how this this interview experience felt chatting with an AI about your habits today. And if there's anything else you'd like to add, please let me know. You can end the call whenever you're ready."
      },
      {
        "callId": "386db5b0e4b244e382d0b2917",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:55:53.698000Z",
        "message": "I definitely enjoyed this interview. It felt more like a conversation. I think the AI did an excellent job. Thank you."
      }
