  {
    "id": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
    "responseId": "f8712c8ee7e241c0b0fa56f04",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:42:42.978000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:42:51.288000Z",
        "message": "It's going okay."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:42:54.968000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it's at least okay. Start simple. When you need to look something up online, what's usually the very first thing you do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:43:05.018000Z",
        "message": "Go to Google. Go to Google and search it up."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:43:09.438000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Google's your starting point. You walk me through what that usually looks like step by step? For example, from the moment you have a question or need,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:43:17.398000Z",
        "message": "Yeah."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:43:19.968000Z",
        "message": "what do you do next?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:43:23.288000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. I go to Google, and then I type in what I wanna search for in the I want."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:43:30.548000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Once you type in what you're searching, what's the next thing you pay attention to, on the results page."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:43:39.318000Z",
        "message": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:43:41.218000Z",
        "message": "When the results pop up, do you usually click on the first link scan a few, or look for something specific like images, AI summaries, or news. Tell me a bit about what catches your eye."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:43:52.748000Z",
        "message": "Usually, I look at the news and the image"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:43:59.678000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. You're drawn to news and images first. What kinds of questions or or searches make you look at those sections instead of regular links?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:44:10.678000Z",
        "message": "Um, if I'm, uh, searching for the news, like, what happened with Trump or something or what's going on, stuff like that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:44:22.848000Z",
        "message": "That helps paint the picture. So if it's something current or or breaking, you had for the news. What about images? What situations would make you check those first?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:44:33.097000Z",
        "message": "When I'm looking at something to when I wanna look at something interesting to see, based around the topic."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:44:46.678000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So if you want a quick visual maybe to see a person, a place, or how something looks, you'll check images. Thinking back, when was the last time you searched on Google for an answer? And what was the situation? Can you walk me through that specific moment?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:45:02.498000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. I searched on Google about a couple of days ago about the shooting that happened to Kirk, and I wanted to know more about it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:45:21.478000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing. Can you tell me the story of how that whole search went step by step? Start with what made you curious. What you typed in, what you clicked, and what felt most helpful. Annoying."
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:45:36.548000Z",
        "message": "So I wanted more information on the Charlie Kirk incident. So I searched on Google and got some information, and I just wanted to know more about it. So I went to, like, the"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:45:51.388000Z",
        "message": "When you search"
      },
      {
        "callId": "d09ad856266a41819363458cf",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
