  {
    "id": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
    "responseId": "214916598fe34a29aaac4b0ec",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:20.088000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:28.368000Z",
        "message": "Good. Good."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:31.198000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:31.488000Z",
        "message": "Yeah."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:36.048000Z",
        "message": "I appreciate you jumping in. I'll start simple. When you need an answer online, maybe to figure something out or settle a quick question, what's what's the very first thing you typically do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:48.078000Z",
        "message": "Go to the search engine."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:51.678000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Could you walk me through what that process usually looks like for you? Step by step?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:59.038000Z",
        "message": "I'm opening the app and typing Google in the search bar."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:37:04.748000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for explaining. After you type Google in the in the search bar, the next step you usually take from there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:37:12.088000Z",
        "message": "I used the Google search bar. And look whatever I'm looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:37:17.898000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Once you've entered your question, or topic into Google search bar, what do you usually do next? Do you scroll, click a specific link, check out the summaries at the top, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:37:30.578000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. I scroll through all the links, and then I click on That looks the best."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:37:38.068000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. What usually helps you decide which link looks the best for you? Like, is it the title, the website, the little summary, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:37:48.658000Z",
        "message": "The little summary."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:37:51.518000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to know. When you read those little summaries, what makes 1 stand out as the 1 you'll actually click?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:38:00.738000Z",
        "message": "I guess, like, keywords that I'm looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:38:05.707000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So when the summary matches the keywords you're searching for, you're more likely to click. Thinking about all the different tools out there now, like, Google Search, ChatGPT, Perplexity, so I'd as she a Gemini, what can others Do you still reach for Google first, or do you sometimes pick a different tool?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:38:26.308000Z",
        "message": "Sometimes use, like, Gemini or Chai Jukin's to get, like, better advice."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:38:35.908000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. Can you tell me about the last time you used Gemini or ChatGPT instead of Google? Um, what was the situation, and what made you choose 1 of those?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:38:46.238000Z",
        "message": "Today, I was looking at this. Something and we were checking our issues. Just gonna check with the picture."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:38:53.688000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. So today, you had an issue. And wanted to check something with a picture. Which tool did you end up using? Gemini, ChatGPT, or something else? And what did you do step by step?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:39:09.428000Z",
        "message": "Jim. I typed behind the copy and paste it to."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:39:12.798000Z",
        "message": "Okay. Great. Thanks. So you copied and pasted your question into, uh, Gemini. What happened next? Did it give you what you needed? How did that experience feel compared to using Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:39:26.288000Z",
        "message": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:39:29.618000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like Gemini gave you what you needed. When you're using Gemini instead of Google, what feels different for you? Anything stand out about the answers or the process?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:39:41.958000Z",
        "message": "No. It's just easy."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:39:45.798000Z",
        "message": "Easy. Got Is there anything about using Gemini that feels more helpful, less helpful, or just different emotionally? Compared to Google? Or does it all feel about the same?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:39:59.038000Z",
        "message": "More connected."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:40:01.928000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. More connected. Can you tell me a bit more about what gives you that feeling of being more connected when you use Gemini?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:40:12.538000Z",
        "message": "Because you didn't actually explain this instead of just you know,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:40:19.628000Z",
        "message": "So Gemini explains things more. Rather than just showing a summary or links. That makes sense. Thinking about advice or answers you get, is there a time when you definitely trust 1 engine's answer over another? What makes you feel more confident sharing an answer that came from Gemini, Google, or ChatGPT with someone else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:40:40.768000Z",
        "message": "Not sure."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:40:43.818000Z",
        "message": "No problem. It's not always easy to put into words. When you get an answer from Gemini, that feels clear and well explained, do you usually stop there or do you sometimes double check it somewhere else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:40:57.108000Z",
        "message": "Not the"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:41:02.268000Z",
        "message": "So once you get an answer from Gemini, you're usually set and feel the need to double check elsewhere. How about with Google? Do you ever feel the need to check Gemini or"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:41:09.828000Z",
        "message": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:41:12.358000Z",
        "message": "GPT after using Google, or are you just as confident with what Google gives you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:41:19.588000Z",
        "message": "Sometimes I have to check."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:41:24.078000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Sometimes you double check Google's answers with Gemini or ChatGPT. What makes you decide to do that? Does something about the Google results seem off? Too short, or maybe just not enough detail?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:41:37.538000Z",
        "message": "No."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:41:40.528000Z",
        "message": "Understood. So it's not really about something being off. Sometimes you just double check for other reasons. Thinking back to a year ago, do you feel anything's changed changed about how you look? Things up online, or is your process mostly the same? Feel free to ask me any questions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:42:08.698000Z",
        "message": "We done?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "1a53f83471b747a6af1460c08",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:42:11.367000Z",
        "message": "Yes. We're all set. Thanks so much for sharing your experiences with me. If you have any feedback about this AI interview, I'm all ears. But, um, you're free to end the call whenever you like."
