  {
    "id": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
    "responseId": "4c21366481c04fd393377bbc2",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:35:54.502000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:08.892000Z",
        "message": "Hello? Can you hear me?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:11.452000Z",
        "message": "I can't hear you, but I can read anything you type here. Thanks for checking in. How are you doing today?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:17.831000Z",
        "message": "I'm fine."
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:21.582000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. Let's jump in. When you need answers online, what's the first thing you usually do? Can you walk me through your typical process? For looking something up?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:31.602000Z",
        "message": "When I search something up, I usually go to because I have a iPhone. I although I do have Safari, I still prefer going to Google. So I Google whatever answer whatever answers I need to my quest"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:48.962000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. So you usually open Google on your iPhone. Even though Safari is an option. Can you describe"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:54.622000Z",
        "message": "Yeah."
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:57.232000Z",
        "message": "the steps you go through starting from when a question pops into your mind, what do you do first, then next?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:37:04.781000Z",
        "message": "When a question pops up in mind, first thing I do is I go on the Google app on my phone, and I go to the search engine. And I type in my question, and majority of the time when I do type in my question, I get, like, an AI overview. And majority of the time, that's enough information for me to answer the question I needed."
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:37:28.942000Z",
        "message": "Got it. You open the Google app, type your question, and the AI overview often gives you what you need. You tell me about the last time you did this? Like, what was the question you had? And how did it go from start to finish?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:37:43.961000Z",
        "message": "I actually recently probably yesterday. No. I was just wanted to know who Charlie Kirk was, so I googled it. Because of the news coverage on him recently."
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:37:59.022000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for that example. So So you wanted to know who Charlie Kirk was after seeing some news coverage. And you googled his name. What did you see? When you searched? Did the AI overview show up? And what sort of information did it give you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:38:13.372000Z",
        "message": "When I searched who he was, they talked about his, like, how he fits in politically. Um, they just explained who he was and what his, you know, like, his occupation is. You know? He's a speaker. He speaks about certain topics. You know? So they basically gave me a brief description on who he was."
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:38:39.522000Z",
        "message": "In that brief description, was it enough for what you needed in that moment, or did you feel like you had to click through to other links or look for more details?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:38:48.182000Z",
        "message": "I think it was enough for what I needed because I know now know that he's a ally of Donald Trump and I didn't know that before."
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:38:58.962000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like that AI overview gave you a pretty quick answer. Without you needing to dig deeper. Was there anything about that experience that felt especially helpful or maybe anything that annoyed you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:39:10.822000Z",
        "message": "I think the most I found helpful is that I got, like, a basic you know, description on who he is instead of just being clueless about it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:39:20.672000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense of the basics right there. With, you know, no extra steps. If Google's AI overview hadn't been there, what would you have done? Would you have clicked on links or maybe tried another tool? You had to guess, what's the next tool you'd reach for besides Google? When you want quick answers?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:39:38.162000Z",
        "message": "I think I was still going Google, but if it didn't have the overview, I would just go on Wikipedia when you first search up the person."
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:39:48.672000Z",
        "message": "That's a classic move. Straight to Wikipedia from the search results. Thinking more broadly, uh, have you ever tried using other answer engines? Like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini for quick questions? So, what was the situation, and what made you switch from Google in that moment?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:40:06.672000Z",
        "message": "Does Meta AI fit in with those?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:40:10.892000Z",
        "message": "Absolutely. Meta AI fits right in with those kinds of answer engines. Have you tried using Meta AI or any of the others, like ChatGPT or Perplex Can you tell me about a time you used something besides Google? To answer a question? What led you to try it?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:40:27.162000Z",
        "message": "Actually, when I was, like, on social media, that's when I, you know, found out about, like, Meta AI. So I kinda wanted to, like, test it out. So I basically just searched up, a someone else's Instagram, like, celebrity's Instagram, and they gave me, like, a whole breakdown on who they are."
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:40:48.112000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. You discovered Meta AI through social media and decided to try it out right there. When you got that breakdown about the celebrity, how did that answer feel compared to what you usually get from Google or even Wikipedia? Was there anything noticeably different about how it gave you the info? Or how helpful it felt?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:41:07.942000Z",
        "message": "I think 1 thing that was different is that they actually it felt like they actually took the time to really explain to you. They like also, when you're on Meta AI, when they're they actually type it out, like, slowly so you can actually read the answer to the question."
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:41:30.572000Z",
        "message": "That's neat. So Meta AI's answer felt more thoughtful and kinda paced almost like a person talking to you directly. Did that make you trust the answer more? Or was it just a nicer experience overall?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:41:41.922000Z",
        "message": "I feel like it was just a nicer experience overall."
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:41:48.362000Z",
        "message": "Got it. A smoother, maybe more enjoyable way to get info. Thinking about these these engines, if you had to line them up from most helpful to least helpful for you, like Google, Meta AI, Wikipedia, maybe Chat GPT, what would your order be? And what's driving that ranking?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:42:04.812000Z",
        "message": "My order will probably Google then Meta and then ChatGPT. And I ranked it like that based off of the app I use the most and the app I use the least."
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:42:20.232000Z",
        "message": "Helpful. So for you, what you use most guides what feels most helpful. When you think about each of these Google, Meta AI, ChatGPT, what words or feelings come to mind for each? For example, how would you describe the vibe or personality of each 1?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:42:36.812000Z",
        "message": "I feel like for Google, I would describe it as, like, a old fashioned. Like, that's just something that's always gonna be a helpful tool, something that's been around and can tell for a long time, it can tell you things. For Meta, I would say is like, modern and fun. Like, it's new, and it's also, like, a fun way to get answers. And for ChatGPT, I would consider them kind of an AI leader"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:43:03.542000Z",
        "message": "That's a cool way to put it. Google has old fashioned and reliable meta as modern and fun, and ChatGPT as an AI leader. If you were telling a friend about an answer you found, which engine's answer would feel most credible to share? Makes you feel that way?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:43:18.142000Z",
        "message": "I feel like the most credible will be Google because not a lot of my friends use like, the other AI. They don't really use AI. I know that they use Google, though, and it's already, like, AI built into it. So know, that puts everything together for them."
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:43:34.712000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. Uh, Google's kind of the shared language among your group. Thinking back over the past year, has think changed about how you look things up online? Any new habits, engines, or triggers you've noticed?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:43:47.852000Z",
        "message": "I noticed a new habit of being I never really noticed the Google AI overview, but I noticed now I don't dig deeper into certain topics because when I have a question, the Google overview will already, you know, give me the answer I needed. So it will be no need for me to keep scrolling through the search page."
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:44:07.832000Z",
        "message": "That's a big shift. Not feeling the need to dig much because the AI overview covers your need right away. Do you remember when you first noticed that change or was there a certain moment where you realized you were relying on that overview, uh, more than before?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:44:22.982000Z",
        "message": "I feel like I just never noticed. I feel like it the AI overview has been there for a while, and I'm just barely starting to notice, like, now that I actually that's what I'm relying on."
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:44:35.042000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. Almost snuck up on you without you realizing it. Sometimes habits build up like that. Has anyone, like friends or family, ever suggested trying a different engine for answers or shared cool AI results they found, Or is it mostly just what you discover on your own?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:44:51.562000Z",
        "message": "I think my family kinda has a influence because my family, they use AI tools, like, picture tools on social media, and they're always showing me and telling me to try it out."
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:45:04.892000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to know. So your family's use of AI tools for things like images has nudged you to try new a a I features yourself. Has that ever made you more curious to use these AI answer engines? Or do you mostly stick to Google unless you need something different?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:45:21.181000Z",
        "message": "I feel like I mostly stick to Google unless I need something different. But I feel like the AI is still convenient."
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:45:31.162000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing your experiences. Um, that was really insightful. Before we wrap up, how was it chatting with an AI for this kind of interview? You can end the call whenever you'd like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "471bab0924bb4727acecf1c87",
        "index": 43,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:45:41.012000Z",
        "message": "I'm chatting with AI. I feel like a really good way to have a conversation, and I felt like I was talking to a real person."
      }
