  {
    "id": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
    "responseId": "ccbbfccebe5942929c859a5ba",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:29:26.754000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:29:34.604000Z",
        "message": "It's going great. How's your day?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:29:37.564000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. I don't experience days quite like humans do. But always curious. So every conversation is a fresh start for me. Let's jump in. When you need answers online, what's what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:29:52.083000Z",
        "message": "Go to Google search."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:29:54.804000Z",
        "message": "Got it. You head straight to Google. Can you walk me through what that typically looks like for you? For example, do you go to the home page? Type something in, scan results? What's your personal process from start to finish?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:30:06.064000Z",
        "message": "Well, I don't have a preference. It's just whatever chat thing is open, whether it's on my phone or by laptop, I just go to the search bar and put in what I what I'm looking for, and then I press search. Very easy."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:30:22.824000Z",
        "message": "Sounds super straightforward for you. So you use whatever search bar or chat tool is handy. No loyalty, just convenience. In the moment. Thinking about the last time you did"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:30:31.884000Z",
        "message": "Correct."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:30:33.924000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for clarifying. Thinking of the last time you looked something up, which tool or site happened to be open? And what were you searching for?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:30:45.674000Z",
        "message": "I was searching for an outdoor cat house for a feral cat. And I just put it in the search bar not on Google search bar, but dip in the where you type in the an email or a web page, I instead of typing a web page, I just typed in outdoor heated cat houses."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:31:07.614000Z",
        "message": "That's a good example. So you type your search directly into the browser's address bar rather than going to Google's homepage. When the results popped up, what did you see, and what did you do next?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:31:21.534000Z",
        "message": "Looked at the 1 clicked on for shopping. So all the the ones that were for sale would pop up. And then I just scrolled through till I found some that look good. And I clicked on to go to the web page to get more information."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:31:38.734000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. So you scan the shopping results and browse to what caught your eye. Were there any parts of that experience that felt especially helpful or maybe a little annoying"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:31:51.024000Z",
        "message": "No. Not really. There was a lot of choices, which I sometimes get overwhelmed with. Too many options. But, no, there wasn't anything annoying"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:32:03.684000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to know. So lots of choices, sometimes overwhelming, but nothing that truly bugged you. You didn't use that search method, what do you think you would have done instead?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:32:16.704000Z",
        "message": "I I don't think it would have done anything. I mean, Google or the Internet is how I get most 99 percent of my information, so I wouldn't have done anything different."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:32:29.654000Z",
        "message": "It sounds like using the Internet, especially Google or the browser search, is pretty much your default for finding answers. Have you ever used any of the newer AI driven answer engines like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini when looking something up? Or is it always the standard search?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:32:46.814000Z",
        "message": "I try I always try to avoid AI. Because I don't trust it. And I don't wanna rely on it. But I'm sure I use AI sometimes and don't realize it, but I do not intentionally ever use AI."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:33:05.264000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So you avoid AI tools on purpose, mostly because of trust and not wanting to be dependent. When you say you don't trust it, can you tell me a bit more? What makes AI engines feel less trustworthy to you compared to regular search?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:33:19.594000Z",
        "message": "I don't know where they got their information. And I don't know how AI works, and I don't trust anything. That I don't know how it works. So I kinda feel like maybe I'm searching for outdoor cat house or something like that. It wouldn't be harmful. But I'm thinking if you got, like, some serious medical question, or whatever, I'm not sure I would trust a nonhuman."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:33:46.794000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. So for simple things like finding a cat house, it's not a big worry. But for anything serious, like medical questions, you'd wanna rely on something someone you fully understand. When you see an AI summary, or answer pop up in your results, what kind of feelings or thoughts usually come up?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:34:07.704000Z",
        "message": "Well, I I can't say of any time that I've ever seen the AI I I don't know when I've ever used AI on purpose, so I can't say what it looked like. I'm sorry."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:34:20.644000Z",
        "message": "No worries at all. It sounds like you're not always sure when AI is working behind the scenes. And you steer clear of tools that are clearly labeled as AI just to be safe. Over the past year or so, would you say the way you look things up online has changed at all? Maybe new habits, tools, or routines compared to before?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:34:39.974000Z",
        "message": "Nope. Everything's the same."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:34:43.404000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Pretty steady habits then. Quick question. Have friends or coworkers ever mentioned using those AI tools? Or"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:34:52.054000Z",
        "message": "I'm sure if you heard me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:34:55.963000Z",
        "message": "I heard you. You said everything stayed the same. And you haven't changed how you look things up. To check-in, have friends or coworkers ever talked about using AI tools like ChatGPT Gemini, or anything different from regular Google search. Or does that not come up in conversations?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:35:14.033000Z",
        "message": "No. I don't have any coworkers. So it does not come up in my business. And I I can't think of any time that I ever talked to my friends about AI. It just sounds too serious. I don't talk about serious stuff with my friend. Sounds silly, it?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:35:35.764000Z",
        "message": "Not silly at all. Makes sense that AI isn't really a topic among friends. Especially if it feels kind of serious or technical. Last thing, thinking about Google search. If you imagine Google as a person at a party, what's what's their vibe or personality like?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:35:52.024000Z",
        "message": "A know it all. Somebody that knows everything that you'd ever need to know. So I'm gonna say they would they'd be a a know it all person."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:03.384000Z",
        "message": "That's a great image. Google as the know it all at the party. If you picture ChatGPT or any of those AI tools as a person at the same party, what kind of vibe do you think they'd have? Even if you don't use them much?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:17.993000Z",
        "message": "I would think they would have a square head with antennas coming out. Because I don't know where they're getting their information that is coming out of their mouth. So they look like an alien to me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:32.114000Z",
        "message": "Love that visual. AI is the square headed alien at the party. Kinda mysterious, not really fitting in. Thanks for sharing that. That covers everything I wanted to ask. Before we wrap up, any thoughts about this AI interview experience? And you can end the call whenever you'd like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e1d834184d944dd38ed1965d5",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:36:50.254000Z",
        "message": "No. It's actually been kind of enjoyable, but it think kinda silly to be talking to a nonhuman. But no, not nothing really Just kinda silly, I guess. But I've enjoyed it. Thank you very much."
      }
