        "message": "I get it. So seeing consistent answers across a few different sites helped you feel more confident. Uh, was there anything about"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1e86c901065401f9dde2e2bb",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:31:49.766000Z",
        "message": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1e86c901065401f9dde2e2bb",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:31:50.976000Z",
        "message": "the way Google organized those results or maybe the info in those little summaries or boxes at the top. That made the process easier or harder for you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1e86c901065401f9dde2e2bb",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:32:00.406000Z",
        "message": "Think I made it pretty easy. I just pick the ones at the top and work my way down."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1e86c901065401f9dde2e2bb",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:32:06.076000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. That's straightforward. When faced with something really important and accuracy matters, do you ever use any AI driven answer engines like Chess GPT, Perplexity, or Gemini instead of Google? If so, what's that experience like for you? If not, what's held you back from trying them?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1e86c901065401f9dde2e2bb",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:32:24.096000Z",
        "message": "I'm kinda old school, so I just use Google. I'm not really familiar with all them yet."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1e86c901065401f9dde2e2bb",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:32:30.616000Z",
        "message": "Makes a sense. So for you, Google feels familiar and reliable. If you imagine those newer AI engines, like ChatGPT or Perplexity, what comes to mind about them even if you haven't really used them? Any impressions, feeling"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1e86c901065401f9dde2e2bb",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:32:42.526000Z",
        "message": "Are you checked? PT in college a little bit for some schoolwork. So other than that, I've really never used it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1e86c901065401f9dde2e2bb",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:32:54.535000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate that. Thinking about those times you used ChatGPT for schoolwork, can you tell me about 1 specific example? What kind of taps did you use it for? And how did it feel compared to"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1e86c901065401f9dde2e2bb",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:33:03.726000Z",
        "message": "It's you. Help research a project. For a criminal justice class."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1e86c901065401f9dde2e2bb",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:33:12.915000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. Walk me through that experience. Starting from when you decided to use chat"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1e86c901065401f9dde2e2bb",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:33:15.356000Z",
        "message": "It was good."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1e86c901065401f9dde2e2bb",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:33:18.466000Z",
        "message": "what part of using ChatGPT for your criminal justice project felt most helpful or stood out most?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1e86c901065401f9dde2e2bb",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:33:25.706000Z",
        "message": "I gotta go green on it. So definitely need the correct information."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1e86c901065401f9dde2e2bb",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:33:31.386000Z",
        "message": "Totally get that. The need for accuracy. When you use ChatGPT for that project, did you do anything to check the info it gave you? Like cross checking with other sources, or did you mainly rely on what it provided?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1e86c901065401f9dde2e2bb",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:33:43.716000Z",
        "message": "I just relied on it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1e86c901065401f9dde2e2bb",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:33:48.676000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for being honest about that. Comparing Google and ChatGPT, does 1 feel more trustworthy or reliable to you, or is it pretty much the same? Depending on, uh, what you're searching for?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b1e86c901065401f9dde2e2bb",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:34:00.926000Z",
        "message": "Pretty much the same."
      },
