        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:12.116000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. Let's jump in. When you need answers online, maybe to settle a random question or help you with something, what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:22.286000Z",
        "message": "Go on Google search."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:25.206000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Walk me through your typical process when you use Google Search to look something up. Uh, just the steps you follow. From the moment you think of the question."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:35.026000Z",
        "message": "Going on Google. Then typing it in."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:39.606000Z",
        "message": "Straightforward. After you type in your question, what do you look at first on the results page? Are you reading snippets clicking links, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:51.616000Z",
        "message": "I read 2 different snippets and click different links."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:56.956000Z",
        "message": "Nice. So you kinda scan a couple of snippets, and then dig deeper if needed. Last time you did this, what kind of question or task were you looking up? Can you walk me through that moment? A bit more detail?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:11.586000Z",
        "message": "A a recipe."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:14.695000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. So you searched for a recipe. Can you tell me step by step how that played out? For example, what did you type? What did you see? And how did you decide which results to click?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:28.736000Z",
        "message": "A tomato macaroni. And I looked for the ones that had my dietary restrictions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:36.226000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. When you were scanning those results for tomato macaroni recipes that fit your dietary restrictions, what helped you figure out which ones were worth clicking? Was it something in the snippet, a familiar website, or something else? Are you still there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:59.575000Z",
        "message": "Still there? Yeah. Did you hear me?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:02.536000Z",
        "message": "Yep. I can hear you just fine. For checking. So thinking back to those tomato macaroni recipe results, what usually catches your eye? Is it keywords about your restrictions, site names you trust, ratings, photos, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:17.956000Z",
        "message": "Just checking different links and see if I seeing which ones have our best dietary needs."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:26.256000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Mostly clicking around and scanning until you spot something that matches what you need. Thinking about that experience, what parts felt helpful? Was there anything annoying or time consuming about it?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:38.606000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. Sure. Less time consuming."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:42.236000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. So in general, the process feels pretty quick. And you get what you need. There anything that could make it even smoother or save you more time when you search for answers or recipes?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:55.286000Z",
        "message": "No. It was pretty easy."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:58.066000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Google's working well for you right now. Do you ever use any other tools or sites, like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini when you're searching for answers? Or is it pretty much always Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:25:10.046000Z",
        "message": "The APT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:25:12.995000Z",
        "message": "Just to make sure I understand, by APT, did you mean ChatGPT? Or are you referring to a different tool? Can you can you tell me a bit more about when you'd reach for that instead of Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:25:25.085000Z",
        "message": "When I'm doing work asana."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:25:31.656000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So you use ChatGPT or a similar AI tool when you're working, uh, in Asana. Can you walk me through a moment when you last used it there? What kind of task were you handling? And how did the AI engine help?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:25:48.416000Z",
        "message": "I had to write an essay about what I think my business needs and I use Jack PT to help me put my words together."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:05.176000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate the details. Starting from that, essay task, you tell me step by step how you used ChatGPT? For example, what did you type or ask it? How did its answer help you? Did you go back and tweak what it gave you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:18.396000Z",
        "message": "Were away that my company can retain customers?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:23.646000Z",
        "message": "Got it. You asked ChatGPT for ways your company could retain customers. When it gave you its answers, how did you decide which points to use? Did you feel confident in what ChatGPT came up with? Or did you double check anything elsewhere?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:39.166000Z",
        "message": "I double checked on Google search, and then it it resonated with me, so I kept it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:45.796000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful. So you used ChatGPT to get ideas, but then and checked Google to confirm or add context. What about the way ChatGPT presents answers? Does it feel different from what you get on Google? Anything stand out about style, depth, or usefulness?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:27:03.326000Z",
        "message": "Some more realistic Talk to you more like you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:27:08.055000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So ChatGPT's style feels a little more realistic and conversational. Almost like speaking to a person. Does that help you feel more comfortable or confident in in the advice it gives? Or do you still lean on Google? For that final sense of trust?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:27:26.976000Z",
        "message": "Trust that chat GPT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:27:31.136000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. When you think about sharing answers with someone else, say, um, passing along advice from ChatGPT or Google, whose answer feels more credible to quote to others, or does it depend on the situation? Are you still there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:27:57.166000Z",
        "message": "Stay single, but Stay single."
      },
      {
        "callId": "f02636f8ee74439885b6ec5e4",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:28:01.556000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for that. You're keeping it simple. Just to clarify, when it comes to trusting or sharing info from these tools, are you saying you usually just stick with what you find most helpful? Regardless of the source? Or do you think about where the answer came from before sharing it?"
      }
