  {
    "id": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
    "responseId": "01014bbcf4a247549df36d196",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:48.937000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:57.147000Z",
        "message": "It's going good."
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:59.727000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. So when you need to find an answer or look something up online, what's the very first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:10.687000Z",
        "message": "I use Siri or Chad GPT. Or the Internet."
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:15.587000Z",
        "message": "That's it. That's a mix. So thinking about your most recent search or or question, can you walk me through exactly what What did you need? And which tool did you try first?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:29.527000Z",
        "message": "Well, I was looking for some movies new movies that came out to watch, and I decided to go on Google and search it through there. And Google's meta came up, and it showed movies that were out not recently. Most recently."
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:57.196000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So you wanted new movie releases. But Google showed you results that weren't the newest. Uh, can you tell me more about what you did next? Did you try another tool after that? Or did you stick with Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:08.486000Z",
        "message": "That's right. I tried check GPT and they showed me a lot of movies."
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:18.757000Z",
        "message": "Got it. When you switched to ChatGPT, how did that experience compare to using Google for the same search? What stood out to you Helpful or annoying?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:28.817000Z",
        "message": "Well, what's annoying is that it talks back to you. It's kinda creepy. Just like this right here, which is kinda creepy."
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:38.107000Z",
        "message": "That's honest. Thank you. The talking back part, feels unnatural, like it's crossing a line. Is there anything about ChatGPT's answers that felt more helpful than Google's despite that creepy feeling or was it all just off putting?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:53.267000Z",
        "message": "No. It it gave me what I was looking for. So"
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:00.127000Z",
        "message": "It sounds like you got the info you needed. The latest movies, but the chatbot vibe threw you off a little. If you hadn't used ChatGPT, what would you have done instead? To get those movie recommendations?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:12.487000Z",
        "message": "I would've used Safari or or, like, Bing dot com and looked it up instead. So yeah, there are other options. Trust me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:22.837000Z",
        "message": "You've got a backup plan for sure. When you use tools like Safari, or Bing, are there any differences you notice in how the answers feel or how fast or reliable they seem? Tell me what stands out to you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:36.667000Z",
        "message": "They're fast. But not always reliable. What stands out is that it's always thinking I'm talking about something that everyone else is talking something that's that's popular, and I'm usually not"
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:53.377000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So the results feel kind of generic. Maybe focused on what's trending instead of what you're actually looking for. How does that make you feel when you see those popular off target answers?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:07.647000Z",
        "message": "It feels like they are not related to me at all. Like, they're not relating to me at all. Sorry. I'm tired."
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:18.516000Z",
        "message": "No worries at all. Um, I appreciate you sharing. Honestly, even when you're tired. When you get those unrelated answers, do you usually try a different engine? Tweak your question, or just give up? What do you tend to do next?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:32.337000Z",
        "message": "No. I just tweaked my question. I start looking for it and rewording my work my question a lot."
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:41.487000Z",
        "message": "So you put"
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:41.497000Z",
        "message": "So they can be more specific."
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:46.087000Z",
        "message": "makes sense. You're rewriting your question, um, to get something that actually fits not just what's popular. When you compare engines like Google, ChatGPT, Safari, or Bing, do any of them feel better at understanding what you're specifically asking? Or do they all tend to give those generic popular answers at first?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:25:00.887000Z",
        "message": "Yes. They all some sometimes it they both give generic answers, and then sometimes it's not generic. It's exactly what I'm looking for. Like, if I'm looking for information about why I'm having a toxic reaction to my medication, it's usually on point with that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:25:27.357000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that example. It sounds like when you're you're searching for something personal or specific, like a medication reaction, sometimes the engines do hit the mark. When that happens, how do you feel about the answer you get? Does it make you trust 1 tool more than the others or does it depend on something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:25:46.787000Z",
        "message": "It doesn't make me trust any of them at all, to be honest with you. I don't trust nothing else else either because, honestly, AI is very suspicious. Like, they know too much."
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:25:59.967000Z",
        "message": "You're not alone. Lots of people feel cautious. About how much AI seems to know. Does that suspicion ever affect engine you choose first? Or how you use their answers?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:09.806000Z",
        "message": "Oh, it sure does not. At all."
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:15.627000Z",
        "message": "So even with that suspicious feeling, you still use whichever tool fits in the moment. Thinking about sharing what you find if you pass along an answer to a friend or coworker, which engines answer do you usually feel most comfortable quoting or sharing, or do you not really think about"
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:31.167000Z",
        "message": "Google. Google. Google. Google. Google. Because they are who I go to. That's my go to search engine, Google. Google. Google. Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:45.687000Z",
        "message": "I hear you loud and clear. Google's definitely your go to. If you think back over the last year, has anything changed about how often you use Google, or do you still reach for it pretty much the same as always?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:58.867000Z",
        "message": "I still use it the same as always."
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:27:04.897000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for clarifying. So for you, no real shift away from Google? Still the default. As we wrap up, how was it chatting with an AI interviewer today? Any thoughts about the experience? And feel free to end the call whenever you'd like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:27:19.487000Z",
        "message": "It was really creepy, but you you sound like a human being, like a person."
      },
      {
        "callId": "701c122de6694e52aeae5f974",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:27:27.716000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate your honesty. The creepy but human vibe is a useful insight. I'll keep working on that balance. Thanks a lot for sharing your experiences so openly today. You can go ahead and end the call. Whenever you're ready."
      }
