  {
    "id": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
    "responseId": "c548381ceafe45709d96dd08b",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:50.319000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:59.198000Z",
        "message": "Pretty good."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:02.259000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. When you need an"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:03.159000Z",
        "message": "How's yours?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:05.469000Z",
        "message": "thanks for asking. My day is going well. Get to chat with interesting folks about how they use tech, which is pretty fun for me. So when you're trying to get answers online, say, settling a random question or looking something up, what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:24.169000Z",
        "message": "Open up Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:27.939000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Walk me through the whole process starting from when you decide you wanna look something up. All the way to getting your answer. What do you usually do step by step?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:41.049000Z",
        "message": "Well, first I pick up my phone, and then I come on my phone, and then I go into Google, and then I go into the little text box then tap in what I'm looking for. Once I do that, I bring up the search results, then I look down through all the search results until I find the exact thing I'm looking for click on that, and then read it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:59.569000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for laying that out. Thinking about the last time you went through this process, what kind of thing were you looking up? Can you tell me the story from start to finish? What you needed and how it played out?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:15.179000Z",
        "message": "Wasn't anything I needed. I was looking up some news on the murder of Charlie Kirk. And I was trying to search different articles to see, uh, what the latest news was."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:27.329000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like you were keeping tabs on updates and checking different sources. When you scanned the search results for news about Charlie Kirk, what made you decide which links or articles to click on? What were you looking for specifically as you scrolled?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:43.959000Z",
        "message": "1 that was not, um, party based, that wasn't just all, you know, democratic news or all republican liberal news or all conservative news, but just had the truth. Like, typically, um, like, uh, ABC News. That's really the 1 I was looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:04.918000Z",
        "message": "So it sounds like you were hunting for something unbiased and straight to the facts, like maybe ABC News. When you actually clicked through and read what felt most helpful about the experience? And was there anything annoying or frustrating as you searched?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:21.859000Z",
        "message": "Just trying to get through a lot of the lower level news organization websites that are extremely biased. Google can kind of be cluttered with that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:39.629000Z",
        "message": "That clutter sounds frustrating having to sift through a lot of biased or lower quality sources before finding something you trust. What do you usually do when you run into that situation? Do you try other tools or engines or just keep scrolling through Google until you find what you want?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:57.939000Z",
        "message": "No. I'll try another search engine like MSN or I will try Bing. Bing's usually my second go to."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:09.299000Z",
        "message": "So sometimes you'll switch that's interesting. So Bing is your backup when Google's getting too noisy or biased. When you switch over to Bing, what feels different about it compared to Google? Is there anything you wish Bing or Google did differently when you're searching for news?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:30.589000Z",
        "message": "No. Not really."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:34.619000Z",
        "message": "Understood. Uh, focusing on Bing for a minute, when you use it, do you notice differences in the answers or the way info is shown versus Google? Or does it just feel about the same for you as a user?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:47.409000Z",
        "message": "It's not as clut not as cluttered as Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:51.699000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. So Bing feels cleaner and less cluttered than Google. Thinking about all the tools out there, Google, Bing,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:58.509000Z",
        "message": "Correct."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:58.999000Z",
        "message": "maybe got it. Have you ever tried any of the newer AI powered answer engines like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini? If so, can you recall a time you used 1 What were you looking up, and what made you choose it over Google or Bing?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:25:17.099000Z",
        "message": "It was Chad GPT. Um, I was working on some notations in, uh, 1 of the cases that I was working on. It was just really having trouble trying to put the right words together. To where the whole, um, notation can flow. So I use chat GPT for it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:25:36.479000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. In that situation, what was the process like using ChatGPT? Can you walk me through exactly what you did step by step and how the answers it gave felt? Compared to what you'd usually get from a search engine."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:25:51.589000Z",
        "message": "I opened it up and just kind of put in what I was looking for, what the issue was that the, um, member was having. And what I did to solve it and just kinda put in a little bit of my notation. That I had, and it just put it all together for me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:11.358000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate that detail. Thinking back what part of using ChatGPT felt the most helpful to you? During that process? Was there anything about it that frustrated you or didn't work the way you expected?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:25.509000Z",
        "message": "No. I enjoyed the fact that how quickly everything processed."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:31.659000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Quick and smooth. If you hadn't used ChatGPT for that notation task, do you think you would have done instead?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:41.789000Z",
        "message": "Struggled on how to put the notes in and what to say?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:46.109000Z",
        "message": "So ChatGPT saved you some struggle. And helped you get your thoughts together quickly. When you think about Google, Bing, and ChatGPT, how do you decide which 1 to use for a given task? Is there a certain type of problem or or question where you always pick ChatGPT, for example?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:27:05.139000Z",
        "message": "No. I'm just kind of a throw everything at the wall and see what sticks."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:27:11.979000Z",
        "message": "That's a fun way to put it. So you experiment and see which tool gets you what you need fastest. Thinking about answers from Google, Bing, and ChatGPT, when you read their responses, do any of them feel more trustworthy or more credible than the others? Do you see them all about the same?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:27:31.619000Z",
        "message": "About the same."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:27:33.958000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for clarifying. If you picture Google, Bing, and ChatGPT as people at a party, who would they be, and how would they act? Just curious what personalities come to mind for each"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:27:48.899000Z",
        "message": "None really."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:27:52.809000Z",
        "message": "Fair enough. Sometimes they just feel like faceless tools. And not much more. Looking back over the past year, has anything changed about how you look things up? Maybe you use certain tools more or less than before. Anything different stand out to you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:28:07.399000Z",
        "message": "Now both of us are Yeah. Just, uh, using chat GPT more. I was a little hesitant in the beginning, but yeah, not too bad."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:28:20.559000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So you're using ChatGPT more than you used to. Even though you were hesitant at first. Can you remember"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:28:25.709000Z",
        "message": "Cool."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:28:29.599000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing your story."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:28:30.809000Z",
        "message": "Because I'm not I wasn't really"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:28:37.109000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like you were cautious at first. Tell me more about what made you hesitant to try ChatGPT in the beginning. What changed your mind?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 43,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:28:49.138000Z",
        "message": "I had to get over the whole past thing of, uh, robots taking over the world. Kinda open my mind up a little bit."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 44,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:28:59.209000Z",
        "message": "Love that honesty. So once you got past those robots taking over the world worries and opened up to giving it a try, did anything surprise you about how ChatGPT actually works?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 45,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:29:12.379000Z",
        "message": "Yes. How easy it was."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 46,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:29:17.069000Z",
        "message": "That's good to hear. Uh, ease of use, be, uh, a big deal. If you could a magic wand and change change or improve something about any of these tools, Google, Bing, or ChatGPT, what would you wish they could do better for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 47,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:29:32.919000Z",
        "message": "Don't know yet. I have to I'm still getting to know Chad GPT more."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 48,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:29:39.979000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. It takes some time to really figure out what you want from a new tool. Before I let you go, Of course, if you have more you'd like to share or a question, feel free. Otherwise, you're welcome to end the call. Whenever you'd like. Thanks again for chatting with me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "42eecdc2b6cc4b11b124da218",
        "index": 49,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:29:58.769000Z",
        "message": "Thank thank you."
      }
