  {
    "id": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
    "responseId": "37a7c49e44334854ad9c2b8fe",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:05.500000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:13.600000Z",
        "message": "It's going good. How about for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:16.980000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear. It's going good. I don't have a day quite like yours. But I'm excited to dig in and learn from you. Let's kick things off. When you need answers online, what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:29.839000Z",
        "message": "I Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:33.830000Z",
        "message": "Got it. You go straight to Google, Can you walk me through what that looks like? For you? Say you've got a question in mind. What's your typical process? From start to finish?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:45.460000Z",
        "message": "Basically, I will open up my browser on my phone or on my computer. I will type in my question and, typically, the results generate within a few seconds, and I get an AI overview on Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:06.710000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for laying that out. When those AI overviews show up, what do you usually do next? Do you tend to read the summary, go into the website links, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:17.660000Z",
        "message": "I turn read them. And if I need further information, I will go into the link"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:31.720000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Thinking about the last time you did this was the question you looked up? Could you walk me through exactly what you needed, what you typed, and how you decided whether the answer was good enough or if you needed to dig deeper?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:47.390000Z",
        "message": "I googled gallstones. For personal medical reasons. And more or less, I got my answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:00.910000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. When you saw, uh, the AI overview for gallstones, what about it felt most helpful for you? And was there anything in that experience that frustrated or annoyed you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:13.250000Z",
        "message": "More or less, I wanted to know if they require surgery. Um, and I was I was okay with the answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:25.610000Z",
        "message": "Understood. You were mainly after whether surgery is needed. Um, did you feel confident with the AI summaries answer? Or did you end up checking any of the linked sources or looking for more details after reading reading it?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:39.150000Z",
        "message": "I if I remember correctly, I believe I I recall checking out other links as well."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:47.930000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. What was the reason for, uh, for checking those other links? Were you hoping to find something more specific? Looking to confirm the info, or was there another reason?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:58.950000Z",
        "message": "I was looking for something more specific just to rule out any possibilities."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:05.240000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So having that next layer of detail mattered to you. When you're looking for more specifics or confirmation, you ever use answer engines besides Google, like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini? Or do you tend to stick with Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:20.930000Z",
        "message": "I typically tend to stick to Google, but in the past, I have used AI such as, ChatGPT and DeepSeek."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:32.810000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. You've tried ChatGPT and DeepSeek in the past. Can you think of a time when you chose 1 of those instead of Google? What was the situation? And what made you reach for a different tool?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:44.420000Z",
        "message": "Chat out yes. I used DeepSeek to generate an outline, uh, or basically a study guide for myself."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:57.890000Z",
        "message": "Nice. Using DeepSeek for a study guide, is a good example. Can you tell me the full story of that time? What did you need? What did you ask DeepSeek? And how did the experience compare to doing something similar with Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:12.840000Z",
        "message": "Due to the political climate and my lack of knowledge uh, in politics, I wanted a specific guideline that would catch me up to see up to speed so I can better understand what is going on in today's society under this current administration."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:36.500000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. When you ask DeepSeek for that guideline, what stood out to you about the answer you got? Was it the way it was structured? The amount of detail, or something else? And did you feel like you got what you needed? Or did you need to look elsewhere for more context?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:53.960000Z",
        "message": "It was all of the above. It was detailed and thorough more than I expected. And, I didn't mean to I mean, aside from DeepSeek's recommendations on, um, what to read online for myself. I didn't need anything else."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:16.480000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like DeepSeek gave you exactly what you needed. Detailed, thorough, maybe even more than you expected. If you compare that to Google, especially for tasks like making a study guide or or getting up to speed, what feels different? Are there things that each 1 does better or worse for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:35.709000Z",
        "message": "With Google, I believe I would've Google would've provided me with a handful of information. DeepSeek was able to organize that for me so I can better properly do my research and break things down in a a certain time frame."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:00.020000Z",
        "message": "That's a really clear distinction. So DeepSeek organizes and structures info. While Google mainly gives raw sources. When you get answers from DeepSeek or ChatGPT, do you approach those with the same level of trust as answers from Google? Or do you feel differently about accuracy, authority, or bias?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:19.640000Z",
        "message": "Um, it's all programs. So at the end of the day, I view them more or less the same, but, also, I know that I have to go out of my way to make sure that the information that is being provided to me is accurate."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:39.570000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. You see them similarly, but still feel the need. To double check information. So when you're passing info along let's say, sharing an answer with friends or coworkers, is there any engine whose results you feel more comfortable quoting? Or does it not really matter to you which 1 it was?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:57.750000Z",
        "message": "Google. Definitely Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:25:00.900000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So Google answers feel most credible for you to share. What is it about Google that gives you that sense of trust? Is it their reputation? The way sources are shown, or something else? What words or feelings come to mind when you think of Google Answers? Versus ChatGPT or DeepSeek? How do the brands feel different to"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:25:17.870000Z",
        "message": "I think I think more so it's just about re the, uh, it being reliable and also the fact that I'm a long time user, whereas ChatGPT or DeepSeek is newer in the sense when it comes to technology."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:25:39.559000Z",
        "message": "That's really interesting. So Google feels reliable partly because you've used it for so long, and newer engines like ChatGPT or DeepSeek feel well, newer, maybe less proven. If you imagine each engine as a person at a party, who would Google be? And who would ChatGPT or DeepSeek be? What kind of vibe do they give off?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:03.279000Z",
        "message": "Google, I would say, would be the loyal information, and I would consider"
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:16.890000Z",
        "message": "I'm intrigued. Google's the loyal information. Who would ChatGPT or DeepSeek be in this party scenario? What kind of personalities do they have compared to Google? Are you still there? Feel free to ask me any questions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:47.890000Z",
        "message": "I don't have any questions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:50.860000Z",
        "message": "No worries. I appreciate you sharing your stories and perspectives. It's really helpful. Before we wrap up, how was this interview experience for you? Anything you wish these AI engines could do better for you in the future. And just letting you know, you can end the call whenever you'd like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:27:10.710000Z",
        "message": "This this survey, it was interesting. I like the voice AI. Approach. I hope to see more of these type of surveys. In the future."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:27:26.519000Z",
        "message": "That's really great to hear. Thanks so much for your honesty and for taking the time. Perspective is valuable. Wishing you a good rest of your day. You're welcome to end the call whenever you're ready."
      },
      {
        "callId": "2de10ec9e8664923864355586",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:27:39.390000Z",
        "message": "Thank you. Goodbye."
      }
