  {
    "id": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
    "responseId": "ffe9c914f660428686212cd54",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:12.408000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:20.288000Z",
        "message": "Great. Hello?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:23.857000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear hello. Glad to hear your day is going well."
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:26.648000Z",
        "message": "Hello?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:27.998000Z",
        "message": "So when you're online and need an answer to something, big or small, what's usually the first thing you do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:37.648000Z",
        "message": "I Google it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:40.218000Z",
        "message": "Got it. You start with Google. Can you walk me through your typical process when you're searching for something on Google? What's what's the step by step you usually follow?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:51.318000Z",
        "message": "I usually actually, it's not Google. It's really like Safari because with the iOS, But I usually go to Safari, and then I type it in whenever I need to, and then usually, the answer or whatever pops up in blue they get the top of the screen. So it's really not that hard to know what saying, just get around it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:15.168000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So Safari is your entry point. And then you type in your question. Or topic right there. When those answers pop up, especially the ones in blue at the top, what makes you decide which link or result to click on first?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:33.468000Z",
        "message": "Usually, the 1 like, a website that I'm there is familiar with or 1 that looks like it states and true to what they say. The answers."
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:46.848000Z",
        "message": "So you're scanning for familiar websites or ones that seem trustworthy. And direct about the answer. Can you tell me about a recent time you did this? What were you searching for and how did you choose which link to click?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:04.988000Z",
        "message": "I really don't remember the last time I had to do anything like that. But like I said, when I usually do it, that's what I just told you. That's basically what I do. But I really don't remember a time recently where I did that"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:23.698000Z",
        "message": "No worries. Sounds like it's a pretty routine thing for you. Even if nothing jumps out from lately. When you go through this process, typing a question in Safari, scanning links, what parts of it feel the most helpful or satisfying?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:36.608000Z",
        "message": "with decisive."
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:36.858000Z",
        "message": "Anything about it you ever got it. So having"
