      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:41.258000Z",
        "message": "Basically, when"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:48.438000Z",
        "message": "Could you tell me, um, could you tell me a bit more what does decisive feel like to you in this context? Is it more about finding an answer quickly, or is there something else that makes the experience helpful?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:03.488000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. It's it's really about finding answer quickly. Like I said, when I type the answer in, it usually not the answer. The question in, it usually already, like, pops up in search bar. So that's very helpful. And then when the words are in blue, the answer is in blue, But I said, yeah, that's very helpful to me. And yeah."
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:32.228000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like speed is a big part of why this process works well for you. The quick pop up suggestions and those blue links Is there anything about using Safari and Google like this? That can get frustrating or annoying for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:46.738000Z",
        "message": "Usually, sometimes most of the time, it's great, but there's, a 15 percent chance that I will Google it, and then I have to go on website and all of that, and they still won't tell me the answers. So not always that it pops up in blue. That's really frustrating because when I put the question in, I expect to, you know you know, have the answer already there because it's good cool. But sometimes they just don't have the or maybe maybe the wrong answer. Not that I know what's right and what's wrong. It just to me, it looks wrong or sounds wrong."
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:30.388000Z",
        "message": "You mentioned sometimes the answer doesn't show up right away. Or the blue link isn't helpful, and you end up clicking through. Only to find the site doesn't actually give you what you need or the answer just looks off. When that happens, what do you do next? Do you keep searching a different way, or do you try something else entirely?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:52.688000Z",
        "message": "Usually, I just will click off or I'll probably go to I'll probably go to 1 of those social media apps to see if I could find my answer on there, but most likely, if I'm going to Safari and googling it, I want the answer from them. So I really don't go anywhere else. I just pick off from Google or Safari and go by my day."
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:19.888000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to know. So if Google or Safari's results let you down, you might briefly try social media. But most of the time, go ahead. Feel free to finish your thought. I'm curious what you were about to say."
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:36.657000Z",
        "message": "Oh, I didn't say anything."
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:41.688000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for clarifying. So just to check, do you ever use tools like ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini, or any AI driven answer engines? If Google doesn't give you what you're looking for. Or have those not become part of your routine yet."
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:55.858000Z",
        "message": "No. Those aren't really a part of my routine. I think 1 or 2 times I'm may have went to chat GPT, Just more so they like, are very clear about things. Like, can tell them, like, make this in bold or make like this. Or just put this picture and it'll work out. Russell, hush."
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:23.808000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like you've dabbled with ChatGPT maybe once or twice, mostly for clarity. When you need something specific, like formatting text or handling a picture. It's not regular for answering questions. When you did use ChatGPT, do you remember what the task was? What made you choose it that time instead of Google or Safari?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:45.868000Z",
        "message": "I'm not really sure. When I used it or why I used it. Could you re could you re say that question for me, please?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:56.938000Z",
        "message": "Of course. Can you remember anytime you used ChatGPT even just once? If so, what did you wanna get done? And what made you choose ChatGPT instead of searching on Safari or Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:14.188000Z",
        "message": "T oh, it's still okay. I used ChatGPT because I needed to find some hyperlinks. So the reason why I did that instead of googling it because I still like ChatGB chat GBT will give me a more realistic answer and I can actually like I said, I can actually tell them like, what to do, what to put in bold, um, to do different website, what type of website, website, was that the hyperlinks and all of that. So I feel like it was more useful than Google because I cannot tell Google to do all the but I could tell chat GBT to do all of that, and they would do it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:54.268000Z",
        "message": "That's really interesting. So for tasks like getting hyperlinks with custom formatting, ChatGPT feels more doable. Because you can give it instructions, like asking for bold. Or specifying the type of website. And it listens. With Google, you can't control those details. It just gives you whatever it finds. How did you feel? Using ChatGPT for that compared to your usual Google routine? Was it quicker, more satisfying, or maybe a little confusing?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:25:23.468000Z",
        "message": "It was more satisfying, like I said, because I can tell them what to do, what to put, in certain things, do bullet points, and all of that. So it was very satisfying."
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:25:36.908000Z",
        "message": "So that ability to customize like asking for bullet points or formatting made the experience feel satisfying for you. If you think about the main differences between Google and ChatGPT for getting answers, what words or feelings come to mind for each."
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:25:53.268000Z",
        "message": "Can you re that question, please?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:00.038000Z",
        "message": "Absolutely. When you think about using Google, what words or feelings come to mind? And when you think about using ChatGPT, what words or feelings come to mind?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "76c38231a74a46f295289d4be",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:26:13.138000Z",
        "message": "When I think about Google, I feel I feel like don't know. I really don't have a feeling about Google, but"
      },
      {
