  {
    "id": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
    "responseId": "a71fcee2be27476997663cb11",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:35.300000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:44.050000Z",
        "message": "Good."
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:46.450000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. To start us off, when you need answers, online, what's the first thing you usually do? Just walk me through your typical approach."
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:56.320000Z",
        "message": "I Google whatever I need to know."
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:02.370000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So Google is your first stop when a question pops up. Can you tell me about the last time you looked something up?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:08.580000Z",
        "message": "Today."
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:11.350000Z",
        "message": "Could you walk me through what you needed to know? And every step you took? From the moment you had"
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:18.630000Z",
        "message": "I needed to know about Donald Trump. And what happened on September eleventh. And I just typed in his name and September eleventh."
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:30.200000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Uh, after you typed in those keywords, what did you see on the results page? Did you click any links read summaries, or do anything else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:37.920000Z",
        "message": "I clicked the link, and I found exactly what I was looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:45.170000Z",
        "message": "Nice. Sounds like it was pretty straightforward. Um, was there anything about that experience that felt especially helpful or maybe a little frustrating at any point?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:54.849000Z",
        "message": "Everything went smoothly."
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:59.750000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. When you use Google for answers like this, what's the main thing that keeps it your go to? Is it speed, accuracy, the layout? Or something else entirely?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:09.800000Z",
        "message": "When I look for is something that's in your face exactly what you're looking for, and easy to find."
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:19.940000Z",
        "message": "That's clear. It sounds like you"
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:20.760000Z",
        "message": "That's clear."
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:22.690000Z",
        "message": "I hear you. Having the answer front and center, easy to spot. That clarity matters a lot. Do you ever use any other tools or sites for quick answers? Like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini, or is it pretty much always Google? Feel free to ask me any questions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:50.010000Z",
        "message": "I don't have any questions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:53.730000Z",
        "message": "All good. Thanks for letting me know. So thinking back, has there ever been a time you tried a different answer engine maybe ChatGPT or something similar, for a particular question If yes, what led you to switch that time? If not, what keeps you sticking with Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:12.380000Z",
        "message": "Because Google has everything I need to know They have never let me down, and it's pretty easy to find what you're looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:21.250000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. You trust Google to deliver, and it's always met your needs. When you think about other engines like ChatGPT or Perplexity, even if you haven't used them much, do any words, feelings, or images come to mind? Maybe things you've heard from others?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:36.370000Z",
        "message": "I have heard about it, but I've never used them."
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:42.700000Z",
        "message": "Understood. Thinking back over the past year, has anything changed about how you use Google? Uh, maybe how often you search or what you look up or has it stayed pretty much the same?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:53.150000Z",
        "message": "It stayed pretty much the same. I look up exactly what I wanna know, and I'm satisfied with it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:00.960000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Consistent habits and reliable results for you. If you imagine a scenario where you might try a new answer engine instead of Google, what would have to happen? Any frustrations, new features, or something someone recommended? What would make you consider switching?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:17.850000Z",
        "message": "If I had to switch, I would switch because I wasn't satisfied anymore. But I don't know where I would go to find what I'm looking for yet."
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:30.450000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for spelling that out. So satisfaction is key. As long as Google keeps meeting your needs, you're sticking with it. If things changed, you'd be open, but aren't sure what your next pick would even be. Last quick thing before we wrap. When you share an answer with a friend or coworker, does it matter to you where it came from? Does quoting Google feel more credible? Or is it all about the info itself?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:54.390000Z",
        "message": "It's all about the info. If the info sounds accurate, then it's accurate to me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:02.109000Z",
        "message": "That's super clear. I appreciate you sharing your habits and thoughts. It's really helpful. Before we end, how was chatting with an AI today? Any feedback or final thoughts? And you're free to end the call whenever you'd like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:17.370000Z",
        "message": "I haven't um, I don't have any questions, but thank you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "391142f8fc9c475dafff149fc",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:22.980000Z",
        "message": "Thank you for calling."
      }
