      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:18.595000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:26.935000Z",
        "message": "Pretty good. How about yours?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:29.875000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. My day is going well. Always interesting meeting someone new and hearing about how they use tech. To kick things off, when you need an answer online, what's probably the very first thing you generally do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:44.095000Z",
        "message": "Pardon me?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:47.185000Z",
        "message": "No problem. Let me ask that a bit more simply. When you're looking something up online, what's what's the usual first step for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:55.625000Z",
        "message": "Probably Google search."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:59.245000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So starting with Google search, is a habit for you. Can you walk me through, like, what that process looks like? Step by step from, you know, typing your question to finding your answer?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:12.495000Z",
        "message": "I would type my question. I would hit enter, and then I would choose 1 of the search results."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:22.635000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for laying that out. Thinking about the last time you did this, can you tell me the whole story? What did you need to look up and how did it play out from start to finish?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:36.265000Z",
        "message": "I probably looked up the name of my home newspaper so that I could look through the articles. That would have been this morning. All in all, it would have taken about 5 minutes. From start to finish."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:55.205000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Sounds like it was it was pretty quick. What part of that experience felt most straightforward or helpful for you? And was there anything about it that bugged you or slowed you down?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:09.075000Z",
        "message": "No. It was pretty simple."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:11.805000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Just to check, do you ever use other tools besides Google? Like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini when you're looking for answers online? Or is it mostly Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:24.025000Z",
        "message": "Once in a while, I'll use Meta AI."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:29.754000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. Meta AI comes into play sometimes for you. Can you think of a recent time you chose Meta AI instead of Google? What was the situation, and what made you pick Meta AI that time?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:41.515000Z",
        "message": "Well, lot of times in Facebook, posts, Meta AI will give options for researching the subject a little further. So I like that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:55.495000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful detail. So while you're on Facebook, Meta AI offers some quick ways to dig deeper into a topic right from a post, and you use those options because they're right there. In those moments,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:06.835000Z",
        "message": "Correct."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:09.815000Z",
        "message": "thanks for clarifying. When Meta AI pops up those research options, what feels different about using it compared to doing a regular Google search. Anything stand out about the answers, how you interact, or how the results feel?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:24.864000Z",
        "message": "It does tend to give you questions to click on as options and Google search is more geared towards searching for what you type into the search field"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:44.675000Z",
        "message": "That's a helpful distinction. So with Meta AI, you're guided by preset questions, whereas with Google, you're inputting your own search every time. Do the answers or suggestions you get from Meta AI feel more or less useful than Google's results? Makes you feel that way?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:06.595000Z",
        "message": "Sometimes, and I think that's probably because the Meta AI gives questions in a more conversational manner. It gives answers to questions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:20.555000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. You're saying that MetaEye feels more conversational. Presenting things, uh, almost like it's talking with you. Does that tone"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:27.685000Z",
        "message": "Correct. Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:29.855000Z",
        "message": "thanks for confirming. When you get 1 of those 1 of those answers from Meta AI, do you feel more or less or, uh, about equally confident in its accuracy compared to a Google result? Your gut reaction about trust with each?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:47.985000Z",
        "message": "Honestly, I guess I kinda get similar results. From Google or from Meta AI."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:20:58.085000Z",
        "message": "That's good to know. So sounds like you feel both give you about the same level of trustworthiness at least for the kinds of things you're usually searching. If you were to line up Google and Meta AI thinking about how helpful they feel for your typical searches, Which 1 would come first for you? What what puts that ahead? Feel free to ask me any questions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:27.834000Z",
        "message": "Probably Google. Is what I would go to unless it was just I was right there on Facebook and it was easier, but mostly I go to Google first."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:21:43.374000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. That makes sense. So Google's your go to. Unless Meta AI happens to be right in front of you when you're on Facebook. Thinking back over the last year or so, has anything about your search habits changed? Even a little? More often using Meta AI or pretty much the same as always?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:01.525000Z",
        "message": "Pretty much the same."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:05.894000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So no big shifts for you lately. When you're searching or sharing info with someone else, say, sending a link or passing along an answer, do you feel more comfortable sharing something from Google, Meta AI, or does it not really matter to you? Are you still there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:29.585000Z",
        "message": "Probably more comfortable with Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:34.525000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. When you think about Google's answers, uh, or results, what words or or feelings come to mind? And how about for Meta AI? Any different associations or emotions there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:22:48.935000Z",
        "message": "Well, like I said, Meta AI does feel like a person talking to you and Google kind of just lists the top you know, search results."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:02.704000Z",
        "message": "That's a clear way to put it. So Meta AI sort of talks with you. And feels more conversational, while Google is more of an organized list or directory. Do you think 1 feels more credible or official? Or do you just see them as serving different styles?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:20.365000Z",
        "message": "I think they serve different styles."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:24.775000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate your take on that. Just to wrap up, is there anything you wish these answer engines could do better? Any features or changes that would make searching for answers online smoother or more useful for you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:43.124000Z",
        "message": "At the moment, I can't think of anything."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:23:47.714000Z",
        "message": "That's totally fair. Thanks for sharing your stories and thoughts today. Um, it's been genuinely interesting hearing how you navigate these tools. Before we end, how did you find talking with an AI about your search habits? Anything you'd like me to know about the interview experience itself, and you're welcome to end the call whenever you're ready."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:10.825000Z",
        "message": "It was very friendly and conversational."
      },
      {
        "callId": "70ea61a22ed044ccbb5f5fe75",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:24:15.185000Z",
        "message": "Thank you for calling."
      }
    ],
