  {
    "id": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
    "responseId": "52aebfb7c77f48c6861b887b5",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:19.601000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:28.131000Z",
        "message": "It's going just fine. Thank you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:31.491000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. To start off, when you're looking for, uh, answers, online, what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:39.641000Z",
        "message": "I open up Google. And type in what I'm looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:44.751000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So Google is usually your starting point. Walk me through what happens next. After you enter your search, what do you typically do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:53.900000Z",
        "message": "I read the summary of the item that I'm looking for or the information. And then I will scroll to find which 1. Sometimes I have to click on images to actually see the picture of the item."
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:11:14.391000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. That's super clear. Thinking back to the last time you did this, what kind of answer information were you looking for? Can you tell me the story of that specific search starting with what triggered it and what steps you took?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:11:27.800000Z",
        "message": "I was actually looking for different board games that my husband and I could play. So I typed in classic board games. And started the process from there."
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:11:44.211000Z",
        "message": "Nice. You searched for classic board games, what did your results look like? And how did you decide which ones to click or read?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:11:54.131000Z",
        "message": "It was actually overwhelming. It came up a whole bunch of games board games. So I narrowed down my search to the game trouble. And was looking for different places to buy other than Walmart and Amazon."
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:12:15.681000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. Sounds like there was a flood of options at first. When you narrowed your search, to trouble, and places besides Walmart and Amazon, what helped you decide where to click next? Did anything in the results feel especially helpful or frustrating?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:12:32.491000Z",
        "message": "The visuals were good. And the summary of the products I was actually able to find an old trouble game on Etsy."
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:12:46.601000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So visuals and the summaries played a big part. And Etsy popped up as a helpful find. Was there anything about using Google in that moment that felt annoying or, like, extra work? You wish could have been less frustrating or or or more straightforward?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:13:04.031000Z",
        "message": "No. Google usually is my go to because I can click on type in something in the search engine and then usually, that gives me, like, the top 10 most places to look for that information. I use sometimes also use Pinterest and with the visuals on there, it also gives me clear examples of information I'm looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:13:33.941000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful. So Google is your main go to. But you'll switch to Pinterest for even more visual sometimes. Thinking about other answer engines like ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini, do you ever use any of those, or do you mostly stick with Google and Pinterest?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:13:49.621000Z",
        "message": "No. I use my Siri a lot. Especially when my hands are full. And I'm looking for, like, a quick measurement or to set my timer or to search where to find the best air fryer recipe for chicken."
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:06.291000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate that detail. So Siri comes in handy when you need quick answers. Especially if you're multitasking or looking for something like a recipe or measurement. When you use Siri, is there anything about the way it responds speed, tone, accuracy, that stands out compared to Google or Pinterest. It ever feel more helpful, less helpful, or just different?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:30.231000Z",
        "message": "It feels more diff different However, sometimes she doesn't understand me. I'd like to use the chat or something else besides Siri. To find the answers. However, I don't know if I have to open the app in order to get into it. And most of the times, my hands are pretty full."
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:52.371000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So series quick and hands free, but sometimes misses what you mean. You'd actually be interested in trying chat based tools, but juggling devices or opening apps makes it tricky when you're busy. Thinking about the answers you get, from each Google, Pinterest, Siri, do any feel more trustworthy or For example, if you were sharing info with someone else, which one's answer would you feel most confident quoting?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:15:20.571000Z",
        "message": "I would probably if I had to order them, put them in order of usefulness, I would go Google, Pinterest, then Siri. However, I do think it applies to the situation. When I'm looking for different information about arts and crafts projects. I go straight to Pinterest because, uh, that's more of a straightforward area to look for it. If I need something more broad, I'll use Google. And for something quick that I think Siri can can find, I'll use her. So I think it's more of the situation."
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:15:59.681000Z",
        "message": "Super clear. So it's a mix depending on what you need. Google for a broad info, Pinterest for visual or craft ideas, Siri for quick hands free stuff. Thinking about these tools as personalities, if Google, Pinterest, and Siri were people at a party, what kind of vibe would each have? How would you describe what they're like?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:20.821000Z",
        "message": "I would say that Pinterest would be the nerd sitting on the couch. Siri would be social butterfly, and Google would be the 1 just surfing the crowds gathering information."
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:39.051000Z",
        "message": "Love that. Each has a totally different energy, Makes a lot of sense. Looking back over the past year, has anything shifted in which you reach for first, or how often you use Google, Pinterest, or Siri? Uh, maybe even something subtle. Like the way you trust their answers or what you expect from them."
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:57.901000Z",
        "message": "No. I think I used them all same equally. I don't use anything else because Google, Pinterest, and Siri work for me in those situations that I need them. So I haven't been able I I haven't wanted to look for something better because I think those are sufficient enough."
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:19.861000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. It sounds like the mix you use fits your needs well enough that you haven't felt any urge to branch out. Is there anything you wish 1 of these could do better? Maybe a feature or a way answers show up that would make your experience smoother or save you effort? Or has it been pretty much good as is?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:41.041000Z",
        "message": "I wish that Siri would explain things better instead, I mean, for me to click on, uh, 1 of the stories. Say, I'm looking for a recipe, and she'll say, here are several different recipes to click on. So I don't I wish it was more it could take me directly to a site."
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:07.341000Z",
        "message": "That's a really clear wish. Wanting Siri to explain things more fully. Just take you directly to the site. Rather than giving several options. If a new tool came out that solved that friction, say hands free, quick answers, and effortless jump straight Chat to details. Do you think you'd try it, or would that mostly depend on what your friends or family suggest?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:29.221000Z",
        "message": "Oh, no. Most definitely. I would try it. If it would simplify you know, researching something, simplify it and make it quicker, it would give me more time to do something else instead of researching an answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:45.861000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Saving time is a big motivator. That's really helpful to know. Before we wrap up, how was chatting with an AI moderator today? Anything you'd change or suggest to make the conversation better? You're welcome to"
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:18:58.011000Z",
        "message": "No. I actually have enjoyed this very much and would take more surveys like this. I like to explain things in detail, and sometimes it's hard to type I'm using my phone for surveys."
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:16.551000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate that. For sharing so much detail. Glad this style worked well, um, for you. You're all set on my end. And you can end the call whenever you'd like. Have a great rest of your day."
      },
      {
        "callId": "af7164cb14a94f98b5e1ab8c6",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:19:29.191000Z",
        "message": "Thank you. You too."
      }
