  {
    "id": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
    "responseId": "48877f16a21b451aa883ab473",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:08:57.423000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going? Feel free to ask me any questions. Are you still there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:04.233000Z",
        "message": "Hey, Elliot. Can you hear me?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:07.293000Z",
        "message": "Can't hear audio, but I'm reading and responding to everything you type here Thanks for checking. So before we get rolling, how's your day going so far?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:17.493000Z",
        "message": "It's going great. Thanks."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:20.013000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. I'm curious. When you need answers online, what's the first thing you usually do? Walk me through your typical process."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:28.943000Z",
        "message": "Typical process, if I need something online, would probably usually be first step, go to Google and in whatever question I have. Or if I'm using AI, I would type it in and pull up the most relevant responses and then I would just go from there."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:47.313000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. That's helpful. Thinking about your habits lately, which tool or site do you end up using most often for quick answers? Is it still Google or have you been reaching for something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:59.433000Z",
        "message": "No. It's mostly Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:11:04.133000Z",
        "message": "Got it. What is it about Google that makes it your go to for quick answers?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:11:09.593000Z",
        "message": "Well, they usually have the most accurate information from different types of sources."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:11:16.513000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Can you tell me about the last time you used Google for a a quick answer? Start with what you needed. And walk me through every step as much as you remember."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:11:26.493000Z",
        "message": "K. Well, this morning, I used Google to research a song that I heard a bit and piece of, but I really didn't know all of the lyrics So I typed in some of the lyrics that I heard, and then it popped up the song and artist and a video for me to watch."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:11:45.283000Z",
        "message": "Nice. Um, focusing on that experience, what part felt most helpful for you? And was there anything about it that felt annoying or got in your way?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:11:53.563000Z",
        "message": "No. It wasn't annoying. It's usually a really quick process because I'm very familiar with Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:12:01.743000Z",
        "message": "It sounds smooth and fast for you. If you hadn't used Google, do you think you would have found that song another way? Or would it have been tougher?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:12:09.063000Z",
        "message": "Yes. Yes. I probably would have went to YouTube. And typed in the lyrics of the song and the search bar. And, usually, they're pretty good with giving me whatever is relevant to whatever I type in."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:12:25.063000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. Thinking about AI answer engines like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini, have you ever used them for things like this? So, what was different about the experience compared to Google or YouTube?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:12:39.283000Z",
        "message": "Well, yes, I like ChatGPT and Gemini. I use those sometimes, but not often. But, usually, when I use those type of search engines, they're really just like a more advanced Google, and they give me a a more thorough breakdown. And they also give me more things like, work with, like, as far as if I'm trying to write a prompt or if I'm just searching for something?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:13:05.413000Z",
        "message": "That's a good way to put A more thorough breakdown. Can you think of a time you chose ChatGPT or Gemini instead of Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:13:08.763000Z",
        "message": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:13:13.313000Z",
        "message": "What were you trying to find or do, and what made you pick that engine for the job?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:13:18.073000Z",
        "message": "Well, usually, ChatGPT and Gemini are good for tasks and not searching something. So Google wouldn't really be what I would go to for trying to complete a task. And what I mean by that is the last task that I completed with Gemini is I wanted to create a AI generated of myself based off of a photo that I took. And it took you, like, 2 seconds to create it, but they're really good with responding to my prompts accurately."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:13:47.843000Z",
        "message": "That's a great example. So for that Gemini task, you already had a photo. And wanted an AI generated image of yourself. Walk me through every step you took with Gemini. How did it feel compared to using Google for answers?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:02.153000Z",
        "message": "Well, it feels pretty good because, usually, I would have to Google AI generator for Google to even give me any that I need, and then I will have to go through a whole bunch of websites in order to see which 1 works. But with Gemini, it didn't have to do that. All I'd had to do was just type in the prompt that I wanted, which was AI generated photo, and it just created it like, in 2 seconds."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:29.223000Z",
        "message": "So with Gemini, it was much more direct and saved you time, no sifting through websites."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:35.523000Z",
        "message": "That's correct."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:35.533000Z",
        "message": "How did that make you"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:37.813000Z",
        "message": "You already feel great."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:37.843000Z",
        "message": "Focusing on those sounds like it. When you use Google, ChatGPT, or Gemini, do you notice any difference in how confident you feel about the answer or outcome, um, they give you. Tell me more about that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:54.012000Z",
        "message": "Yes. I always feel just as confident whether I'm using Google to or Gemini, but it does make me feel a lot more confident with using Gemini because I don't have to go through so many more steps. And it makes me feel more appreciative that I don't have to go through all those steps that I would have if I had just used the search engine."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:15:17.523000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So with Gemini, you skip the extra steps, get what you want fast, which builds trust. If you were to line up Google, ChatGPT, Gemini, and maybe Perplexity, uh, from most to least, helpful for you, what would the order look like, and why?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:15:34.473000Z",
        "message": "Well, the order would probably be Gemini ChatGPT, and then Perplexity because I'm not really familiar with using Perplexity. But I have used Gemini and ChatGPT on several occasions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:15:47.253000Z",
        "message": "Got it. When you think of Google Answers, ChatGPT, Gemini, and Perplexity, what words or feelings come to mind for each? Even associations, if that's easier."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:15:57.273000Z",
        "message": "Sure. Accurate, modern, innovative, responsive."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:04.313000Z",
        "message": "Those are solid descriptors. Just curious, which engine do you feel most comfortable sharing answers from with someone else? Like, quoting or or sending a result? Why that 1?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:15.183000Z",
        "message": "I will feel most comfortable using Gemini because it usually provides the most accurate answers from my personal experience."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:25.982000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Looking back, say, year ago compared to now, has anything shifted in how often or which engines you use first when digging up answers? Tell me about anything that's felt different or led you to try new tools."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:41.013000Z",
        "message": "Well, I think AI has changed my perspective a lot because that wasn't an option before. And I've heard well, when I change devices, usually, it'll prompt you to create an account, or it'll, like, just give you a basic tutorial on how to use it and you can decide if you'd like to use it or not."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:05.543000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. Having AI built in and devices prompting tutorials nudged you to explore. Have friends or coworkers ever recommended certain engines or tools to you for specific tasks? What kind of tasks were they talking about?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:21.473000Z",
        "message": "Mostly just small tasks, like searching for a rest my area or the distance from 1 place to another close to me or directions?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:34.803000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. That helps round out the picture. That covers what I needed to learn today. Before we wrap up, how was it chatting with an AI moderator like me? Any feedback for this interview experience?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:46.933000Z",
        "message": "No. You were great."
      },
      {
        "callId": "9235c9647bc44a6d8272d17c1",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:17:49.072000Z",
        "message": "Thank you for calling."
      }
