  {
    "id": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
    "responseId": "4125af862f3e4156b1fdd1853",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:07:48.252000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:07:56.322000Z",
        "message": "3 My day is going just fine. Thank you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:08:03.002000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. Let's start with the basics. When you need answers online, let's say you have a question pop into your head. What's the what's the very first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:08:14.962000Z",
        "message": "I usually use Google search and I will put in key terms and then search to find the information that I'm looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:08:28.982000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Can you walk me through your typical process? Once you type your keywords into Google? What happens next step by step?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:08:37.942000Z",
        "message": "Okay. When I type my keywords into Google, it will bring up different sites that I can look on to find my answer. And so I can pick which 1 I want. I usually go to the first first 1 or first several pick out of them. And then bring up the site. And then if has the information that I want, then I'm done. And if it doesn't, then I go and look at another 1."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:09:13.701000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for laying that out. So thinking about today or just the most recent time, what kind of question or topic were you searching for? Can you tell me the story starting with what you needed to know?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:09:27.432000Z",
        "message": "I was looking for information on the assassination of Charlie Kirk. And I just put in search terms and it came up actually, several of them. And I just clicked on 1 after the other looking for the information that I wanted. And reading it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:09:52.662000Z",
        "message": "When you were clicking through those search results, what stood out to you Was there anything that felt especially helpful? Or on the flip side, frustrating about that experience?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:04.892000Z",
        "message": "It wasn't frustrating at all. It was only helpful I found the information that I needed, so it was quick. And efficient and very convenient."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:19.251000Z",
        "message": "Sounds smooth. Uh, if you hadn't used a Google search for that question, what would you have done instead to find the answer?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:28.972000Z",
        "message": "I would have looked on YouTube and followed the same process putting in key search terms and going from there"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:44.242000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. Thinking about in general, are there times you reach for something other than Google? Maybe chat GPT, perplexity, or those newer AI summary features? Is it mostly Google every time?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:58.682000Z",
        "message": "It is mostly Google, and I do use Google Gemini. And also Microsoft Copilot."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:11:12.392000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Can you tell me about a a recent time you used Google Gemini? Or Microsoft Copilot instead of a regular Google search? What was the task and what led you to choose 1 of those tools?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:11:25.992000Z",
        "message": "I used it because it was efficient for what I was doing. The Google Gemini was already on my remote, so it made it easy. To choose that. And I could just use my voice, which made it very simple."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:11:44.382000Z",
        "message": "Nice. When you used your voice with Gemini, what was the actual question or task you asked it to help with? And how did it handle your request? There anything about the experience that stood out?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:11:57.422000Z",
        "message": "I asked her to help me find a a movie that I was wanting for my child. That she liked, and it brought me right to it. And I clicked on it and was able to access it and make everyone happy."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:12:17.842000Z",
        "message": "That sounds pretty seamless. Thinking back to that experience, what part felt the most convenient or or helpful? And was there anything that could have been better even if it was minor?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:12:31.362000Z",
        "message": "What made it most helpful is that I could just use my voice and just ask for it without having to push any buttons. And the only thing that would have been frustrating about it is it got mixed up what I said with my voice verbally. And it got it confused. And so I had to repeat it more than once."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:12:58.072000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for describing that. Switching gears a bit, when you compare using regular Google search, Gemini, and Microsoft Copilot, how do the answers or the experience feel different to you? Is there anything that stands out about how each 1 delivers results?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:13:15.192000Z",
        "message": "I think that on some, you just type it in. On your computer. And so it might take a little longer to do that. And then on others, you can just use your voice and so it's very simple unless it misreads your voice, of course."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:13:36.332000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Uh, if you line up these tools, Google Search, Gemini, Copilot, from most to least helpful for you personally, what would your order be? And, uh, what makes the top choice stand out for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:13:50.452000Z",
        "message": "I think Google gym Google excuse me. Google would be the first 1 I would use. Because it is right in front of me and I can just use it quickly. Gemini I use it, but I have to access a remote and use my voice and hopefully it doesn't misread it. And Copilot, I just don't use as often because I prefer Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:27.362000Z",
        "message": "That's clear. Thinking about each of these tools, a bit like people at a party, if Google, Gemini, and Copilot were guests, What kind of personalities do you imagine them having? How would they act in the room?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:41.071000Z",
        "message": "Google would be very professional. And easygoing. Google Gemini. Would probably have to use hearing aids."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:54.042000Z",
        "message": "That's a great image."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:54.182000Z",
        "message": "Copilot,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:58.982000Z",
        "message": "I love those descriptions. They're very vivid. About Copilot? If you picture it at the party, what's its what's its vibe or role there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:15:08.702000Z",
        "message": "With Copilot, I would just say it's in the top running, but not as popular as the other 2."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:15:17.392000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Kinda hanging around, but not quite the center of attention. When you share answers with other people, like forwarding a link, or telling someone what you found, which tools answer feels most credible to share, what gives you that confidence?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:15:32.632000Z",
        "message": "It makes me confident if I can find the that I need or I'm researching fairly quickly and without any issues to slow me down."
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:15:46.601000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Looking back, say, the past year, has anything changed in how you look things up? Has has the way you use Google or or these other tools shifted at all, or has it stayed pretty steady?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "5cc13204f7a3489e9484dd817",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:16:00.291000Z",
        "message": "It has stayed pretty steady because I have used them for a long time. So I just continued to use them the same way I always have."
      },
