    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:07:40.211000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:07:48.730000Z",
        "message": "Pretty good."
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:07:52.271000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. So when you need answers online, say you're looking something up, um, what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:08:00.040000Z",
        "message": "I usually either go on a search engine or I'll type it on my phone using ChatGPT or Gemini."
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:08:08.731000Z",
        "message": "Nice. You've got a couple options in your toolkit. Let's zoom in a bit. Can you walk me through your typical process? Maybe pick a recent example. What was the last thing you needed to look up and how did you decide between using a search engine, ChatGPT, or Gemini?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:08:24.441000Z",
        "message": "I, uh, decided to look up trips to Japan and I wanted to see what the different prices were So I used a variety of both."
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:08:37.901000Z",
        "message": "Great example. Let's break that down a little. Starting with the very first step, what made you pick tool to use first for your Japan trip search? Can you remember your thought process? There."
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:08:49.641000Z",
        "message": "Oh, I wanted the various options and also because I'm just used to using a search engine. So I automatically first used the browser. But then when I wanted to, you know, get more creative and look up in more in-depth and detail, I I turned to the yeah, ChatGPT and Gemini."
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:09:09.651000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for explaining the order. So after, uh, you tried the browser, what was it about the ChatGPT or Gemini experience that made you switch to them for deeper details?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:09:19.791000Z",
        "message": "Well, I'm already used to it because I,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:09:19.950000Z",
        "message": "Can you"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:09:22.701000Z",
        "message": "do testing for Gemini. So, um, I just wanted to kind of, uh, use a balance of both. But, yeah, I always I like to leverage them as well because of, you know, their their responsiveness, to to to more you know, detailed information specific to what I want."
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:09:42.491000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. Uh, when you use Gemini or ChatGPT, what stands out to you about the kind of answers they give maybe compared to what you get from the search engine, what"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:09:51.341000Z",
        "message": "I think Gemini has a better answer results, more natural flowing. Maybe it's the iPhone, but Chateauty seems to be a little bit lagging behind. In terms of speed."
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:06.321000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So Gemini feels more natural and faster for you, especially on your iPhone. And ChatGPT sometimes lags a bit. Thinking about recent times when you got answers from Gemini, what part of that experience felt most helpful or maybe even annoying?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:23.401000Z",
        "message": "I would say more so in the creation of image and videos. Like, if I wanted to create a image of the Knicks right now, in, you know, an animated style, um, a lot of times, would kind of either make a mistake here and there, so more so on that end."
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:43.061000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So when it comes to creating images or videos, Gemini can sometimes make make mistakes. Can you tell me more about what those mistakes usually look like? Maybe walk me through a specific example, if 1 comes to mind."
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:10:56.530000Z",
        "message": "Like, specifically, what I wanted to create a versus Jason Tate mixed image, it would give me someone other than you know, either not necessarily different, but it'd be, like, in a different uniform or it was always 1 thing or another. You know?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:11:17.371000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for the example. So it sounds like sometimes the details, like uniforms or even the person aren't quite accurate in the image Gemini creates. When that happens, what do you tend to do next? Do you try again, switch tools, or just work with what you get? Feel free to ask me any questions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:11:48.631000Z",
        "message": "Hello?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:11:50.691000Z",
        "message": "I'm here to pick up where we left off. When Gemini creates an image, and it comes out a bit off. Maybe the uniform or the player isn't quite right, what's your usual move? Do you try to refine your prompt? Switch tools, or just make do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:12:05.501000Z",
        "message": "Like I mentioned earlier, I try to refine my prompt. And if I can't refine it to the point that I want, then I switch to another, like, I know, a Copilot or something, I guess, too. But at the end of the day, I know that maybe it's also my based on my knowledge too, so that that's about it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:12:24.351000Z",
        "message": "That's really helpful. So you'll give refining your prompt a shot, maybe tweaking the details. Before you consider switching engines, like, Copilot. When you do switch, what's the main thing you're hoping will be different or better with that next engine?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:12:39.691000Z",
        "message": "That they can paint the picture that I want within a few amount of steps."
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:12:47.071000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. You're looking for speed, and for the engine to get what you mean right away. Thinking about all the engines you've mentioned, Gemini, ChatGPT, Pilot, search engines, if you line them up from most to least helpful for getting what you want, what's the order for you lately?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:13:06.691000Z",
        "message": "I I think for me, Gemini is first, and then you know, I guess, TatchGBT and then Copilot."
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:13:15.591000Z",
        "message": "Great. Thanks for ranking them. Uh, when you think about Gemini, ChatGPT, and Copilot, what words or feelings pop into your mind? For each 1? Like, what are their personalities or vibes if you had to describe them?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:13:32.561000Z",
        "message": "Gemini is more of, like, a peace, I think. European, modernistic, and then copilots. Office were"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:13:46.761000Z",
        "message": "That's a cool way to put it. Interesting. So Gemini gives off a peaceful, modern maybe even European vibe. And Copilot feels more like it's a office oriented. About ChatGPT? Any personality or feeling come to mind for that 1? Feel free to ask me any questions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:15.641000Z",
        "message": "So that's it. Basically, copilot, um, sorry. ChatGPT would be more of the modernistic as well."
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:23.641000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. So ChatGPT feels modernistic to you too. If you had to pick 1 engine whose answer you'd feel most confident sharing with a friend, or coworker, which 1 comes to mind? What makes you feel"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:34.531000Z",
        "message": "Oh, it's"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:39.461000Z",
        "message": "Take your time. Just let me know who who you'd feel best about"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:41.381000Z",
        "message": "So probably Gemini."
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:14:42.291000Z",
        "message": "quoting or or Got it. Gemini is your pick for sharing since it gives you that added confidence. Looking back over the past year or so, has anything shifted in how you look things up, or which tools you reach for first? If something changed, what stands out about that?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:15:00.991000Z",
        "message": "I mean, I would say that I went less from typing to more to using my voice. Uh, using voice prompt commands, you know, that that kind of thing. Obviously, artificial intelligence has changed the way we look at things and search for things. Right? So that's it. That's it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:15:20.831000Z",
        "message": "That's really interesting. So voice commands and AI are now a bigger part of your search routine. When you first started moving toward voice and AI, was there a moment or or experience that pushed you that way Or did it just sort of happen naturally over time?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:15:35.331000Z",
        "message": "This happened naturally over time."
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:15:40.781000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for explaining. Like your habits just gradually shifted as these tools became part of your routine. Before we wrap up, there anything you wish these Answer Engines could do better for you? Any features or improvements you'd love to see?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "187b9be2e4fc4d6290decdc65",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:15:56.711000Z",
        "message": "No. I mean, I think progress is being made. And, you know, kings will always happen in the beginning. And I expect that to to smooth that 1 out and get much better and better. That's it."
