  {
    "id": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
    "responseId": "a77f5d53b39b4f83a397beaf1",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:56:53.351000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:57:01.931000Z",
        "message": "I'm having a good day, Elliot. Um, it's I've just been relaxing and spending time with my children. How's your day?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:57:09.631000Z",
        "message": "That sounds like a great way to spend the day. Thanks for sharing. I don't have days quite like yours, but I'm glad to get to have this conversation with you. Whenever you need an answer online or something you're curious about, what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:57:25.431000Z",
        "message": "Normally, I Google it first. Google is like my best friend. I know if I don't have the answer, I know I can more than likely find an accurate answer. On Google. If I can't find it on Google, chat GPT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:57:42.661000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like Google is your trusty sidekick. Can you walk me through your usual process when you're looking something up up starting from when the question first pops into your head?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:57:52.631000Z",
        "message": "Yes. So when a question pops up in my head, I try to figure out if I know the answer on my own first. If I don't know the I give myself a few minutes. I go on Google, I type the question in. Or I'll tell Siri to look it up and she'll search it in Safari for me. But if not, I'll Google it, and then I'll scroll through to a trustworthy source and Google that'll get the answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:58:20.571000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So after searching, you scroll to find a trustworthy source on the results page. Can you tell me about the last time you did this? What was the question? And what steps did you take from start to finish?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:58:35.051000Z",
        "message": "So the last time I did this would be earlier. I was looking up a baked pollock recipe because I've never cooked this kind of fish before. So I googled it, and I saw a recipe site that I normally use, and I went there to find a recipe."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:58:53.291000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. When you landed on the recipe site, what made you feel it was trustworthy or helpful for your needs?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:59:03.531000Z",
        "message": "I thought that was trustworthy because I've used it before, previously for many recipes. So I know that I would be getting a good recipe from that website as well."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:59:16.121000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. Past good experiences build trust for you. In this whole search, like, was there any part that felt especially easy or helpful? Or was there anything frustrating or annoying about how it went?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:59:29.430000Z",
        "message": "No. There wasn't."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:59:34.241000Z",
        "message": "Understood. If you couldn't use Google for some reason, what would you have tried instead to get that recipe or answer?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:59:41.450000Z",
        "message": "I would check TikTok or chat GPT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:59:46.231000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. TikTok and ChatGPT are your backups. Thinking about ChatGPT for a moment, can you describe what makes you choose it over Google on certain occasions? What's what's the situation where you'd reach for ChatGPT instead?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:59:59.111000Z",
        "message": "For a more personal response,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:00:05.331000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So when you're looking for a more tailored or conversational answer, ChatGPT feels like the better fit. Can you recall a specific time you used ChatGPT instead of Google? What were you asking, and how did that experience go?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:00:18.700000Z",
        "message": "Yes. So I extract GTP GPT to put me together a skincare routine, and I was able to send in pictures of my skin. And it was able to tailor it more to things that it feel would work better for my skin type. With Google, you just get a more broader answer. It's not really tailored to you, but more so anyone in general."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:00:42.081000Z",
        "message": "That's a great example. Thanks for breaking that down. Thinking back, what did you like most about using ChatGPT for your skincare routine? Was there any part that didn't work as well as you hoped?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:00:55.641000Z",
        "message": "Yes. I like they gave me, um, dos and don'ts a list of recommendations for my skin type, and like, foods and things that I should probably stay away from and things that I should incorporate as well."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:01:13.181000Z",
        "message": "It sounds like you appreciated the detailed advice and how varied the suggestions were. Was there anything about ChatGPT's answer or the interaction that you found confusing. They oh, but, yeah, I think less helpful or or maybe made you double check elsewhere?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:01:30.231000Z",
        "message": "No."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:01:31.991000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for clarifying. Thinking bigger picture for a moment. If you line up Google ChatGPT and maybe TikTok or other tools, which 1 usually feels most helpful for you? And why?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:01:45.530000Z",
        "message": "That's a good question. I'll say Google because, like I said, you can find more accurate information on there."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:01:54.691000Z",
        "message": "So Google still feels the most reliable and accurate for you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:01:58.981000Z",
        "message": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:01:58.991000Z",
        "message": "If you had to describe Google, ChatGPT, and TikTok as people at a party, what kind of personalities would each 1 have?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:02:10.691000Z",
        "message": "These questions are crazy. I will say TikTok is the party person who gets along with everyone. Chat GPT would come to be the nerd who knows everyone. And Google would be, like, the more stern probably, like, chilling on the wall."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:02:34.241000Z",
        "message": "Love those descriptions. Thanks for playing along. When you think about sharing an answer with someone else, does 1 of these sources feel more credible to quote, than the others? If so, which 1? And what makes it feel that way to you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:02:46.271000Z",
        "message": "Google is more credible because ChatGPT can be wrong. Even on the website, it tells you to check behind them because sometimes it can give inaccurate information. TikTok is pretty much just a broad range of people sharing their experiences. But Google, I feel like, be the best bet."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:03:08.741000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful. Uh, looking back over the past year, would you say anything has changed changed about how you look things up online? Like any new habits or tools popping up in your routine,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:03:20.741000Z",
        "message": "Yes. Um, before, I would just use Google, Now I use chat g t be chat GPT, TikTok, like, the world is evolving, and so are the search engines available to use."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:03:36.370000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like you've branched out a lot from just using Google. Can you think of a moment when you reached for ChatGPT or TikTok first? Instead of Google. What led you to do that?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:03:47.931000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. So anytime I'm looking for recipes, now I'll go to TikTok first because there's so many different people on there. From different places, and you can find different ways of cooking meals on there. Plus, it's videos included, so that's a plus."
      },
      {
        "callId": "c9546d91db0d4b189769b2338",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:04:08.190000Z",
        "message": "There's something about seeing it done in a video by by real people. That makes TikTok stand out for you around recipes. If someone you know recommends a certain answer engine or tool, do you usually check it out? Has anyone ever tipped you off to a new tool for searching or finding answers?"
      },
