  {
    "id": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
    "responseId": "017b92c053ae4f2c895e8a43f",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T03:59:10.465000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T03:59:22.325000Z",
        "message": "Hayden."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T03:59:25.225000Z",
        "message": "Nice to meet you, Hayden. How's your day been so far?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T03:59:29.955000Z",
        "message": "It's alright."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T03:59:33.814000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it's not a bad day, at least. Thanks for being here with me. Let's jump in. When you need answers online, say, you've got a quick question or you're looking something up, what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T03:59:47.734000Z",
        "message": "You can go to Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T03:59:51.045000Z",
        "message": "Got it. You usually head to Google. Can you walk me through what that typically looks like for you? For example, what kinds of things do you search for? And how does the process go from start to finish?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:00:02.435000Z",
        "message": "I opened a Google browser app."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:00:07.785000Z",
        "message": "Okay. So you open the Google browser app. What usually happens next?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:00:11.215000Z",
        "message": "Clean."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:00:12.165000Z",
        "message": "Do you type straight sounds like it's a pretty straightforward routine. Open the app, and you're ready to go. What kinds of questions or topics do you usually look up on Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:00:28.235000Z",
        "message": "What football games are on today?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:00:32.205000Z",
        "message": "Nice example. So let's say you wanna know what football games are on today. After you type that into Google, what do you see and what do you usually do with the results?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:00:43.365000Z",
        "message": "This website called l b schedules pop up, and I click on it, and I check today."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:00:51.285000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for breaking that down. So after searching, you spot LB schedules. Click through, and check today's games. What about that process feels most helpful or satisfying for you? Anything about it that ever annoys you or slows you down?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:01:05.764000Z",
        "message": "No. It's very easy to do so. That's all."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:01:10.865000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Sounds like it just works for you and doesn't cause any hassle. Is Google the tool you use most often when you have a quick question like that or have you tried any other tools or answer engines for these types of searches?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:01:26.595000Z",
        "message": "No."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:01:29.925000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So Google's your go to, and you haven't used other tools for these questions. What is it about Google that makes you stick with it? Is it habit, trust, speed, or something else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:01:41.035000Z",
        "message": "Speed is fast and easy."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:01:44.545000Z",
        "message": "That's clear. For you, it's mainly about speed and ease. Has it always felt this way, or or do you remember a time when when finding answers online was less straightforward?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:01:57.655000Z",
        "message": "I remember the dial up days. That was bad, but now everything is fine."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:02:05.495000Z",
        "message": "Ah, the dial up day is painfully slow. Sounds like things are much smoother for you now. Um, talking about Google, if you imagine it as a person at a party, what kind of personality do you think it would have?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:02:18.635000Z",
        "message": "No. Cool and laid back."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:02:24.475000Z",
        "message": "Cool and laid back. That's a fun way to put it. When you think of we think of answers you find through Google, does it feel like you can trust what you see there? Or do you ever double check info somewhere else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:02:38.165000Z",
        "message": "It depends on the website. The website look legit, then it's fine. If it looks sketch, then I won't I won't use"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:02:50.005000Z",
        "message": "That makes a lot of sense. So it's really about the websites Google shows you, not Google itself. How do you usually decide if a website looks legit or sketchy? Are there certain things you look for?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:03:03.925000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. The website interface. A contact number,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:03:08.325000Z",
        "message": "Got it. The design so things like a clean interface and having a contact number, helps signal that a site is trustworthy for you. Have you ever found a new website through Google that you ended up visiting regularly? Or do you usually stick with sites you already know?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:03:31.155000Z",
        "message": "It depends on what I'm looking for. Sometimes I discover new sites looking for things."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:03:39.075000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Sometimes you branch out when searching for something specific. Thinking back, has your process for looking things up online changed much in the past year or so, or has it stayed pretty much the same?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:03:52.505000Z",
        "message": "Kinda the same. I don't really look up as much stuff as I used to. Now because you know, I'm kinda the scene and everything. So that's about it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:04:06.905000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to know. Um, so your routine hasn't shifted much. But you just don't feel the need to look things up as often these days. Has anyone in your life, friends, family, coworkers,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:04:15.745000Z",
        "message": "Yeah."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:04:18.295000Z",
        "message": "ever suggested you try other ways of finding answers online Or do people around you mostly stick with Google too?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:04:27.945000Z",
        "message": "Everybody just do Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:04:32.264000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Sounds like Google is still the standard in your circle. Is there anything you wish Google could do differently when it comes to finding answers? Or are you pretty happy with how it works now?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:04:43.865000Z",
        "message": "I'm pretty satisfied. Satisfied. It it works fine. I I don't have any complaints."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:04:51.285000Z",
        "message": "That's really clear. Sounds like you're happy with how things are. Thanks for sharing all of that with me, Hayden. Before we wrap up, how was this little AI interview for you? And whenever you're ready, you can end the call."
      },
      {
        "callId": "be3660427aad4b8a96818117c",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-14T04:05:05.705000Z",
        "message": "I was fine."
      }
