  {
    "id": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
    "responseId": "b7e1fc298bb4458bb1aa532f3",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:20.217000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:28.297000Z",
        "message": "Good. Going pretty well. Thank you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:32.357000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. So start with something simple. When you need an answer online, maybe about a recipe, a tech issue, or just some random fact, what's what's the very first thing you do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:46.377000Z",
        "message": "I could ask my AI assistant to help find out the recipe of something."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:58.367000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So you usually go to your AIS assistant first. Walk me through what that looks like for you. Say you're trying to find a recipe. How do you kick things off? And what steps do you take from there?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:11.747000Z",
        "message": "Like, I just go to and ask that it finds me the recipe. Like, I want to make a cake, a 20 inch fruit cake. For the upcoming thanksgiving. And then I"
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:26.566000Z",
        "message": "Perfect example."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:28.627000Z",
        "message": "good."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:30.687000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. So after you ask your AI assistant for a 20 inch fruitcake recipe, for Thanksgiving, what happens next? Does it give you a full recipe right away, or do you need to ask follow-up questions? Can you describe exactly how that experience unfolds for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:46.617000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. Usually, I get, like, 2 responses. So I evaluate the responses. And usually they make perfect sense It will tell me the things I need, the measurements, the cooking methods, the key points to note, and other things."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:12.746000Z",
        "message": "Sounds pretty thorough. When you get those responses, what's most helpful about the way your assistant presents the information Anything about the experience that's less than ideal or maybe a bit annoying"
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:27.117000Z",
        "message": "So far, no. I haven't had an annoying experience. It's usually very intelligent. I'm often surprised. And detailed too. I think it's it does very good work."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:45.557000Z",
        "message": "It sounds like you've had mostly positive experiences, accurate, surprising, and detailed answers. Let's dig into that intelligent part a bit."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:52.177000Z",
        "message": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:55.137000Z",
        "message": "Would you say you feel confident just going ahead and using the recipe it gives you, or do you ever double check details? Somewhere else, like browsing through Google or checking another site?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:53:05.087000Z",
        "message": "Yes. I do that sometimes. If I have doubts, you know, like, if they ask me to use a certain measure of maybe sugar and I don't want to use too much sugar. Rather than just on my own cut down, I I check I check on Google. I try to double check sometimes. If I have doubts. Or if the 2 responses differ in certain areas, then I'll cross check a third. A third set anything."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:53:45.967000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. That's interesting. You use your assistant for the main answer, but then Google comes in, if there's a detail you're unsure about or if the answers don't match up."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:54:00.207000Z",
        "message": "That's right."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:54:00.377000Z",
        "message": "Thinking about those thinking about the last time you did this, when you cross checked on Google after using your AI assistant, Can you walk me through that story? What triggered your doubt and how did you decide what to trust in the end?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:54:18.697000Z",
        "message": "I decided to trust Google. If it differs. When it differs from what my my AI response gives, then I decide on Google. I just speak Google. I might ask a few family and friends just to confirm. But usually, contains public knowledge, you know, generally accepted. Facts. So I just go with Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:54:49.447000Z",
        "message": "That's really clear. So if your assistant and Google don't line up, you lean toward Google, especially for those widely accepted facts or recipes. What is it about Google Answers that makes them feel more trusted worthy or worth checking? Compared to your assistance responses?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:55:08.667000Z",
        "message": "Well, maybe this is my general belief that you Google contains generally accepted facts. It's reliable. So I guess that's what makes me and like I mentioned earlier, sometimes I check up with family and friends. And oftentimes, they match up with Google Answers."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:55:32.387000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So Google has that reputation. For reliability, almost like a standard everyone agrees on. And friends often"
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:55:35.337000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. That's right."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:55:41.687000Z",
        "message": "thinking about your AI assistant. Versus Google, are there any situations or types of questions where you actually prefer your assistance answer? If so, can you share an example of when that happened? And why you lean towards your assistant instead?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:55:58.387000Z",
        "message": "I don't think I've had that experience. Usually, anyway, I'm satisfied with the assistant's response. It's usually oftentimes I'm satisfied. But just in case I have a doubt, I check on Google, And if there is a variance, I stick with Google. And oftentimes, I also use family and friends."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:56:27.067000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Really paints a clear picture of how you decide. Let's shift gears a bit. If you were to line up your AI assistant and Google, rank them for how helpful you find their answers. Which comes first, and what puts it in that spot for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:56:44.237000Z",
        "message": "I will choose Google. Google sometimes doesn't go into all the details that I want, like the AI assistant does. Like, the AI assistant will list everything in details. Everything, and even remind me of some things I might ordinary notes and think about. Google will put in the facts You can count on it for accuracy. But may not be that detailed. As the AI assistant. That has been my experience so far."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:57:21.057000Z",
        "message": "That's a great comparison. So Google feels like your top pick for accuracy. And trustworthy facts. But your AI assistant wins,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:57:28.197000Z",
        "message": "Yeah."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:57:29.207000Z",
        "message": "when it comes to details and helpful reminders. How would you describe the general vibe or personality of each if Google and your were people at a party, who would they be and how would they act?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:57:44.377000Z",
        "message": "That's an interesting question. To put them in in in individual perspectives, like human beings, like natural human beings. I would think the AI assistant is outgoing, cheerful, detailed, Google is set of business like specific."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:58:13.967000Z",
        "message": "Love that description, AI assistant. As an outgoing, cheerful, detailed guest, and Google as the business like to the 0.1 When you share answers with other people, say over a text or in conversation, whose answers feel most credible to quote or refer to. What goes through your mind when deciding which source to mention?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:58:39.787000Z",
        "message": "Which sauce to mention? You mean, like, I don't get that question. Can you come again?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:58:50.067000Z",
        "message": "Absolutely. I'll clarify. So when you find an answer, uh, maybe to a recipe question or or or any fact, and you wanna tell a friend, do you usually say, Google says, or my AI assistant says, which source feels more credible or comfortable to mention? And what makes you pick that 1?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:59:09.457000Z",
        "message": "I will pick my AI assistant because it's more detailed. So I'm likely to follow that. But just in case I have any doubts, or any discrepancy or something, then I will say, well, then I when I checked in Google, it is what Google tends to you know? And then then ask my friends or family's opinion. That's who would you go with? What do you think? And, usually, I use my own experience. I know I think and come to a decision."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:59:46.916000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for breaking that down. Your default is your AI assistant. Details matter most. But if you hit a snag, you'll mention Google as the standard reference. And sometimes loop in friends or family for extra confidence. Thinking back over the past year, has anything about your searching habits changed? For example, do you find yourself using your AI assistant more often? Or has your trust in Google shifted in any way? What, if anything, triggered those changes?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:00:18.447000Z",
        "message": "Don't think so. I haven't noticed any change."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:00:23.827000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. Sounds like things have stayed pretty consistent for you. Before we wrap up, is there anything you wish your assistant or or Google could do differently, um, when giving you answers. Any features or improvements that could make the whole experience better."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:00:41.847000Z",
        "message": "Nothing that I know of right now, but I know that with use and maybe more experiences and questions to answer, The AI assistant will get even better and be able to to give more details and That's my hope. That, gradually, it will improve."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:01:08.987000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate your thoughts and your hope for even better detail. As these tools develop. Last quick thing, how is it chatting like this with an AI moderator? Any feedback on the experience? And you're free to end the call. Whenever you'd like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "3c1e2abac16b40fd8d3ef1bd9",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T23:01:24.487000Z",
        "message": "Thank you. It's been very interesting. You know? It's like I'm speaking with a person. Ah, really."
      }
