  {
    "id": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
    "responseId": "b64b71d8e29d400d98f78f397",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:49:15.058000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:49:22.868000Z",
        "message": "Go ahead."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:49:25.078000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. I'll kick us off. Simple. When you need answers online, uh, what's what's the very first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:49:33.618000Z",
        "message": "Check. Check. Check. GPT."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:49:36.798000Z",
        "message": "Got it. You go straight to ChatGPT. Can you walk me through your usual process for looking something up, uh, with ChatGPT? What do you do? From start to finish?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:49:44.637000Z",
        "message": "I'll hold the button and ask you a question. And then depending if I need more details, I'll ask you to look for more details or if I need to look at something similar and compare it to Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:49:57.108000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for breaking that down. Can you tell me about the last time you did this? Started with ChatGPT. Then maybe compared to Google. What did you need, and how did the whole process go for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:09.038000Z",
        "message": "I looked up what type of oil my motorcycle needed. And when I looked up on Google, it doesn't necessarily give me too much detail. When I looked up in chat, GBT already remembers how I've been working on lots of. Here it is. So it already has my history and previous questions saved in the records."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:30.508000Z",
        "message": "That's really interesting. Sounds like ChatGPT's memory of your past questions is a big plus for you. What part of that experience felt most helpful? And was there anything about using ChatGPT or Google that annoyed you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:45.088000Z",
        "message": "What was helpful is whatever suggested for the oil, I tried out and it worked. And with Google, it's just nothing frustrating. It's just it just saves me time."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:55.838000Z",
        "message": "Quick check. So when ChatGPT suggests something, do you usually feel confident acting on it? Or do you ever double check its answers somewhere else, like on Google or other sites?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:06.518000Z",
        "message": "I feel confident enough to use it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:11.838000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Confidence is high. With ChatGPT's answers. Now thinking about situations where you might switch tools, can you remember a time you used something other than ChatGPT first? What was the task? And what led you to try another tool?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:26.988000Z",
        "message": "I looked up the product again on ChatGPT, but I went to Google to see which store to buy it from. Since it does have all marketplaces that I previously purchased from already saved."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:39.648000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. So ChatGPT for product info, Google for finding where to buy, when you compare how ChatGPT feels versus Google, for those kinds of searches, what stands out as different in the experience? Anything obvious?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:53.058000Z",
        "message": "Check GPT seems to be a little more personal and more human like versus Google is more moderated and technical."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:02.558000Z",
        "message": "That's a helpful way to put it. If you line them up from most to least helpful for you personally, how would you rank ChatGPT, Google, and any other engines you use? What's your order and why?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:14.708000Z",
        "message": "I would use"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:19.878000Z",
        "message": "Take your time."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:22.068000Z",
        "message": "I would use Google first because it has all of my records from previous purchases to my search history to emails to photos and everything I've purchased, the card numbers to everything. And then chat GBT just for personalized reasons. And support."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:39.918000Z",
        "message": "That's a strong connection to Google's whole ecosystem. When you think about Google as an answer engine, what words or feelings come to mind? And same for ChatGPT, anything different come up for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:53.248000Z",
        "message": "With Google, it's more of a memorial since I've been using them since my first smartphone. And with ChatGPT, it's become a little more personal. Because I can ask you for so many different questions. I normally would not look up on Google. Because it gives it more descriptive answers."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:53:13.778000Z",
        "message": "Really interesting. Google's like a memorial of your digital life. And ChatGPT feels more personal and and descriptive. If you were to share an answer with someone else, say, to send them info about motorcycle oil, whose response would you feel made the most comfortable quoting? Google ChatGPT or someone else. Why? Just letting you know, after"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:53:33.078000Z",
        "message": "I forgot I feel confident with both equally, but with Chet I know it looks up a lot of search engines and not just with Google, but other search engines as well. Versus Google, I feel like it's just more retained to just them to whatever is on Google itself and now what's on other private search engines."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:53:53.068000Z",
        "message": "That's a great distinction. Sounds like you trust ChatGPT to pull in a broader range of"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:53:56.708000Z",
        "message": "It's just"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:53:57.318000Z",
        "message": "info. No rush. Can you tell me more about what you're thinking?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:54:06.047000Z",
        "message": "Did you repeat the question?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:54:08.487000Z",
        "message": "Sure thing. If you were sharing an answer, like info about motorcycle oil, with someone else, would you feel most comfortable? Quoting a Google, ChatGPT, or another tool? What makes you feel that way about your choice?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:54:23.298000Z",
        "message": "I would feel comfortable chatting with you because they list the links of where they receive their sources from. It's not just someone just gloating random answers."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:54:33.348000Z",
        "message": "That's clear. Having those source links gives you something to trust, and refer back to. When you think back over the past year, has anything changed in how often you reach for Google or ChatGPT first? What do you notice about your habits?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:54:48.238000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. I've actually noticed that I've not drifted away, but I do rely on CHECK ABT a lot more. Since I'm I've used Google in the past, and I've not necessarily got the answers I've been looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:55:01.508000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like you're leaning on chatty more now, mostly because it delivers the answers you really need Can you remember a specific moment when you went to ChatGPT first instead of Google for something you'd usually ask Google? What pushed you to make that choice?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:55:19.148000Z",
        "message": "I was creating a random business logo for a friend of mine. And I went to use Google to see which place to use, and I kept recommending Canva and other places. In the end, I went to ChatDBT because it did it itself. And it did similarly to what I was looking for and without me having to do too much work."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:55:42.008000Z",
        "message": "That's a great story. With the logo task, could actually handle it for you rather than just suggesting services. Was there anything about that experience that changed how you felt about using these tools overall?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:55:56.188000Z",
        "message": "Yes. Is it big time saver. I can just ask you to do something, and I can just step away, and it will give me an alert when it's done doing what it's doing versus just sitting there on a Google search engine and having to retype a question just to get a different type of answer."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:56:11.808000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. And having the work handled for you and getting notified sounds pretty freeing. If you could change or improve anything about the current answer engines, what kind of features or changes would make you want to use them even more?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:56:25.968000Z",
        "message": "Just to make sure that my security is more private and know it's not going to be hacked or used against me in some form of way."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:56:34.368000Z",
        "message": "Privacy is definitely a big deal, not just getting an answer, but trusting your info is safe. Anything else, small or big, you wish these tools did or any unmet need you've noticed when using them?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:56:45.978000Z",
        "message": "Nope. Everything seems to be fine. As is, I haven't run into any problems so far."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:56:52.918000Z",
        "message": "That's good to hear. For walking me through your habits and thoughts. It's been really enlightening. Last question. How did you feel chatting with an AI about your search experiences today? And whenever you're ready, you can end the call."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 41,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:57:08.618000Z",
        "message": "This is the first time using it, and it's unique and I think a little more easier to explain my details versus typing."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b498481dcdd748d5a3253f73b",
        "index": 42,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:57:18.547000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. I appreciate your openness and detail today. If you ever want to chat about tech or search habits again, I'm here. You can end the call whenever you'd like."
      }
    ],
