  {
    "id": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
    "responseId": "4073384d512a442cab03a4e96",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:48:47.968000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:48:56.068000Z",
        "message": "Doing fine. Thank you."
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:48:58.718000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. So when you need answers online, let's say you're curious about something or need quick quick info, what's what's the very very first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:49:09.968000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. Google AI."
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:49:13.888000Z",
        "message": "Got it. You usually reach for Google AI. Can you walk me through what that process looks like for you? From the moment you realize you need an answer to actually getting 1,"
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:49:26.438000Z",
        "message": "I just go to Google dot com. I type in what I'm looking for. And Google summarizes basically what I'm looking for. And offers some sites that I can go to."
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:49:37.588000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for laying that out. Thinking about the last time you did this, can you tell me the story starting with what you needed to look up and all the steps you took?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:49:47.078000Z",
        "message": "I was looking for info on the news on a news item. And I typed in Google and and followed the search prompts from there."
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:00.628000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. When you saw the summary Google gave you, what did you do next? Did you stick with what was in the summary? Or did you check other sources or links?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:10.587000Z",
        "message": "At first, I checked out what was in the summary, and then I I went and looked for for some more news sources. To find out about it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:22.148000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate the detail. Um, what part of that experience felt most helpful to you? And was there anything about it that was confusing or or frustrating frustrating?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:31.538000Z",
        "message": "Uh, I don't think there was anything confusing or frustrating, but, um, summary was was exactly that. It was a summary, and it it gave me an idea of what I was how and what I was actually looking for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:46.328000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to know. When you were digging deeper and and checking more news sources, how did you decide which links or sites to to trust or click on?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:56.638000Z",
        "message": "Well, I normally go to like, the the major news networks like Fox News or CNN or BBC. And, uh, I actually checked all 3 of those sites. After I looked at the summary."
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:11.567000Z",
        "message": "So you rely on those bigger news names for extra context. Thinking about the Google summary itself, do you ever double check it? By comparing with other engines, like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Gemini, or do you mostly stick with Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:24.338000Z",
        "message": "No. I mostly stick with Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:28.368000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. I'm curious what is it about Google that makes it your default choice these days? Especially when you want quick answers?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:37.097000Z",
        "message": "All Google is pretty much the the main player on the block. As far as searching you know, search engines go."
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:46.207000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. If you ever needed a more detailed explanation or wanted to ask follow-up questions, about something, would you ever use something like ChatGPT or Perplexity or would you still stick with Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:58.578000Z",
        "message": "For now, I'm just sticking with Google. I don't have a lot of experience with chat GPT. I've used it a few times, but I like the way that Google has their setup."
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:12.188000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate you sharing that. You mentioned you tried ChatGPT a few times. Can you recall a specific moment you used it? What were you trying to find out, and how did that experience feel compared to using Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:23.498000Z",
        "message": "Actually, I was just I've I've I'd I'd I'd seen it on the chat you could see on the news. And I just wanted to check it out. I I forget what I was looking for. It wasn't anything specific. I I was just checking out how you know, the page layout was set up and what what links to that chat GPT suggested."
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:48.088000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So that was more of an exploration than a task driven search. When you first saw ChatGPT"
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:52.898000Z",
        "message": "Correct."
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:56.188000Z",
        "message": "thanks for clarifying. Thinking about chat GPT or even, uh, Perplexity or Gemini if you've tried them, Do any words or feelings come to mind? When you hear those names compared to Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:53:09.048000Z",
        "message": "Not really. I mean, they're just it's another option. And if if there was something if there was a reason that I needed to use ChetGPT or Plexity or Gemini, I'd I'd use it. But so far, Google's been everything I need."
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:53:26.067000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. Looking back, has anything changed about how you search or or find answers? Online over, say, the past year? Or have your habits pretty much stayed the same?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:53:37.028000Z",
        "message": "No. I'm I'm I'm relying more on the summaries. At first, I was kinda skeptical because when it first came out, uh, Google AI was I don't know. It was a little it was you could tell that it was being written by AI. It wasn't it wasn't as human like as it is today."
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:54:00.158000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. Over time, as those Google AI summaries got smoother, and felt more natural, did that affect your confidence or trust in using them? Or maybe how fast you rely on them for info?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:54:13.098000Z",
        "message": "No. It it it increased my, you know, I wanna say trust, but, you know, I I I believe that it's more accurate. With the with the more human like language that it uses."
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:54:28.128000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for explaining that. Uh, if you ever talked with friends or coworkers about these answer engines, do they ever recommend using something other than Google? Or does Google usually come up as as the main option in your circles?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:54:42.578000Z",
        "message": "Yep. Google is usually the main option. I I know some people who you who have used GP ChatGPT in the past, but as as far as where I work, everybody use uses Google AI on the search engine."
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:54:57.257000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful context. Wrapping up, is there anything you wish these answer engines Google or the others, could do better for you? Any features or abilities you'd love to see added?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:55:09.258000Z",
        "message": "Not really. They're they're serve my purposes for now, and I I I can't complain"
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:55:20.417000Z",
        "message": "Perfect. Thanks for sharing your honest take. That's actually all I have for you today. Uh, thanks again for chatting. If you have any last thoughts, feel free to share. Otherwise, you're all set, and you can end the call whenever you'd like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "997c253e574140a88e134c2af",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:55:33.078000Z",
        "message": "Alright. Thank you. Have a nice day."
      }
