  {
    "id": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
    "responseId": "01d9801a3976437a82c2473af",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:47:51.231000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:47:59.511000Z",
        "message": "Fine."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:48:02.411000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. Let's jump in. When you need to look something up, get an answer online, what's the the very first thing you typically do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:48:11.991000Z",
        "message": "Go to Google search. And now Genie since I have it on my phone."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:48:21.470000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Could you walk me through what usually prompts you to choose Google Search versus Genie? What kind of situations lead you to use 1 or the other?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:48:33.411000Z",
        "message": "I guess. With Google because I'm so used to it. And Genie is sorta new to me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:48:43.441000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So it sounds like habit a big role with with Google. While Genie is still getting into your routine, do you remember the last time you used Genie instead of Google? What was the situation? And what made you pick Genie that time?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:48:59.651000Z",
        "message": "Because it's new to me, This is a newer phone. And I wanted to see what it was like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:49:07.991000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So curiosity in having it ready on your new phone, guided you to try Genie out. Can you tell me the story of that time? Were you looking for, and what steps did you take? From thinking of your question to getting your answer?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:49:23.241000Z",
        "message": "Well, I normally coulda went to Google, but I went to Genie. Because I wanted a little bit more specific And I exit for some pricing on fitted bed sheets that Macy's. And it was interesting that it was stored really good. The answers they gave me. Compared to Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:49:53.091000Z",
        "message": "That's a helpful comparison. Um, when you say Genie gave you really good answers, what specifically about its response stood out to you compared to what Google would have shown?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:05.931000Z",
        "message": "Just I guess, a little bit more pacific. I guess. And a little bit more tips."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:17.180000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for that. So it sounds like, uh, Jeannie's answers were more specific and maybe offered extra tips too. What part of that experience with Genie felt most helpful to you? And was there anything that felt annoying? Or made you hesitate?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:34.891000Z",
        "message": "Uh, no. Nothing was annoying. I was just rather surprised. Just was my first time ever using anything like that, and I sorta enjoyed it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:50:50.201000Z",
        "message": "Appreciate the honesty. That feeling of surprise it more about how direct and useful Genie's answer was or just about trying a new type of tool? Can you tell me more about what you, uh, you enjoyed?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:04.181000Z",
        "message": "More direct. More honest, I mean, they're both honest, but I don't know. I don't even know how they explain it except they were just a little bit more pacific. And I like the answers they gave."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:19.711000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Some people say that AI engines feel more conversational or tailored. Did Jeannie feel that way? Or was it more about the content of the answer than, like, the tone?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:33.771000Z",
        "message": "I would have to say more tailored."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:38.571000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to know. About Google now, when you use it for searching, how do the answers feel in comparison? Is there anything about Google's results that feels less tailored or just different from what Jeannie gave you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:51:53.311000Z",
        "message": "Well, a little different. Uh, it just Google when you ask something. You always get a lot of other things too. And Jeannie kinda, like, give you specifically what you're for."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:10.151000Z",
        "message": "That's a clear difference. So Google tends to give you lots of links and extra info, whereas Genie goes straight to what you asked for. How does that affect how confident you feel in the answers? Or in how quickly you find what you need?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:24.561000Z",
        "message": "I like that. I I go to Macy's a lot. So the answers they gave me sound for real."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:33.761000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. So when Jeannie gave you info about Macy's, it matched what you know from experience. And that felt for real. Did Genie show you sources for its answers?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:42.231000Z",
        "message": "Yes. It did."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:44.661000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for confirming. Thinking about"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:45.441000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. It did."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:52:49.711000Z",
        "message": "thanks. When Genie shows sources, does that change how much you trust the information compared to when Google gives you links, or does it feel about the same?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:53:04.501000Z",
        "message": "Uh, okay. That's a hard 1. Um, I guess with Google is because I'm so used to it, And with Genie, it's because I'm still learning how to use it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:53:17.691000Z",
        "message": "Totally makes sense. Habits play a big part. If you had to line them up from most to least helpful for you right now, how would you rank Genie and Google? And what, uh, what makes you pick that order?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:53:32.541000Z",
        "message": "I believe I will go with Jeannie first. Always will keep Google, but I will go with Genie because it's to me, it just feels a little bit more interesting."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:53:44.911000Z",
        "message": "That's insightful. Uh, when you say Genie feels more interesting, does that mean for you? Is it the way answers come back? Or something about the way you interact with Jeannie?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:53:56.211000Z",
        "message": "The way the answers come back, and so far, way I interact with Gini."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:54:03.181000Z",
        "message": "That's really clear. Thank you. If each engine, Google, Genie, were a person at the party, how would you describe their personality or how they how they act?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:54:16.921000Z",
        "message": "Google will be calmer I think Genie would be funner."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:54:25.961000Z",
        "message": "Great visual. So Google feels calm. Genie feels more fun. When you share answers with someone else, like texting a friend about Macy's sheets, which engine's information feels more credible or comfortable to pass along."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:54:44.401000Z",
        "message": "Well, I'm kinda private with most information. It have to be a real family member. But, normally, I try not to put too much when I'm texting. Someone because of security reason."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:55:02.890000Z",
        "message": "That's thoughtful. So sharing info regardless of the engine doesn't happen often unless it's someone close and you're mindful of privacy."
      },
      {
        "callId": "e545e16118da4db2bf1e5c38f",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
