  {
    "id": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
    "responseId": "f81b2d21e5d34f3bb03ae8cc7",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:35:01.123000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:35:09.003000Z",
        "message": "Pretty good."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:35:12.373000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. When you're looking for answers online, say, you wanna figure something out quickly, what's the very first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:35:22.772000Z",
        "message": "Ask Bing."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:35:26.893000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So Bing's your top pick. Can you walk me through exactly how that goes? Maybe thinking of the most recent time, that you used Bing to look something up, start from what you needed, and tell me every step you took."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:35:44.753000Z",
        "message": "I was looking for the side effect of Ozempic, which I just recently started to take. And I clicked on the microphone. I simply said side effects for Ozempic, and they came up. And I found the information I needed."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:36:03.023000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for laying that out. Thinking back to, uh, that experience, what parts felt especially helpful or smooth while you were using Bing? And was there anything that annoyed you? Or made you hesitate along the way?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:36:17.963000Z",
        "message": "Nothing that comes to mind. I was able to get the information I needed. In a fairly efficient way and all is well that ends well."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:36:29.702000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like a pretty seamless experience. Did you notice, um, if Bing gave you a summary read out loud or cited sources for that info? Anything special about how it delivered the answer that made you feel confident using it?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:36:43.793000Z",
        "message": "It's rather pointless, think, but it beginning, it always reads me part of the initial answer and then stops. And then I can go on and read all the other information that's there."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:36:58.473000Z",
        "message": "Interesting. So Bing gives you a taste of the answer. With a brief audio read, but then leaves you to explore the rest yourself. How do you feel about that Does the audio snippet actually help or do you mostly just skip ahead and read?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:37:13.023000Z",
        "message": "It doesn't really help because it's up on the screen, and it's just repeating what it I can see on the screen. So I just kind of ignore it and go on with my own"
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:37:29.633000Z",
        "message": "Makes sense. So you're focused more on what's written, what's spoken. When you use Bing, do you usually trust the first answer or do you ever feel the need to double check by clicking into other sources or using other tools."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:37:43.733000Z",
        "message": "Well, depending on the information, if it's medical information, then I may check another source if something seems a bit off. But most the answers I get are pretty close to what I expect only in rare cases do I feel a need to check somewhere else."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:38:04.303000Z",
        "message": "That's helpful to know. Thinking beyond Bing for a moment, are there times you switch to another answer engine? Like Google, ChatGPT, or anything else? What's usually going on when you decide to make that switch?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:38:18.473000Z",
        "message": "I sometimes use Google Chrome only because I have I have the browser on my site, and it works better with some matters than others."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:38:32.593000Z",
        "message": "Can you tell me about a specific time when you chose Google Chrome instead of Bing? What were you trying to do, and how did the compare?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:38:43.993000Z",
        "message": "I can't remember what I was trying to do, to be honest. And the really not much of a difference between the 2 that I noticed."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:38:54.772000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So your experience feels pretty similar between Bing and Google. Nothing really stands out as as dramatically different. I'm curious, do you ever use AI answer engines like Chat Gemini, or Perplexity? Or have you mostly just stuck with Bing and Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:39:10.603000Z",
        "message": "I'm stuck with Bing and Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:39:15.113000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. That helps me understand your usual go tos. If you lined up Bing and Google side by side, just thinking about how they handle giving you answers, which 1 feels more helpful? And what what makes you say that?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:39:28.983000Z",
        "message": "It's definitely Bing because that's the 1 I use most frequently. I probably use that 3 times for every 1 time I use Google. So something that you have used more frequently is easier to use and easier to format the questions and so forth."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:39:45.863000Z",
        "message": "That's clear. Frequency makes Bing feel familiar and comfortable for you. If you had to describe Bing and Google as people at a party, what kind of personalities would they have? How would they act?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:39:59.093000Z",
        "message": "I don't anthropomorphize any unliving creature. I don't believe that that that non humans have human characteristics. So I couldn't do that at all."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:40:15.143000Z",
        "message": "Fair enough. And thanks for being direct about that. Instead of personalities, when you think of, um, Bing versus Google, what are the first words or feelings that come to mind for each just anything that pops up?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:40:29.453000Z",
        "message": "Nothing really. It's, you know, it's like people ask you that sort of a question, like, what first pops into your mind? And sometimes for me, it's just nothing. I mean, it's I I know what the word is. I know what the the the thing that it is describing, but I don't automatically think of any magical words."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:40:54.413000Z",
        "message": "Totally makes sense. Not everyone has instant associations for these tools, especially when they're just practical parts of everyday life. Looking back over the past year, has anything noticeably changed in the way you search for answers online? Maybe how often you use Bing versus Google? Or any new habits."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:41:14.203000Z",
        "message": "Well, I use my Amazon Echo, and ask for quick information like what's 12 times 12 or whatever happens to be. With Bing and the AI. It's being included in more and more places. And it's just becoming more frequent that you encounter it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:41:39.883000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. So you're using your Echo some quick answers. And you're noticing Bing's AI showing up more often. Almost everywhere you look. Can you think of a recent time when Bing's AI showed up somewhere new or unexpected for you? Was the situation?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:41:56.043000Z",
        "message": "I really can't think of any such incident."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:42:01.703000Z",
        "message": "Alright. Thanks for sharing what you could. Before we wrap, I'm curious how did you find talking to an AI interviewer today? Any thoughts or feedback on the experience? And you're free to end our call you'd like."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:42:16.323000Z",
        "message": "Well, to be honest with you, I find AI is rather concerning at times because sometimes it is it refuses to accept an answer when it wants something. So it keeps asking the same question in different forms over and over and over again."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8820c076c09143509e9719475",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:42:34.252000Z",
        "message": "I appreciate you being honest, and I hear your point. No 1 likes getting peppered with variations of the same question. Thanks for giving me a try today. You're all set. And you can end the call whenever you'd like."
      }
    ],
