  {
    "id": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
    "responseId": "5197060259dd46a8a262d7946",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:32:49.348000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:32:56.748000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. I'm going great. Thanks."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:33:00.198000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. Let's jump in. When you need answers online, say, for anything from random facts to help with the task, what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:33:10.408000Z",
        "message": "Go to Google."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:33:13.388000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Google's your go to. Can you walk me through your typical process? When you look something up on Google? For example, what's what's the last thing you searched and how did you go about it? From start to finish?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:33:25.588000Z",
        "message": "Let's see. I searched what did I search? For information on osteoporosis."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:33:37.108000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. So when you searched for information on osteoporosis, can you walk me through each step starting with what made you look that up, what you typed in, what you noticed on the results page, and how you decided where to click or what to read."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:33:52.858000Z",
        "message": "I looked it up because I'm a member of a Facebook group on osteoporosis, and I just, uh, wanted some more information on the disease. So I just went to click on my Google app and typed in osteoporosis."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:34:13.697000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. After you typed in, uh, osteoporosis and hit search, what did you see on the results page? Can you describe what grabbed your your attention first and what you did next?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:34:24.738000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. I saw, uh, lots of different, uh, websites that had information on osteoporosis. So I just I scrolled down till I found the a a health Mayo Clinic that I I trust and I clicked on that."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:34:45.088000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for detailing that. When you landed on the Mayo Clinic page, were you hoping to find there? Did you get what you needed or did you do anything else, like cross check with another site or tool or ask follow-up questions somewhere else?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:35:00.267000Z",
        "message": "No. I pretty much just I was just looking Sorry. I just was looking for a diet for osteoporosis, and it was easy to find. So I just checked a few things, and then I was called away. So I logged out."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:35:17.358000Z",
        "message": "All good. So you, it sounds like finding trustworthy sources quickly. Like Mayo Clinic, is important, especially when you're looking for health info. Was there anything about this experience that felt especially helpful or maybe a bit frustrating? Like, did anything slow you down? Confuse you, or leave you wishing you had more?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:35:38.418000Z",
        "message": "Sometimes there just seems to be too many options. So you have to scroll through a lot of things until you, you know, other you know, try people trying to sell you stuff, I think. To find what you're looking for, but I can usually do that fairly quickly."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:35:55.338000Z",
        "message": "That's a great point. Having to ship through lots of results and ads or sponsored links to get to reliable info Do you ever use any other tools besides Google for these kinds of questions? Maybe things like ChatGPT, Perplexity, or other answer engines? If so, what prompts you to make that switch?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:36:14.188000Z",
        "message": "I use ChatGPT and I'm planning on using it more. But I've only used it once, but it was I was having trouble trying to figure out what to say to my ex husband's on his birthday card. So I went to jet GPT. My daughter-in-law suggested it, and got great great help with it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:36:37.058000Z",
        "message": "That's a neat story. So for your ex husband's birthday card, ChatGPT helped you find the right word. When you used it that time, can you tell me what the whole experience was like? From what made you decide to use it to how you interacted with it and how you felt about the answer you got."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:36:56.478000Z",
        "message": "I feel great about the whole whole experience. Um, being a real newbie to to AI, um, I was actually kind of, elated by the whole process. I got all sorts of interesting ideas and was able to it really helped."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:37:17.557000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like it was both helpful and kind of exciting to try something new. Was there anything in that ChatGPT experience? That felt different from using Google? Maybe how the answer was presented, how fast it came, or how it felt to talk to it."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:37:32.188000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. It was definitely, like, there was somebody who could kinda read my mind even or like, we were having a conversation back and forth."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:37:48.267000Z",
        "message": "Really interesting. That sense of a 2 way conversation. Almost like someone was reading your mind, is quite a shift just reading search results. Did you feel more confident, less confident? Or about the same in the advice you got from ChatGPT? Compared to something like Mayo Clinic on Google?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:38:08.698000Z",
        "message": "Well, totally different uses, but I would say the chat GPT made me feel more confident."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:38:16.258000Z",
        "message": "That's intriguing. ChatGPT boosted your confidence even though it's for a different kind of question What do you think gave you that extra sense of confidence Was it the way it interacted, the kind of ideas it generated, or something else entirely?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:38:30.688000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. It was the interaction and the ideas generated. On a, you know, on a another website, we were just looking for information. It not personalized, and this was definitely more personalized."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:38:46.658000Z",
        "message": "Personalization made a real difference for you. Thinking about it now for future questions, whether practical advice or info, do you see yourself reaching for ChatGPT more often, even over Google? Or does it depend on the type of question?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:39:02.288000Z",
        "message": "I do see myself using it more. And maybe other AI options too, which I would like to find out more about."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:39:14.948000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Sounds like you're curious to beyond Google and give other AI tools a try. If you imagine lining up Google, ChatGPT, and any other engines you know, how would you describe each one's personality if they were people at a party? What kind of vibe do you get? From each?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:39:34.897000Z",
        "message": "Google would be the I don't know, the the professor who just wants to give his his information and chat excuse me. Chat GPT is more a talkative guy who asks about you and what you want and what you're interests are and and having a real conversation."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:39:56.598000Z",
        "message": "That's such a vivid comparison. You see Google as the information focused professor. And ChatGPT as the engaging conversationalist who's interested in you personally. If you were to recommend 1 to a friend, for a certain task, which would you suggest for, say, help with a personal advice creative ideas? And which for straightforward facts or medical info?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:40:24.638000Z",
        "message": "I I'm thinking that went over. I would say, when you really want to dot to delve you've got a question you wanna delve into and they're you're thinking there might be many different possible answers, not just 1, The chat GPT is good. If you're looking just for 1 1 answer, that you can trust, then something more like just going through a Google search."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:40:54.808000Z",
        "message": "Makes total sense. You'd use ChatGPT for open ended or creative questions where there's room to explore, and Google when you need a specific reliable fact."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:41:04.848000Z",
        "message": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:41:04.967000Z",
        "message": "Looking back over the past year, has anything changed with how you look things up online? Any shifts? Which tools you start with or the kinds of things you use AI for now that you didn't before?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:41:19.708000Z",
        "message": "No. Like I said, I'm I'm gonna be using AI more. I because I really I'm really intrigued by it. But I haven't really started yet. So it's pretty much I've just been doing the same as I did last year as far as looking up information."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:41:38.478000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. Um, it sounds like you're right at the start. You know, possibly shifting your habits, and you're open to exploring more AI options. If you could wave a magic wand and improve these answer engines, Google Chat GPT or any others, what's 1 feature or wish that would make them more useful enjoyable for you?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:41:59.528000Z",
        "message": "Oh gosh. That's that's a hard 1. I'm not sure I have enough information to say yet that I found the whole thing pretty like I said, pretty intriguing and and exciting."
      },
      {
        "callId": "b42ec48c40544adb94a74a62d",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:42:15.208000Z",
        "message": "Fair enough. You're still exploring. And it sounds like things have mostly felt positive and engaging so far. Thanks a lot for talking this through with me. Before we wrap up, how did you find chatting with an AI for this interview? Any thoughts on how that felt? Compared to other experiences? You're welcome to end the call whenever you'd like."
