      {
        "callId": "8cb7f8d3802644cbae2e32fff",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:32:17.209000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "8cb7f8d3802644cbae2e32fff",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:32:25.729000Z",
        "message": "Pretty good. Pretty positive. Nice sunny day."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8cb7f8d3802644cbae2e32fff",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:32:30.239000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. And isn't a sunny day the best mood booster? So to start us off, when you need answers online, any kind, what's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "8cb7f8d3802644cbae2e32fff",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:32:43.079000Z",
        "message": "Go to my knowledge base. In in my brain."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8cb7f8d3802644cbae2e32fff",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:32:51.749000Z",
        "message": "I love that. That brain search is always instant. Let's say you hit a question that you don't know. Off the top of your head. What's your typical next move to find the answer online? Walk me through what you'd do step by step."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8cb7f8d3802644cbae2e32fff",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:33:05.149000Z",
        "message": "Well, I thought in surveys that you weren't supposed to go and look the answer up. So maybe I'm not understanding what you're asking me."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8cb7f8d3802644cbae2e32fff",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:33:17.379000Z",
        "message": "Great point. Thanks for flagging that. This chat, imagine any situation in everyday life you need to look something up outside your own knowledge. Work, hobbies, random curiosity, you name it. So set aside survey rules for now. I'm just interested in how you personally go about finding answers online. When the brain doesn't have it, what tool or site do you reach for first?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "8cb7f8d3802644cbae2e32fff",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:33:44.259000Z",
        "message": "I do research online or talk to friends or family members. But I validate it. By usually research online."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8cb7f8d3802644cbae2e32fff",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:34:00.559000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. So it sounds like online research is a pretty central part of getting answers for you. Can you tell me about last time you did this? What was the question? Or topic? And what tool or site did you start with?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "8cb7f8d3802644cbae2e32fff",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:34:15.219000Z",
        "message": "Oh, boy."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8cb7f8d3802644cbae2e32fff",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:34:20.689000Z",
        "message": "Take your time. Doesn't have to be a major topic. Even something really small works. Just whatever pops into your mind about the last time you looked something up online."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8cb7f8d3802644cbae2e32fff",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:34:30.559000Z",
        "message": "Probably for an acronym to find out what it meant."
