        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:37:24.679000Z",
        "message": "Thanks. Like, when you use a Google Chat GPT or Perplexity for research, do you notice any differences in how the answers feel compared to to Gemini? Anything stand out about the depth? How trustworthy they seem, or just how you interact"
      },
      {
        "callId": "8cb7f8d3802644cbae2e32fff",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:37:36.668000Z",
        "message": "No. But I don't I don't use the Google Once I use Gemini, I don't go back to chat GBT or Google GBT. I'll just go into the regular Google. And put a search in search field."
      },
      {
        "callId": "8cb7f8d3802644cbae2e32fff",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:37:58.599000Z",
        "message": "That's interesting. Mostly stick with Gemini, or regular Google search and not so much ChatGPT or Google's AI powered version. If you're using regular Google search, what makes you pick that instead of Gemini? Is there a certain type of task or question where you prefer the old school search"
