  {
    "id": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
    "responseId": "c23ae06775654763aaeec0939",
    "messages": [
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 0,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:30:12.291000Z",
        "message": "Hi there. I'm Elliot, your AI moderator. Thanks for making the time to chat today. Before we dive in, how's your day going?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 1,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:30:21.171000Z",
        "message": "Good."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 2,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:30:27.201000Z",
        "message": "Glad to hear it. Just wanted to check Does March 8 2000 have any special meaning for you, or was that just a quick reply? Feel free to ask me any questions. Feel free to ask me any questions."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 3,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:30:58.621000Z",
        "message": "Why is this uh, why was you asking about that date? Because that is the date that I met my dad's family. For the first time."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 4,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:31:09.211000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that. It sounds like March eighth so this 2000 has real significance for you. Meeting your dad's family for the first time. Must have been a memorable experience. Switching gears a bit, When you're online, and need to find an answer to something. Maybe quick info or to understand something new. What's the first thing you usually do?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 5,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:31:31.941000Z",
        "message": "I go to Google or Bing or any of the search engines. Or I might use Copilot just depending on what I'm needing to search for. Most of the time, I just use Chrome or Google, Or when I really need to ask something, I can use Meta AI or I use Copilot."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 6,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:31:55.411000Z",
        "message": "Got it. So you've got a toolkit. Depending on the situation. Google, Bing, Copilot, Meta AI. And sometimes just a browser like Chrome. Can you walk me through a recent time you searched for something online? Just start with what you needed. And tell me what step you took first."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 7,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:32:13.340000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. I was looking for cruise tickets for carnival, because the boyfriend goes on cruises all the time with his family. And I was looking to see what my cruise ticket cost would be So I started out with Chrome, I looked at it. The prices looked good. So I checked other websites on Chrome, and then I went to Meta AI and asked her what might be a good source to look up. And then I went to Bing looked for them, and then I went back to Copilot and asked Copilot. And then I ended up talking to Meta AI and got the prices that we needed."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 8,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:32:54.761000Z",
        "message": "That's a great walk through. So you jumped between Chrome, Meta, AI, Bing, and Copilot. Checking and comparing prices. If you think back to that experience, what part felt most helpful? And was there anything that felt frustrating or annoying during the process?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 9,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:33:11.411000Z",
        "message": "Honestly, I don't like using Chrome or Google anymore. I would rather use, like, Meta AI or you know, something like that or Copilot because they're more interactive, and they help you find exactly what you need. Sometimes with a search engine, they misunderstand what you're looking for, especially if you use text to speech. And then you have to start completely over because they"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 10,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:33:40.811000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like the more interactive engines. Meta AI or Copilot, feel more direct and helpful. You mentioned that with Chrome or Google, sometimes it misunderstands what you're after. Especially with text to speech. Can you tell me about a time when a search engine got your query wrong? What happened, and how did you work around it?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 11,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:34:02.211000Z",
        "message": "It was about a week ago. I was up some stuff I needed for a new smartphone I was looking into buying, and it I asked it the simple question. What is the specs of this certain iPhone? And it said something it thought I said something about politics, and I'm just like, okay. Let's take a breather. Let's go back and retype it. Let's just type it and see what it says. And I just found that using Meta AI or Copilot is so much easier than using a search engine anymore."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 12,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:34:33.921000Z",
        "message": "That sounds frustrating, especially when you're just looking for something straightforward, and and it hears something totally different. When you switch to MetaWire or Co Pilot for that same kind of question, like asking about iPhone specs, how did their responses feel different compared to Google or Bing?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 13,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:34:51.861000Z",
        "message": "It basically made me feel like I was talking to a regular person. It should've just something that was AI like meta. Pretty much."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 14,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:35:03.511000Z",
        "message": "Sounds like Meta AI gave you a more conversational vibe. Almost like chatting with a person instead of wrestling with the search engine. When you get answers from a Meta AI or Copilot, do you usually trust what they tell you right away? Or do you ever double check someone?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 15,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:35:17.501000Z",
        "message": "No. I do go look I go look up what they tell me. I do search what they tell me after I talk to them to see if they're correct. Or if there's anything else I should've should've typed in or should've asked. But I do make sure that their answers are pretty on, like, 99 percent. If if it's anything below 98 percent or 97 percent, I go look at a different situation. Alright? Type it in or ask somebody, like, a"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 16,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:35:49.131000Z",
        "message": "So accuracy matters a lot to you. You're pretty careful about double checking. And if something doesn't feel spot on, you'll dig deeper or even ask someone else. Are there any engines, Google, Meta AI, Copilot, Bing, that you trust more than others when sharing information with other people? For example, if you're passing along an answer to a friend, is there 1 you feel most confident quoting?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 17,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:36:13.541000Z",
        "message": "Meta AI and Copilot. If if I know it's pretty spot spot on, I can give them that answer. But sometimes I do tell them go search it for yourself just because I don't want them to think that I gave them a bogus answer or something."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 18,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:36:32.461000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. So Meta AI and Copilot feel reliable, but you still like to give a little disclaimer just in case. Thinking about all these engines, if you had to line them up from"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 19,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:36:42.681000Z",
        "message": "Right."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 20,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:36:43.131000Z",
        "message": "most helpful to least helpful for you, what would that order be and what makes the top 1 stand out?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 21,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:36:55.421000Z",
        "message": "My first 1 would be Meta AI, then the next 1 would be Copilot, then Google and Bing, and all the rest of them. Um, and the only reason I choose Meta AI and Copilot first is because I use them more often than not."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 22,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:37:12.981000Z",
        "message": "Got it. Meta AI first. Copilot next, then Google and Bing further down. You said you use Meta AI and Copilot more more often. Is that mostly because of how interactive they are? Or are there other things about them that make you reach for them first?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 23,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:37:29.291000Z",
        "message": "It's just how interactive they are and how you can almost feel like you're talking to somebody else that's gonna give you the right answer. Possibly, you know, like I said, I do double check their answers."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 24,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:37:44.921000Z",
        "message": "The sense of talking to someone who understands you, seems like big for you. When you picture Google, Meta AI, Copilot, and Bing, as people at a party, what kind of personalities do they each have?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 25,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:38:00.461000Z",
        "message": "They match my personality where I'm kinda bubbly. Happy, go lucky all the time."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 26,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:38:06.860000Z",
        "message": "That's a fun comparison. So Meta AI and Copilot, especially, do they feel like the bubbly happy go lucky types at the party? Or do any of them come across a little differently, like more serious or distant?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 27,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:38:21.771000Z",
        "message": "Sometimes they do come across distant, but most of the time, it's just like you're you're talking to a regular person. I mean, you do have to keep in mind that they are just"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 28,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:38:30.061000Z",
        "message": "Interesting"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 29,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:38:34.031000Z",
        "message": "you do have to keep in mind that they are just a search engine in itself but they do act like a more human than anything."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 30,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:38:45.070000Z",
        "message": "So even though, you know, they're technically just search engines, Meta AI and Copilot still feel pretty human when you use them. Thinking back, say, over the past year, has anything changed"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 31,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:38:54.691000Z",
        "message": "Look."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 32,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:38:58.001000Z",
        "message": "I'm listening. What's on your mind?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 33,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:38:59.161000Z",
        "message": "I think something I think something has changed. Especially when you're using Facebook and that sort of thing to communicate with family and friends. They started using Meta AI as well."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 34,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:39:15.371000Z",
        "message": "That's an interesting shift. So it sounds like people you know have started using Meta AI too. Maybe through Facebook. Can you remember a time when a friend or family member mentioned using MetaAI? Instead of a regular search engine. What happened?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 35,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:39:30.231000Z",
        "message": "Yeah. It was it was just a couple days ago. They're like, hey. We started using Meta AI on Facebook. And I'm like, I've been using it for a while. And they're like, we didn't even know it existed. I said, yeah. It it exists with the new download for Facebook."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 36,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:39:47.321000Z",
        "message": "Thanks for sharing that story. Um, it sounds like people are discovering Meta AI and picking up on it through updates to Facebook. Has seeing your friends start to use Meta AI changed how you use it or how you feel about it at all?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 37,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:40:03.970000Z",
        "message": "No. Not really. I'm gonna always use it. Doesn't mean that I don't double check what I'm searching, but I'm always gonna use it. And I think a lot of that is because I am disabled. So I like to make sure that what I'm searching for is gonna be what I want instead of having to sit there for hours on end."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 38,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:40:24.491000Z",
        "message": "That makes sense. Having a tool that feels responsive and saves you time is really important, especially if it's helping you get exactly what you need. A lot of extra effort. Before we wrap up, is there anything you wish these answer engines could do that they can't do yet? Any features or fixes you'd love to see?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 39,
        "role": "user",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:40:44.280000Z",
        "message": "I wish they would just fix the bugs so people wouldn't be so scared to use them."
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
        "index": 40,
        "role": "bot",
        "time": "2025-09-13T22:40:52.001000Z",
        "message": "That's a good point. Bugs can make people hesitant. If you could wave a magic wand, is there a particular bug or a glitch that's bothered you most lately? Or is it just the general idea that things might not work right?"
      },
      {
        "callId": "06c76ec3fcbd45ac92f4d9a3d",
